title: pizza noodle casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, cook ground beef, onions and bell peppers for 7 to 9 minutes, until meat browns and veggies are crisp.
Drain cooked noodles; add Italian seasoning, pepperoni slices, ripe olives, tomato sauce and paste.
Mix well. Fold in 1 cup of the shredded Mozzarella.
Pour mixture into ungreased 2-quart baking dish.
Top with rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes, until heated throughly and cheese begins to brown.
Sprinkle with parsley (optional).
Makes 6 servings.

title: carrots and walnuts
directions: Cook carrots with water until tender in covered pan over medium heat.
Combine olive oil, nuts, lemon peel and salt in a bowl.
Add carrots.
Toss.
Serve warm.

title: vegetable skillet stew
directions: Cut
pork
into 1/4-inch strips.
Slice broccoli stalks into thin rounds, about 1/8-inch thick.
Break head into small flowerets.
Heat oil and garlic in a wok or a 10-inch skillet. Add pork and broccoli.
Stem pieces.
Cook, stirring constantly over high
heat 5 minutes or until pork is no longer pink. Add broccoli
flowerets,
carrots
and
onions;
reduce heat. Cook, covered, 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring occasionally.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour into skillet. Bring
to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 2 minutes or until sauce is thickened.
Serves 4.

title: potato balls(from leftover potatoes)
directions: Mix leftover potatoes, eggs and onions.
Roll into balls. Roll balls in mixture of cracker crumbs and cheese.
Drop in hot grease and brown.

title: patty's panned pierogies
directions: Yield: 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans.

title: reuben spread
directions: Mix together. Bake in a 325° oven for 30 minutes. Can be put in slow cooker for 30 minutes, then kept warm several hours. Serve with cocktail rye bread or rye crackers.

title: orange blossoms
directions: Combine grated rinds and juice of 2 oranges and 2 lemons.
Add confectioners sugar well and let stand.
Prepare 1 package cake mix according to directions.
Fill greased cupcake pans with 1 teaspoon each of batter. Bake 10 minutes at 350° or until slightly brown.
Roll cakes into icing mixture, coating well.
Place on wax paper.
Makes 7 to 8 dozen.

title: dutch oven dinner
directions: Brown meat lightly in Dutch oven without added fat.
Add salt and remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add cheese.
Cover and cook another 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Spread on crackers or toasted bread, cut small.

title: chicken and artichoke casserole
directions: In a frying pan or Dutch oven, bring chicken broth to a simmer over medium heat.
Place chicken breasts in broth and poach until tender when pierced with a fork (about 15 minutes).
Lift chicken from broth and cool.
Reserve 3/4 cup of the broth for sauce (save remainder for other uses).
When cool enough to handle, remove skin and bones from chicken.
Arrange chicken breasts in shallow 8 x 12-inch baking dish, overlapping them slightly.
Distribute artichoke hearts on top of chicken; set aside.

title: italian white bean and kale soup
directions: In large saucepan, cover beans by 2 inches of water.
Bring to boil on high; boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; let stand 1 hour. Drain.
Heat oil in large saucepan over medium heat.
Add celery, carrot, onion, garlic and Prosciutto.
Cook, stirring frequently, for about 5 minutes.
Add beans, chicken broth and pepper.
Bring to boil over high heat.
Lower heat and simmer for 1 hour, or until beans are tender.

title: easy shrimp creole
directions: Combine all ingredients except shrimp in 1 1/2 quart casserole, breaking up tomatoes with spoon and cover.
Microwave at High for 8 to 12 minutes or until green pepper is tender and sauce is bubbly, stirring once.
Stir in shrimp; cover.
Microwave at High 3 to 5 minutes or until shrimp are just opaque, stirring once or twice. Do not overcook.
Let stand 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
If desired, serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: biscuits
directions: Place mix in large mixing bowl.
Make a well in center.
Add baking soda to milk and stir to dissolve.
Add milk all at once to mix.
Stir with fork just until dough follows fork around bowl. Turn onto lightly floured surface; knead gently 5 strokes.
Roll dough 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter dipped in flour.
Place on ungreased baking sheet; bake in 425° oven for 10 minutes.

title: french lemon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Adjust rack to center position.
Butter and flour round 8-inch cake pan.
Grate lemon peel and mix with sugar; add butter and beat until smooth.
Add eggs and beat until well blended.
Mix baking powder and flour and add to mixture and beat until blended.
Do not overstir.
Pour into pan and bake about 25 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool slightly in pan.

title: italian beef sandwiches
directions: Place roast, fat side up, on rack in a roasting pan.
Roast, uncovered, at 325° about 1 1/2 hours or until thermometer is 145° (medium-rare). Cool for 30 minutes, then cover and chill.

title: butternut balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar in mixing bowl.
Add salt, vanilla, flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Shape dough in one-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes at 375° until light golden brown.
Roll in 1/4 cup powdered sugar while warm. Let cool; roll in powdered sugar again.

title: apple-nut muffins
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add egg.
Add 1/2 flour mixture, mix.
Stir in apple, nuts and milk.
Add remaining flour and mix until barely blended. Grease muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chili cheesy-rice pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, stir together rice and soup.
Transfer rice mixture to greased 9-inch pie plate; press rice evenly over bottom and up sides to form "pie crust.
Pour turkey chili into rice crust.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes or until very hot.
Remove from oven; let set 5 minutes before cutting.
Top each serving with sour cream and sprinkling of green onions, if desired, and serve.

title: kahlua chocolate chip cream cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients until well blended. Serve with bagels, muffins or your favorite type of bread.

title: basic fried rice
directions: Stir fry the onions for about 1 1/2 minutes in the oil, then add the eggs. Once the eggs have set, add the rice and salt to taste. Stir until evenly mixed.

title: broccoli, cheese and rice
directions: Cook rice as directed on package.
While that's cooking, melt butter and saute onions.
Add soup and cheese until melted.
Add thawed broccoli and cooked rice.
Heat through.
Transfer to casserole dish and bake 15 to 20 minutes, until it bubbles, at 350°.

title: green chilies and hominy
directions: Rinse and drain beans.
Rinse and cut each chili into three large pieces.
Saute in small amount of water, onion and garlic. Put into crock-pot or heavy stew pot together with remaining ingredients.
When using crock-pot, allow 4 hours on high or all day on low.
For stew pot, allow 3 hours on low.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add flour and egg yolks and beat 1 minute. Chill. Grease baking sheets.
Make 36 balls of dough the size of small walnuts.
Place 1 1/2-inches apart on prepared sheets.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Using bottom of small glass dipped in sugar, flatten balls to the thickness of 1/4-inch.
Make slight indentation in center of each cookie using thimble or fingertip and fill with jam.
Bake until lightly browned, about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate nut brownies
directions: Beat butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla until smooth.
Combine dry ingredients and stir into batter.
Fold in half of nuts and spread into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle rest of nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Simmer hamburger, taco seasoning and water together.
Add the rest of the ingredients and heat in the microwave.
Serve with crackers or bread chunks.

title: pork chops for company
directions: Saute pork chops to lightly brown in large skillet; cook about 10 minutes until done.
Cut bell peppers in half and trim out seeds to form cup.
Fill each half pepper with cooked rice.
Place bell pepper cups in skillet with pork chops; add mushroom soup and 1/2 can water.
Either continue to cook on top of stove or in the 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Season with black pepper and wine (optional).

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Mix ice cream and peanut butter together on low speed for 1 minute. Pour into pie crust and freeze until firm, about 3 hours. Warm ice cream topping slightly. Spoon over ice cream mixture. Return to freezer. Serve with whipped topping on top of each slice.

title: mexican fudge
directions: Mix
ingredients
together
and pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake
at 350° for 35 minutes.
May be served hot or cold. Serves 12 to 20.

title: crab casserole
directions: Combine 4 cups bread crumbs, eggs, salt, pepper, shrimp, crab, mushrooms, pimentos, onion salt and parsley.
Mix lightly and pour into a large buttered baking dish.
Mix soup, cream and mayonnaise. Pour over first mixture.
Mix 1/2 cup bread crumbs and butter. Sprinkle over casserole.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: squash pickles
directions: Soak squash, onions and peppers in alum and ice water for 30 minutes.
Drain, but do not rinse.
Bring sugar, vinegar, celery seed, mustard seed and pickling spice to a boil.
Add squash, onions and peppers and boil for 5 minutes.
Put in clean canning jars and process in a hot water bath for 5 minutes.

title: chicken and cheese pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water until completely cool.
In a large salad bowl, combine macaroni, chicken, cheese, red pepper, carrots, bacon and olives.
Add dressing and toss well.
Cover and chill.
Makes about 4 main dishes or 6 side dish servings.

title: cottage cheese jello salad
directions: Mix pineapple and Jell-O until dissolved.
Add whipped cream and cottage cheese together, then add to Jell-O mixture.
Pour in bowl or baking dish.
Chill 1 hour.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift together the flour, soda, salt and cocoa.
Add the oil, buttermilk and vanilla to a very smooth batter.
In separate bowl, beat the eggs until thick and foamy.
Gradually add the sugar and continue beating until well blended and fold into the batter until well blended.
Cook in 2 (8-inch) cake pans at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and cottage cheese and spread in 9 x 13 or smaller pan. Pour taco sauce on top of cheese mixture. Add lettuce, tomatoes, green onions and shredded cheese. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: coconut chess pie
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Add oleo, buttermilk, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: broiled scallops
directions: Preheat broiler; spray broiler pan with nonstick vegetable spray.
Coat scallops lightly in bread crumbs; place on prepared pan.
Combine lemon juice and margarine; sprinkle over scallops. Broil 3 to 5 minutes or until cooked thoroughly.
Serve immediately with lemon wedges, if desired.
Makes 2 servings.

title: ravioli
directions: Brown, drain and cool the ground beef.
Mix with ingredients used to make meatballs.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice until half done.
Brown sausage.
Pour off grease from time to time.
Brown onions until golden in a little sausage fat.
Pour 2 1/2 cups boiling water on soup mix.
Mix well.
Place in greased casserole and bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop on waxed paper by teaspoonfuls or place in 9 x 13 inch pan and cut when cool.
May be cooled in refrigerator.
Yield 2-3 1/2 doz. cookies.

title: almond bark candy
directions: Mix pretzels, Rice Krispies and peanuts in a bowl; set aside. Melt white chocolate with peanut butter.
Pour over other ingredients.
Mix well. Drop from teaspoon onto wax paper.
Let dry.
Makes 80 to 90 pieces. Do not bake!

title: easy punch
directions: Mix together and add 1 1/4 cans of water.
Freeze in 1 gallon milk jug (make sure it's not too full).
Shake often and it makes a "slushy."

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch casserole.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes. Serves 6.
Yummy!

title: pie crust(makes 6 to 8 crusts)
directions: In large bowl with lid, add flour, salt and shortening.
Shape up and down until balls start to form.
Add egg, vinegar and water; shake in circular motion until mixed well.
Divide into balls; wrap in plastic wrap and freeze.
Use when needed.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Precook, skin and bone chicken.
Put in baking dish.
Mix soup and milk and pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing as directed on package.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: spanish noodles and ground beef
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat cook beef, chopped green pepper and chopped onion until meat is no longer pink.
Drain. Stir in noodles, tomatoes, water, chili sauce, salt and pepper. Mix well.
Cover and cook over low heat for 15-20 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Stirring frequently.
Add bacon.
Yields:
5 servings.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Combine with celery, onions, green pepper, vinegar, salt, pepper, mustard and eggs.
Toss lightly to mix.
Add oil and bacon.
Toss again.
Spoon into shallow 9-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Broil, with surface of food 3 inches below moderate heat until cheese is melted and golden brown.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar and let them stand for 1 hour.

title: shortcake
directions: Stir together flour, salt, sugar, baking powder and orange peel.
Cut in butter to make a crumbly mixture. Add milk, a tablespoon at a time, to make a slightly sticky dough.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix meat, salt, pepper, garlic, onion and rice.
Roll meat mixture in cabbage leaves; place in pot.
Cover with tomatoes and water.
Bring to boil, turn down heat and cover.
Cook on low heat for 1 hour.

title: scallop-mushroom noodle soup
directions: Bring a large pot of water to a boil.
Meanwhile, shred or mince the ginger.
Cut the mushrooms into thin slices.
Cut the scallions into slivers, 1 1/2-inch long.
If using sea scallops, cut into quarters.

In a large saucepan, bring the chicken broth, ginger, sesame oil and red pepper to a boil over medium-high heat. Add noodles to the first pot of boiling water and cook 3 minutes. When broth comes to a boil, add sea scallops, sprouts, snow peas and mushrooms.
Reduce heat, cover and cook 2 minutes.
Add scallions and cook 30 seconds.
Drain noodles and add.

title: russian eggs
directions: Make deviled eggs using the horseradish sauce and mustard (no quantities given).
Place eggs in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex.
Mix together the remaining ingredients and pour
over the eggs.
Store in refrigerator at least 6 hours or longer.

title: wake up casserole
directions: Layer in 9 x 12 pan the hash brown patties, shredded cheese and ham. Beat eggs, milk, salt and mustard. Pour over first 3 ingredients. Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°. Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: monster cookies
directions: Beat eggs and add other ingredients.
Use small ice cream scoop and drop onto cookie sheet.
Flatten out.
Bake about 12 minutes at 350°.

title: mom's cornbread
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar, vanilla, egg, milk and butter.
Add dry ingredients.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Roll out to 1/4-inch and cut into desired shapes.
Ice with powdered sugar and milk after cookies cool.

title: cream dessert
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip. Spread on top of crust.
Blend together in pan the pudding and milk.
Heat to boil.
Cool and spread on top of cream cheese mixture.
Cover with Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: wassail bowl
directions: Heat the cider and cinnamon stick in a large saucepan; bring to a boil and simmer, covered, 5 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients and simmer, uncovered, for 8 more minutes.
Keep hot over low heat.
Float an orange, studded with cloves.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef. Drain fat.
Add all ingredients and simmer several hours.

title: tea
directions: Combine cinnamon, cloves and 1 quart water in a saucepan. Boil for 20 minutes.
Add 2 more cups of water, jello and sugar. Heat to dissolve.
Add pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Serve hot.
Cloves and cinnamon sticks can be removed, if desired.

title: chicken chip bake
directions: Mix and pile lightly in 8 1/4 x 13 1/4-inch Pyrex baking dish. Sprinkle cheese, then potato chips over contents of dish. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes. Serves 6.

title: chocolate raspberry brownies
directions: Cream butter and 3/4 cup sugar until light and fluffy.
Add the egg yolk and vanilla, beating until thick and silky.
Stir flour, cocoa and salt; mix thoroughly.
Add this butter-sugar mixture and stir until moistened.
Spread dough in ungreased 8 x 8-inch baking pan and put in the freezer to chill for 10 minutes. Heat oven to 325°.
Stir raspberry jam to make it smooth.
Spread over chilled dough and freeze for 5 minutes.
Beat egg whites until frothy and brush about 1/2 over cold raspberry jam.
Scatter walnuts on top and press into place.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes. Remove from the oven and sprinkle with sugar.
Makes 16 small squares.

title: frog eye salad
directions: Combine sugar, flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Gradually stir in pineapple juice and eggs.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring until thick.
Add lemon juice.
Cool mixture to room temperature.
Bring water, remaining 2 teaspoons salt and oil to a boil.
Add acini de pepe and cook at a rolling boil until done.
Drain, rinse with water, drain again and cool to room temperature.
Combine egg mixture and acini.
Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Refrigerate overnight in airtight container.
In morning, add remaining ingredients.
Salad will keep as long as a week in an airtight container in the refrigerator.
Makes 25 servings.

title: strawberry delight punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in tea.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and cool. Mix tea and Jell-O; add chilled fruit juices (orange juice undiluted).
If cold juices are added before Jell-O cools, you will have lumps.
Before serving, add strawberries and ginger ale. Freeze ring of ginger ale with fresh strawberries in it to float in punch bowl.
Serves 24 with seconds.

title: peppers, onions and sausage
directions: Boil sausage for 10 minutes.
Fry peppers and onion in olive oil until brown.
Then fry sausage in peppers and onion for 15 minutes under a slow flame.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix
ingredients
thoroughly.
Form into balls and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: easy potatoes
directions: Mix together, put in a small roaster pan (covered).
Bake at 350° about one hour.
Stir every once in a while.

title: sour cream potato salad(for a large group)
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salt water (1/2 tablespoon of salt to 1 cup of water).
Boil 30 to 40 minutes or until tender.
Drain and cool slightly.
Peel and cut into cubes.
Toss potatoes with chopped onions, salt and pepper.
Pour Italian salad dressing over potatoes; cover and chill thoroughly for 8 hours.
Add celery and chopped egg whites.
Mash egg yolks and mix with mayonnaise.
Add sour cream and horseradish mustard, then fold into salad.
Will serve 20 to 25 people.

title: pineapple-upside down cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add well beaten egg yolks.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add to first mixture, a little at a time alternating with milk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Melt the 1/2 stick margarine in large pan.
Spread the brown sugar over the margarine.
Drain juice from pineapple and arrange slices close together over brown sugar. Pour cake batter over fruit and bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Let rest in pan about 5 minutes, then turn out on cake plate.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Pour pineapple in large casserole dish, 9 x 13-inch or larger. Mix flour, 1/2 cup pineapple and sugar.
Mix well; pour over pineapple.
Sprinkle cheese over the casserole.
Melt oleo; let cool.
Crush crackers in plastic bag; spread over casserole.
Pour oleo over cracker crumbs; mix well.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: haussner's crab cakes
directions: Remove cartilage from crab meat.
Mix breadcrumbs, eggs, mayonnaise and seasonings. Add crabmeat and mix gently so crabmeat stays firm. If mixture is too dry, add more mayonnaise.
Shape gently into cakes.
Fry into oil approximately 5 minutes on each side.
Brown well.
Makes 6 or 7 good sized cakes.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix and drop by teaspoons into shells and bake at 350° at least 20 minutes.
Makes 24 tarts.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Combine pineapple, sugar and salt.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix unflavored gelatin to 1/4 cup boiling water until the texture is sugary.
Let cool.
Combine pineapple mixture and Cool Whip.
Cream the cheese.
Mix all ingredients together and chill. Top with mandarin oranges and serve.

title: broccoli buffet casserole
directions: Partially cook broccoli.
Drain and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add broccoli and put in 9 x 13-inch dish. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put rice in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put broccoli on rice and then the cut up, cooked chicken.
Mix the mushroom soup with milk and pour over chicken and vegetables.
Put a package of onion soup mix over mixture and top casserole with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jalapeno cornbread with meat
directions: Combine corn meal, milk, eggs, salt, soda, drippings (or oil) and corn.
Mix well and set aside.
Brown ground beef and drain. Pour half of batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.
Sprinkle cheese, onion, slices of pepper and meat.
Top with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° (325° for glass) for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: roach exterminating formula(helpful hint)
directions: Add water to form soft dough.
Cream ingredients.
Place dough in cracks where bugs live.
I put a teaspoon in an old "paper" carton and then when formula gets hard, throw it away.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients, add shortening, blend into flour mixture. Add milk.
Mix into ball.
Flour board and pat ball out with roller, cut into biscuits.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.
(For strawberry shortcake, add 1/2 cup sugar and a dash of nutmeg.)

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Cook potatoes and mash with 1 stick butter plus 3/4 pound cheese. Cook noodles; drain. Add 1 stick butter, salt and pepper. Saute onions in 1 stick butter. Pour noodles in 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Spread mashed potatoes over top of noodles. Spread onions on top and the rest of cheese. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: parmesan fillets(turkey or chicken)
directions: Mix cheese, flour, basil and pepper with butter.
Place fillets in greased baking dish and spread mix over top.
Cover and bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes more.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients. Shape to form 6 patties. Brown on both sides in oleo.

title: jambalaya-spanish rice
directions: Melt margarine in a skillet over medium heat.
Add onion, green pepper and ground beef.
Cook, stirring often, until meat is browned.
Spoon off excess fat.
Drain tomatoes, measuring juice. Add water to juice to make 1 1/2 cups.
Add the liquid, tomatoes, salt, sugar, thyme and bay leaf to ground beef mixture.

title: osgood pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat eggs separately.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in unbaked pie shell.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Roll beef in small balls and coat with flour.
Cook gently in small amount of Wesson oil.
Cook onion with meat.
Add soup, mushrooms and sour cream.
Serve over noodles.

title: chicken wings marinade
directions: Mix and marinate at least an hour.
Cook over hot coals on your Webber for best results.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo; add 1 egg alternately with flour, salt and cocoa until all dry ingredients and eggs are mixed.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 300°.
Put marshmallow cream on hot cake.

title: farmer mc muffins
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease all of cupcake tin.
Form bread to fit in each hole.
Put 1/2 slice of cheese in bread, then add egg to each.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes, depending on how you like your egg.

title: chile con queso dip
directions: Place cheese in a double boiler and remaining ingredients. Heat until cheese is completely melted and onion is soft.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Place cheeses in small mixer bowl.
Let stand at room temperature until softened.
Add onion and Worcestershire sauce. Blend on low speed.
Beat on medium speed until fluffy, scraping side and bottom of bowl. Cover. Chill at least 8 hours. Shape mixture into 1 large ball.
Roll in parsley.
Place on serving plate.
Cover.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Serve with crackers.

title: louisiana shrimp
directions: Place cleaned shrimp in baking dish.
Melt butter.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour over shrimp.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve in bowl with crusty bread for dipping.
Serves 6.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cut up carrots; boil until tender.
Drain, saving 1/2 cup of the liquid.
Combine liquid with onion, horseradish, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Pour over cooked carrots that have been put in a greased casserole.
Top with crumbs mixed with butter.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: 1st Layer:
Crush all but 8 cookies.
Melt butter and add to crushed cookies.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and place in freezer while making second layer.

title: minced clam dip
directions: Drain clams.
Mix ingredients to creamy stage.
Pour into lettuce lined bowl in center of tray of chips.

title: new potato casserole
directions: Boil unpeeled potatoes; slice.
Combine cheese, mayonnaise and onion; gently stir into potatoes.
Place in a greased casserole and top with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: puff pastry chicken bundles
directions: Unfold pastry sheets, roll
each sheet to 12 x 10-inches.
Cut into four (6
x
5-inch) rectangles;
shape each into an oval by trimming off
corners.
Spread each oval with about 1 1/2 tablespoons of
cheese.
Sprinkle
chicken with salt and pepper and place in center of pastry oval.
Fold pastry around chicken, completely enclosing.
Moisten
edge
with
water and press firmly to seal.
Place
seam
side down on baking sheet. Use remaining pastry to decorate bundles, making twisted ropes or heart shapes. Combine
egg
and water, brush over bundles. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes
or
until
golden brown.
Serves four.
Garnish with curly endive.

title: lentil-ham soup
directions: Put lentils in crock-pot.
Add carrots, onion, celery and parsley.
Stir in salt, marjoram, pepper and bay leaf.
Place ham bone on top.
Add water; cover and cook on low heat for 9 hours. Lift ham bone from soup; remove meat from bone and chop.
Return meat to soup.
Makes 10 servings.

title: overnight marinated vegetable salad
directions: Bring sugar, oil, vinegar, water, salt and pepper to a boil. Cool and pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: best ever dumplings
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Work in shortening with a knife or fingertips; add milk to make a soft dough.
These are dropped a tablespoon at a time on boiling soup or stew for the last 15 or 20 minutes of cooking.
Kettle must be covered tightly and cover must not be removed during cooking. Makes 12 to 15 dumplings.
Serves 4.

title: natalie's chicken vegetable pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased casserole.

title: chicken rice salad
directions: Add lemon juice to mayonnaise; blend well. Combine with remaining ingredients, except lettuce cups. Mix lightly and chill. Serve in individual lettuce cups. Garnish with additional sliced olives or paprika.

title: jalapeno cheese beer soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until transparent.
Add flour and brown lightly.
Slowly blend in the chicken broth and Worcestershire sauce.
Add carrots and celery.
Cook until tender.
Add milk, cheese and beer.
Heat thoroughly, but do not boil.

title: easy ham pate
directions: Hollow out center of loaf of French bread, tearing small amount of bread around edges.
Mix ham chunks in blender or food processor until smooth.
Add mustard, allspice and softened butter.
Mix all together in blender.
Slice cheeses in strips. Place a layer of cheese and pickles in loaf.
Stuff with ham mixture.
Chill for 1 hour.
Slice and serve.

title: caesar salad
directions: Chop anchovies and mash garlic.
Add olive oil.

title: pumpkin chip loaf
directions: Cream
oleo
and sugar.
Blend in eggs; beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with pumpkin, beginning and ending with dry
ingredients.
Stir in chips and nuts.	Sprinkle the top
with 1/4
cup
chopped	walnuts
(only 1/2 cup goes into batter). Bake in a greased 9 x 6-inch loaf pan at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes, or until it tests done.
Glaze when cool.

title: fried turnip(kalrotbiff)
directions: Soak slices of cooked turnip in vinegar for a few minutes and drain.
Dip the slices in a mixture of flour, salt and pepper and fry in bacon grease or oil.
Place on heated platter and keep warm while frying sliced onions.
Scald the pan with a little water and pour over the turnip and onions.

title: morton meat loaf
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cinnamon tea rolls
directions: Unroll dough onto lightly floured wax paper.
Press perforations to seal.
Brush with butter.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over dough.
Roll up jelly roll fashion, starting at long side.
Cut into 1-inch slices.
Place in a lightly greased miniature muffin pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and drizzle with orange glaze.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Cream
butter
and
sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add lemon juice and mix well.
Pour into unbaked
pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm in the middle.

title: potatoes and ham au gratin
directions: Combine margarine, flour and dry mustard; cook over low heat, stirring constantly until bubbly.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Cook until smooth and thick.
Season sauce with salt and pepper.
Add 1 1/2 cups cheese, stirring until melted.
Stir in ham and onion.
Alternate layers of potatoes and sauce in greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Add remaining cheese and bake until cheese is melted.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: glazed walnuts
directions: Cook sugar and sour cream to soft-ball stage. Add walnuts and stir. Pour onto wax paper and spread to separate nuts or may be broken after mixture sets.

title: chickpea casserole
directions: Soak the chickpeas overnight in water to cover.
Drain and add water to cover to a depth of 1 1/2 inches.
Add salt and simmer 2 hours or longer, until the chickpeas are tender.
Meanwhile, chop the tomatoes and slice the onions.
Heat the oil in a saucepan. Add the onions and cook until wilted.
Add the tomatoes, tomato paste, water and spices.
Add the chickpeas and simmer 30 minutes longer.
Serve hot over rice, garnished with the red onion cut into rings and chopped cilantro.
Makes 12 servings (1 cup each). Preparation time:
2 hours and 30 minutes.

title: coconut frosting
directions: Melt butter, then add all ingredients.
Cook at medium heat for 10 minutes.
Add coconut and nuts after you have added all other ingredients.

title: breakfast strata
directions: Cube bread and cover bottom of a 13 1/2 x 9-inch glass baking dish with the cubes.
Layer cooked bacon, diced ham, sauteed veggies or sausage over bread.
Sprinkle cheese on top of meat or veggies.
In a large bowl, mix eggs, milk, mustard and salt.
Pour into baking dish.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.

title: miss iva's microwave pralines
directions: Must have a candy thermometer.

title: party mix
directions: Melt butter; stir in onion salt, garlic salt, celery salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Place pretzels, cereals and peanuts in a large roasting pan.
Pour butter mixture over; toss to coat. Cover and bake 30 minutes in a preheated 250° oven.
Remove cover, stir mixture and bake another 30 minutes.
Makes 8 cups.

title: carrots and onions
directions: Peel carrots; slice long and thin in short pieces.
Cook carrots in bouillon water.
Cover for 15 minutes; stir occasionally.
Combine remaining ingredients; simmer for 10 minutes.

title: peach delight
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and flour 2 round pans, 9 x 1 1/2-inches.
Drain peaches, reserving sauce.
Add enough water to reserved sauce to measure 1 1/2 cups.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package, except substitute sauce mixture for the water. Pour batter into pans.
Bake and cool as directed.

title: sour cream lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in a saucepan.
Add cold water; stir until smooth.
Add lemon juice gradually.
Add boiling water and butter.
Bring to a boil.
Add lemon peel and egg yolks. Pour in a large bowl and cool for 10 minutes.
Add sour cream and pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: spaghetti loaf
directions: Prepare spaghetti sauce
as
directed on package.
Brown meat. Add 1/2 cup sauce.
Add
spaghetti.
Pack into greased 8 x 14-inch loaf pan.
Bake at
350° for 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes; unmold.
Pour remaining hot sauce over loaf.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: layered tostada dip
directions: Combine beans and taco seasoning; mix well.
Combine avocados, Miracle whip, bacon bits, onion and seasonings.
Mix well.
Layer bean mixture, avacado mixture, olives, tomatoes, chilies and cheese in 9x13 dish.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Beat egg yolks, then add dry ingredients.
Add milk and vanilla, then add nuts.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: apricot balls
directions: Finely cut up or grind the dried apricots.
Mix apricots, coconut and condensed milk.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll each in confectioners sugar.
Chill at least 2 hours and serve.
No cooking!
Store in refrigerator.
Makes about 4 dozen candies.

title: party chicken
directions: Melt the butter in an electric frying pan. Add the Good Seasons packet and stir.
Brown the chicken on both sides in this mixture.
Remove the chicken from the pan and place in a casserole dish.

title: baked squash
directions: Cook squash in small amount of water until tender, drain well and mash. Combine with butter, sour cream, onions, salt, pepper and other seasonings. Place in buttered casserole; top with bread crumbs and reheat when ready to serve in 350° oven until hot for 15-20 minutes. Serves 6.

title: special fried chicken
directions: Marinate chicken covered with salad dressing in the refrigerator for 8 hours.
Combine eggs and water; mix well. Combine flour and seasonings in a plastic bag.
Shake to mix. Drain chicken.
Place 2 to 3 pieces in the flour mixture; shake well.
Dip into the egg mixture and shake well.
Repeat with all the chicken pieces.
Place chicken in hot grease at 350° and fry 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: busy day pot roast
directions: Place meat in roasting pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Pour over the roast.
(Do not add salt.)
Cover pan and bake in 325° oven for about 3 hours.
Check roast occasionally and add more water if needed.
Baste every 30 minutes.
The pan drippings make an excellent gravy.
I serve the gravy with cornbread and mashed potatoes.
If the gravy is too thin, add a little cornstarch or flour.
If it is too thick, add some water.

title: peachy chutney
directions: Combine all ingredients in Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil and simmer uncovered for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until mixture is thickened and deep brown.
Pour into hot canning jars, leaving 1/2-inch space at top.
Remove air bubbles.
Process for 10 minutes in boiling water.
Remove jars from water and let cool, 12 to 24 hours.
Yields 6 pint jars.

title: chicken quick
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Wash chicken and salt top.
Place in large casserole pan.
Cut up carrots in long sections.
Cut up potatoes in medium size pieces.
Cut up onions and garlic.
Add all vegetables in casserole pan with chicken.
Add water and honey over vegetables.
Sprinkle in tarragon.
Place in oven.
Bake approximately 90 minutes, covered with foil for 45 minutes, then uncovered for remainder of time.

title: bacon-topped cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese and sour cream in a large mixing bowl; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until smooth.
Add shredded cheeses, onion, pickle relish, horseradish and seasonings; beat at low speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Cover; chill thoroughly.

title: fried poki
directions: Combine all ingredients except shoyu.
Mix well.
Refrigerate for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Just before frying, pour shoyu over fish (just enough to wet fish pieces).
Sear fish cubes on high heat in about 2 tablespoons oil in frying pan.
Serve hot.

title: raisin apricot glazed ham
directions: For glaze, in a small bowl stir together well preserves, almonds, raisins and lemon juice. Place ham in a shallow roasting pan. Bake in a 325 degree oven for 2 hours (allow 15 minutes per pound) or until thermometer registers 140 degrees. Spoon glaze over ham once or twice during the last 30 minutes of cooking time. Slice thinly to serve. Serves 32.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need 1 medium clay pot and spoon (clean) and 1 stem of silk flowers.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix some nuts in mix; save some and sprinkle rest on top. Bake ingredients in a Bundt or loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: deep fried cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower in 2-inches water approximately 10 to 12 minutes or until tender.
Drain and pat dry.
Heat oil to 360°, about 1 or 2-inches.
Mix bread crumbs and paprika.
Dip cauliflower in egg, salt and pepper mixture. Coat with bread crumb mixture.
Fry 8 to 10 flowerets at a time in hot oil. Turn occasionally.
Cooking time is 2 minutes.
Drain.
Keep warm in a 200° oven 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: pepper steak
directions: Over medium heat in a large frypan, put oil and steak and cook steak on both sides.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice. Simmer 20 to 30 minutes until pepper is tender.
If it dries out, add a little more beef broth.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hamburger & potato packets
directions: 1. Mix hamburger and onion soup mix together, shape into 8 patties.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in a tightly closed container.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs; add oil and stir.
Sift dry ingredients and add to oil mixture and beat well.
Add pineapple (don't drain) and carrots and beat again.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° about 45 to 50 minutes, until done.

title: vegetable frittata
directions: Heat skillet; add oil or margarine.
Add mushrooms, zucchini, green pepper and green onion; cook and stir over medium heat, about 5 minutes.
Sprinkle diced tomatoes over the top.
Mix together the eggs, water, mustard, salt and pepper; pour over veggies in skillet.
Cover; cook for 5 to 10 minutes, or until eggs are set.
Sprinkle cheese and paprika over the top; cover until cheese is melted.
Cut into wedges to serve.

title: chili pasado con queso
directions: For dried chilies, use 6 cups water to boil.
Remove from heat.
Put chilies in water 10 minutes.
Drain and dice.

title: ranch style deviled eggs
directions: Remove egg yolks, reserving egg whites. In small bowl, mash egg yolks. Stir in dressing, then season to taste with salt and pepper. Spoon into egg whites. Cover and chill 1 hour. Garnish, if desired, with parsley and sprinkle with paprika.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add cooked rice and rest of ingredients.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: baked potato slims(vegetables)
directions: Slice the potatoes into 1/2-inch strips.
Mix water, oil and Tabasco sauce. Dip potato strips in mixture. Combine Parmesan with Shake 'n Bake combination.
Shake until evenly coated. Bake potatoes in a single layer on a cookie sheet lined with foil for 30 to 35 minutes in a 400° oven.
Good side dish or snack.

title: marinade for salmon (or other fish)
directions: Mix together and spread on fish.
Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes before grilling or broiling.

title: mexican dip
directions: Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
To assemble, spread jalapeno bean dip on large serving dish.
Top with avocado mixture.
Sprinkle over this the onions, tomatoes and green chilies.
Add sour cream mixture and sprinkle olives on top.
Cover with shredded cheese.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill.
Serve with Ritz crackers or chips.

title: tangy flank steak
directions: Place steak in large shallow container.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over steak.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours, turning steak often.
Remove steak from marinade; grill over hot coals 10 to 12 minutes on each side.
Serves 4.

title: chicken with lemons and asparagus
directions: Gently pound chicken between 2 sheets of waxed paper to make cutlets. In a plastic bag or shallow dish, mix flour, salt and pepper. Dredge chicken in flour mixture until coated. Remove chicken, saving excess flour. In a large heavy skillet, heat butter and oil until bubbling, but not browned. Add chicken and brown on both sides. Remove chicken and reduce heat.

title: kentucky cream pie(makes 2)
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Mix milk and egg yolks.
Add to flour and sugar mixture.
Add butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly as it will scorch, until thick.
Add vanilla after thickened.
Use reserved whites for meringue, adding 1 tablespoon sugar.
Beat until peaks are formed.
Pour cooked mixture into pie shells.
Top with meringue.
Bake until brown.

title: skinny fries
directions: Slice 4 potatoes in French fry style.
Pat dry.
Use oil to lightly coat fries.
(Do not allow potatoes to get greasy.)
Spray cookie sheet lightly with Pam and spread fries flat on sheet. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Flip fries and bake for 10 minutes more.
Contains 140 calories per 4-ounce serving.

title: orange dump salad
directions: Mix and chill for 1 hour or overnight.

title: no measure cake
directions: Do not mix cake mix according to directions.

title: italian gravy(for tricia's meatballs)
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot. Simmer 3 hours.

title: praline pumpkin pie
directions: Mix butter and brown sugar together; add the nuts.
Spread on bottom of crust and pat smooth with fingers.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.

title: applesauce fruit cake
directions: Grease pan (angel food cake pan) well.
Heat oven to 300°. Prepare fruit.
Sift a portion of flour over fruit, mixing it in lightly.
Sift remaining flour with soda and spices.
Cream shortening well.
Add sugar gradually, creaming well.
When light and fluffy, stir in well beaten eggs.
Add applesauce which has been drained quite dry.
Add dry ingredients gradually, stirring in well.
Add fruits and seasonings.
Mix thoroughly.
Turn into prepared pan and bake in slow oven about 1 1/2 hours.
Cool. Store in cool, dry place with a piece of apple.

title: make your own finger paints(child-approved)
directions: Though most parents leave finger painting to preschool and kindergarten classes, there may be moments when even adults have the urge to get their hands in the "stuff" and enjoy this simple art form at home with their children.

title: homemade barbecue
directions: Cook beef and pork until done.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer.
Good served with fries, hush puppies and slaw or on buns with slaw and tomato.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Place in the refrigerator to chill and serve.

title: crispy herb baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease Pyrex dish with nonstick spray. Mix potato flakes, garlic and Parmesan cheese.
Dip chicken into melted margarine; roll into potato mix to coat.
Place in baking dish; sprinkle any uncoated areas with mixture.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes, or until golden.

title: green apple mignonnette sauce
directions: In a 3 1/2 cup jar, combine lime juice, apple, garlic, tomato, sugar, anchovies and chilies.
Use or cover tightly and refrigerate the sauce.
Keeps ready to use up to 1 month.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: peppermint ice cream pie
directions: Let ice cream thaw while making crust.
Melt German chocolate with butter the size of a walnut.
Add Rice Krispies and mix well. Press in pie pan.
Put in freezer for a few minutes.
Add softened ice cream and freeze.

title: lemon chicken with thyme(makes 4 servings)
directions: In a plastic bag, shake together flour, salt, and pepper.
Add the chicken and shake to coat.
Remove chicken and reserve excess flour.
In a large skillet, warm 1 tablespoon oil over medium heat.
Brown chicken on one side for 5 minutes.
Add remaining oil; turn the chicken and brown well on the other side.
Transfer chicken to plate and set aside.

title: egg nog
directions: Place all ingredients, except ice, in a blender.
Cover and process at liquify with motor running.
Remove feeder cap and add ice cubes, one at a time.
Continue to process until smooth.
Pour into serving glasses.
Garnish with nutmeg.

title: sausage cheese bites
directions: In a skillet, cook and crumble sausage.
Drain.
In a large bowl, combine biscuit mix and cheese.
Add the sausage and stir until well blended.
Stir in water just until mixed.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes or until golden.
Baked bites may be frozen. Reheat at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Pour over sweetened potato mixture and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fat free bean dip
directions: Layer in order listed; eat with tortilla chips.

title: lime or orange jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1 cup pineapple juice.
Put juice in 1 cup measuring cup (add enough water to make 1 cup).
Bring juice to a boil in saucepan.
Add Jell-O to dissolve.
Stir sour cream and add to Jell-O.
Mix and add pineapple.
Refrigerate.

title: lemon chicken and rice
directions: Season chicken with salt, pepper and paprika.
Brown chicken in oil in a large nonstick skillet over high heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed. Fluff with a fork.
Serves 4.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut tops off green peppers.
Remove seeds; rinse peppers. Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place peppers in baking dish. Mix together Spanish rice and ground beef.
Stuff into peppers. Cook at 350° for 30 minutes, until peppers are tender and are hot through.
Top with cheese slices; cook until melted.
Enjoy.

title: oreo cookie delight
directions: Melt margarine.
Crumble Oreos, except for 1 cup of cookie crumbs.
Mix Oreos and margarine together.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread softened ice cream over cookie crust.
Pour chocolate fudge over the layer of ice cream and then spread the Cool Whip.
Sprinkle remaining cookie crumbs on top.
Freeze overnight.
Yum!!!

title: soda pop cake
directions: Blend cake mix, soda pop and egg whites until moistened.
Beat as directed on package.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Combine soda and water and add to dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and salt to mayonnaise.
Mix all together and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350° in 8 x 12-inch cake pan.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Coat a small glass or ceramic baking dish with cooking oil spray. Arrange chicken in dish and sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste. Cover the chicken with sauerkraut. Pour the dressing evenly over all and top with cheese and parsley. Cover and bake 1 hour or until fork-tender.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix together
cake
mix,
oleo and egg.
Save 1 cup for topping.
Mix
salt,
eggs,
pumpkin spice, pumpkin, condensed milk, sugar and vanilla; pour on top of cake mixture.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown onion and meat; drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: rhubarb swirl
directions: Mix sugar, water and red hots in pan and boil to dissolve red hots.
Mix and roll out biscuit mix as for biscuits.
Press rhubarb into dough. Roll up and slice.
Place in a 9 x
13-inch pan, cut side down.
Pour hot sugar mixture over rolls. Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Top with whipped cream and serve.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar and salt in medium bowl with mixer until foamy.
Beat in sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Continue beating for 4 minutes or until stiff glossy peaks form when beaters are lifted.
Fold in almond extract and coconut.
Drop by teaspoon about 1 inch apart.
Place cherry piece on each. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, until edges are light brown.
Cool on cookie sheet for 10 minutes before removing to cool completely.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Chop or mix cabbage, onion, celery and green pepper in food processor.
Combine oil, sugar and vinegar.
Mix well.
Pour dressing over other ingredients, mixing well.
Refrigerate overnight.
This slaw will keep 2 to 3 weeks.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Make cake mix into two 9-inch layers and cool. Place 1 layer in bottom of punch bowl. Layer 1/2 each cherry pie filling, pudding, pineapple, banana (one) and whipped topping. Repeat layers and garnish with coconut and/or pecans and cherries.

title: marinated shrimp(serves 6)
directions: Shell, devein and wash shrimp.
Combine rest of ingredients in saucepan large enough to hold ALL ingredients.
Add shrimp. Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Chill and drain.
Garnish with lemon slices and parsley if desired.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Set aside. Beat egg. Add milk. Add oil. Add to cornmeal mixture; stir just enough to mix. Grease pan and fill half full. Bake at 425° until lightly browned, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: banana cookies (diabetic)
directions: Combine margarine, banana, vanilla, egg and fructose in mixing bowl.
Beat until smooth. Add baking powder, salt and flour, mixing to blend well.
Drop by teaspoons onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375 for 8 to 10 minutes. Yield: 40 cookies.

title: creamed green beans and onions
directions: Cook beans as directed on package; drain.
Save liquid. Add enough
milk to liquid to make 2 1/4 cups.	Melt butter in saucepan.
Add
flour, Cavender's seasoning; stir until blended. Add liquid gradually, stirring, and cook until thickened. Combine with
cooked
green
beans	and
onions.
Cook
until thickened. Stir
into	buttered
quart
baking
dish. Sprinkle with bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and paprika.	Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: quick microwave rice pudding
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, butter, salt and spices together and add the rest of the ingredients.
Pour mixture into a buttered, 1 1/2-quart size baking dish.
Cover with wax paper.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except potatoes in a bowl.
Adjust seasoning.
Add potatoes and mix well.
Turn into casserole dish and bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes on second rack.

title: three bean salad with sweet and sour dressing
directions: Combine apricot preserves, vinegar and celery seeds in a bowl. Add kidney beans, green and yellow beans and sliced onion. Toss well to combine.
Adjust seasonings with salt and fresh ground pepper to taste.

title: pepperoncini macaroni salad
directions: Cook, drain and cool macaroni in cold water; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and let marinate for at least 30 minutes in the refrigerator.

title: easter egg candy
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl and then shape into Easter "eggs."
Chill overnight in refrigerator.
Melt 2 packages of chocolate morsels over hot, not boiling water.
Cover half of eggs by spreading warm chocolate on with a knife.
Let harden and cool well, then cover the other side the same way.
You may then decorate with colored trim or flowers.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions and let cool.
Punch holes all over cake and cover with cream of coconut and Eagle Brand milk.
Spread whipped cream over top and sprinkle with coconut. Refrigerate and let stand 2 hours before serving.

title: saucy swiss steak
directions: Cut beef into serving size pieces.
Coat with flour and pound into beef with mallet to tenderize.
Brown beef in oil in a 10-inch skillet.
Push beef to side.
Cook and stir onions next to beef until tender.

title: rabbit pot pie
directions: Cook rabbit 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Take meat off bone; cut into small pieces. Place rabbit meat and other ingredients listed except for thickening in suitable-size saucepan; cook until vegetables are done. Add salt and pepper and thickening. Turn off heat. Let stand 15 to 20 minutes.

title: old fashioned baked beans
directions: Pick over your dried beans and rinse. Add beans to large bowl and add water. Let soak 8 hours or overnight. Place in large pot and boil uncovered. Add the remaining ingredients, except for the pork. Stir until blended. Lay the bacon or pork slices on top. Cover and simmer 6 to 8 hours, stirring occasionally. Add enough liquid while simmering to barely cover the beans, as necessary. Test for tenderness. Serves 4 to 6.

title: carrot zucchini casserole
directions: Steam vegetables for 5 minutes.
Drain, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
Combine reserved liquid, mayonnaise, onion, and horseradish.
Add to vegetables, stirring well.
Spoon into 8-inch square baking dish.
Combine crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or bake in microwave for 5 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: microwave broccoli casserole
directions: Combine onion, celery, green pepper and margarine.
Microwave 3 minutes on High temperature.
Stir in thawed broccoli and cook 5 minutes on High.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Add rice, soup and cheese.
Microwave 8 minutes on High.
Garnish with onion rings and microwave 1 minute on High.
Total Time:
17 minutes.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream butter, sugar, egg, milk and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder; add to creamed mixture.
Chill.
Cut.
Bake in 375° oven about 8 minutes.

title: chewy brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in saucepan.
Remove from stove. Add rest of ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Place eggs in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Add pineapple (undrained).
Stir in sugar and flour.
Melt butter.
Add bread cubes and coat with the butter.
Put on top of ingredients in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: corn flaky potatoes
directions: Peel or scrub and dry potatoes; dip in oil, then in crumbs. Place on baking sheet.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: fresh tomato sauce
directions: Plunge tomatoes in boiling water for 30 seconds.
Remove them with a slotted spoon and run under cold water.
Remove skins and press out the seeds.
Peel the garlic and slice into big pieces. In a frying pan brown garlic lightly.
Remove some or all of the garlic depending on how much garlic you like.
(Save the garlic not used in sauce to mash and add to salad dressing.)
Add tomatoes to oil; bring to a boil and simmer 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Mash tomatoes and any garlic still in the pan.
Stir in basil.
The sauce goes well with any kind of pasta.
Sprinkle with cheese and other herbs (rosemary, thyme, marjoram) if you like.
(May be substituted for the basil.
Use only 1 to 2 tablespoons.)

title: chewy coconutty german chocolate cookies
directions: Combine melted chocolate and peanut butter.
Stir until smooth.
Add milk, salt, vanilla and coconut.
Stir until blended. Drop by teaspoon on well-greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from sheet while warm.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: nannie's ripe tomato ketchup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large sauce pot. Bring to a hard boil and boil for 20 minutes. Pour into canning jars and seal while hot.

title: mac and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until tender, drain.
Place in ungreased 2-quart or layer casserole.
Make white sauce by melting butter.
Don't scorch, melt over low heat, stirring in flour to make paste. Slowly add milk so not to lump, stirring constantly (turn off heat while you stir).
Cut cheese into chunks and add to sauce.
Cook over medium heat.
Stir to keep from burning.
Pour over macaroni. Bake at 350° to 375° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Layer chicken and broccoli in greased casserole dish.
Combine soup, mayo, lemon juice and milk; mix thoroughly.
Pour over chicken and broccoli evenly.
Sprinkle stuffing evenly over soup mixture.
Pour melted butter over stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

Sprinkle chicken parts with salt and pepper and refrigerate until time to cook. Arrange chicken skin side down in shallow baking pan. Bake 15 minutes. Turn to baste with barbecue sauce. Bake 15 to 35 minutes more, basting every 10 to 15 minutes. To test doneness, insert fork in thickest part of chicken; juices should be clear.

title: mint brownie chip cookies
directions: Combine brownie mix, eggs and oil.
Beat until just blended with a spoon (do not use a blender).
Stir in chopped mint and extract.
Stir in chocolate morsels and pecans.

title: chocolate bonbons
directions: In a large bowl, combine the powdered sugar, graham cracker crumbs, pecans and coconut.
In a small saucepan, melt butter and peanut butter.
Pour over coconut mixture.
Blend until mixture is moistened.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
In another small saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate pieces with shortening. Dip individually into chocolate mixture to coat.
Place balls on waxed paper and chill.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook chicken.* Cool, debone and cut into bite size pieces. Combine soups, chicken broth and tomatoes. Mix with chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan or baking dish. Crush Doritos into small pieces and stir in. Spoon salsa con queso on top and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes. I like to serve extra chips with it at the table.

title: midwest vegetable crunch salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine ingredients, except bacon. Cover and marinate in refrigerator, turning occasionally, 4 hours or overnight.
Just before serving, toss with bacon.

title: kuwaiti fish stew
directions: Fry onions in the bottom of a pan.
Place fish on top of the fried onions.
Dust fish with turmeric, coriander and cardamon. Fry until onions are brown.
Add herbs, salt, pepper, dried lemons and tomato paste.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer at least 20 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Put first 7 ingredients in loaf pan.
Pour tomato sauce over it.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes (or until done).

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix salad dressing and sugar together, then add vanilla and cocoa.
Beat well.
Then add flour and water, a little at a time. Mix until all blended.
Pour into a greased and floured cake pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Check doneness by using toothpick test.
Cool, then frost.

title: kentucky corn pudding
directions: Blend butter, sugar, salt and flour with electric mixer.
Add eggs, beating well.
Stir in corn and milk.
Pour into buttered casserole dish and bake at 325°.
Stir halfway through cooking. When done, pudding will be a golden brown.
The mixture can be assembled ahead of time and kept refrigerated.
In this case, shake well before pouring into baking dish.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add garlic, buttermilk and egg.
Fry tablespoons of the butter in deep hot fat (375°) for 2 to 3 minutes until golden brown.
Drain.
Serve hot.

title: chicken or turkey fricassee
directions: Cook chicken in salted water; cover until done.
Bone and cut into bite size pieces.
Use leftover turkey this way, too.
Remove fat from broth; measure broth to make 4 cups.
Melt butter; add onion and celery; saute until onion is transparent.
Combine chicken with onion and celery; add broth, eggs, soup, cheese, crackers, salt and pepper.
Put mixture in shallow casserole, 9 x 13-inch.
Bake uncovered in preheated 350° oven about 1 hour or until bubbly.
Serves 12.

title: pizza sauce to can
directions: Put all in pan and simmer for 3 hours.
Put in hot jars and cold pack 15 to 20 minutes.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter or margarine in pan or casserole dish, mix other ingredients and spoon over butter in dish.
Add 1 can pie filling (any kind).
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: apple salad
directions: Cut up apples and sprinkle with Fruit Fresh.
Add all other ingredients.
Use salad dressing or sour cream or cream cheese (according to your taste).
Mix all together.

title: traditional eastern curry
directions: Fry onions and garlic in oil.
Add curry powder and tomatoes; cook over low heat for a few minutes.
Add meat and brown.
Add all remaining ingredients; simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice.
Top with coconut, chopped dried fruit, chopped tomatoes and onions, banana, raisins, etc.

title: delicious pork chop and wild rice
directions: Combine rice and water in greased 13 x 9-inch dish.
Season and arrange pork chops into rice.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, covered.
Combine soup and milk.
Pour over casserole. Heat until bubbly.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Make a brown roux with flour and shortening; add onion, garlic, bell pepper and parsley and saute. Add tomatoes, red pepper, bay leaves, celery seed, and thyme; add shrimp and let cook slowly for 1 hour. Cook in heavy boiler with tight fitting cover. About 30 minutes before serving, add Worcestershire sauce. Serve over rice.

title: jalapeno casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and beef together.
Grate the cheese.
Brown the ground beef and drain.
Put half of the jalapeno mixture in a greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle half of the cheese on top.
Layer the ground beef over the cheese.
Pour the rest of the jalapeno mixture over beef.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Remove from oven and sprinkle remaining cheese on top. Return to oven and slightly brown.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and confectioners sugar together; beat until smooth.
Add pie filling and refrigerate for several hours.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix well.
Store in covered glass jar.

title: beef and biscuit casserole
directions: Brown ground meat and onion.
Add tomato sauce; simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Mix cheese, sour cream and egg thoroughly and add to meat mixture.
Do not cook.
Put 1/2 of crescent rolls flat in bottom of pan.
Pour mixture in and top with other half of crescent rolls.
Bake at 375° until top is golden brown.

title: pepper relish
directions: Put peppers in pan and add vinegar and Sure-Jell; add margarine.
Bring to full boil on high heat.
Stirring, add sugar. Boil for 1 minute.
Serve over meat.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, bell pepper and onion. Cook noodles by package. Stir in parsley, steak sauce, ketchup, garlic and tomatoes (drained). Stir cooked noodles into mixture.
Pour into baking dish. Top with cream of mushroom soup. Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Melt in oven.

title: egg rolls
directions: Let ingredients sit for half hour.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese. Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Take out of oven and sprinkle cheese over top.
Return to oven and bake another 15 minutes or until center is firm.
Delicious served hot or cold.

title: "hobo for two"
directions: On large piece of foil, flatten ground beef.
Place onion, boiled potatoes, carrot, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Close foil.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until tender.
Mix all other ingredients and add to vegetables.
Mix 1/2 cup of margarine with 2 cups crushed Ritz crackers for topping.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fiesta chicken
directions: Put single layer of chicken tenders in bottom of greased casserole dish.
Put Mexican corn on top of chicken.
Cover with salsa then with grated cheese.
Bake in 400 degree oven for about 30 minutes or until chicken is tender when pierced with a fork.

title: hot potato salad
directions: In a large casserole dish, dice or slice the potatoes; set aside.
Heat the oil, vinegar, lemon juice, onion and salt.
Pour over potatoes, then sprinkle parsley, pepper and bacon.
In a preheated oven (350°), heat potato mixture only until hot; toss and serve.

title: carol's quick and easy graham cracker surprise
directions: Line cookie sheet with tinfoil.
Place graham crackers on sheet.
Boil butter or margarine and sugar for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Sprinkle with chopped walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: zucchini oatmeal bread
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake in greased loaf pan for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: pasta salad
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients together.
Add dressing and Salad Supreme and mix well.

title: lime slush punch
directions: Dissolve sugar and gelatin in boiling water in large bowl. Stir in juices and cold water.
Cover and freeze 8 hours.
Remove 1 hour before serving.
Break into chunks and pour in ginger ale. Stir until slushy.
Yield: 1 gallon.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugars together until light.
Add vanilla.
Add well beaten eggs and blend.
Sift together the dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Last, add the chocolate chips.
Drop by spoon onto a lightly greased cookie sheet.
A very soft cookie.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken in nonstick skillet.
Add peppers, cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes.
Drain pineapple; add water to pineapple juice to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Add liquid to skillet along with pineapple chunks, vinegar, sugar and spices.
Bring to a boil. Meanwhile, prepare rice as directed on package.
Serve over rice. Makes 6 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cut carrots and place in large pot with about 1-inch of water. Cook until done.
Mash in water they are cooked in.
Add flour, sugar, eggs and cinnamon.
Bake in 10 x 10-inch baking dish for about 30 to 35 minutes or until slightly brown on top.
Bake at 400°.

title: pecan balls
directions: Mix ingredients and make into a stiff ball.
Chill for 2 hours.
Roll into small marble balls and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown the beef.
Place all of the ingredients except the paste in a 6-quart souper pot at 400°.
Cover and let boil about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add meat and more water, if needed.
Cover and boil another 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add tomato paste and turn down; let simmer for 15 minutes.

title: herbed onion dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: better than candy
directions: Cook sugar, butter and water to a soft ball stage.
Beat this a moment and then dump into pan of cereal and stir thoroughly so all parts have a coating of candy.
It is ready to eat almost at once.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Mix melted butter and brown sugar in heavy skillet.
Arrange pineapple slices in pan on top of brown sugar and butter mixture. Place cherries or nuts in center of pineapple (optional).

title: chicken strips in garlic butter
directions: Sprinkle chicken with pepper and garlic powder, then coat chicken in flour.
Melt butter or margarine and garlic in large skillet.
Add chicken and saute, turn chicken to cook lightly on all sides over low-medium heat.
Add broth and bring to slow boil. Lower heat, sprinkle with parsley and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes, covered and stir occasionally.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on cake mix box.
Add pie filling.
Bake in one or two large greased cake pans.
Make 2 thin layers either by baking 1 large cake or 2 layers or cut in half.

title: cooked play dough
directions: Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until stiff.
Let cool and knead.
Store in Ziploc bag or plastic container.
Add food coloring to water for color.
This dough is especially long lasting.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Blend all together.
Bake at 375° until sharp knife comes out clean (50 to 55 minutes).
Cool.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour. Makes 9-inch pie.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Combine pineapple chunks and marshmallows in large bowl.
In saucepan, combine pineapple juice, flour, sugar, salt and beaten egg.
Cook until thick; cool.
Pour over pineapple and marshmallows.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Before serving, add bananas and nuts.
White grapes are good in it too.

title: speedy peanut butter candy
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar and syrup.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Turn off and add peanut butter and vanilla; stir to blend.

title: bou stew
directions: Tip:
It is best to use fresh ingredients, if you can.

title: banana pudding
directions: Cook first six ingredients over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick and smooth.
Pour over sliced bananas. Crumble wafers in and place whole wafers around edge.
Whip egg whites until stiff.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar.
Whip again until smooth.
Spread on top and brown in oven.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend
peanut butter and margarine.
Cream mixture with sugar and salt.
Beat egg and vanilla into cream mixture until fluffy. Sift
together
flour
and soda, gradually blend into mixture; form
balls.
Press down with fork.
Place two inches apart on ungreased
cookie
sheet.
Bake
at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: salmon patties
directions: Combine ingredients (do not drain salmon), except additional package of crumbs and oleo.
Blend well and shape into patties. Flatten out slightly. Dip into oleo and roll in crumbs.
Preheat oil in frypan.
Fry patties until brown.
Serve with catsup or chili sauce.

title: fudge cream pie
directions: Stir together sugar, flour and cocoa; gradually stir in milk. Stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil and thickens. Reduce heat; cook and stir 4 minutes.
Add small amount of egg yolks, return all to pan of hot mixture and cook, stirring 1 to 3 additional minutes, until mixture is very thick.
Remove from heat; stir in butter and vanilla.
Cool 5 minutes.
Turn into pie shell and cover with nuts.
Cover with meringue, sealing well around edges.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix soup, sour cream and potatoes. Add 1 cup shredded cheese. Pour into 13 x 9 pan. In small saucepan, cook onions in margarine until tender. Pour over hash brown mixture. Add 1 cup shredded cheese. Sprinkle crushed corn flakes over cheese. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes. Top is easy to burn. You can place aluminum foil over it until last 10 to 15 minutes. Then remove so cheese and corn flakes can brown.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water.
Cook, stirring occasionally with a wooden spoon, until mixture forms a ball when dropped in cold water.
Pour into egg whites that have been beaten (not too stiff).
Add nuts or flavoring and beat until mixture can be dropped by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: wienie bits
directions: Cut each wiener into 4 pieces.
Cut each bacon slice into 3 pieces.
Wrap bacon around each wiener piece.
Place in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan so they fit snugly so bacon stays wrapped.
Cover with brown sugar.
Bake, uncovered, for one hour.
Pour off grease and serve in a chafing dish with toothpicks.

title: bean casserole
directions: Cut bacon into 3/4-inch strips and crisp.
Remove bacon pieces from
drippings
and add onion rings.
Fry until transparent. Remove
from
pan.	Combine brown sugar, vinegar, dry mustard, garlic salt and pepper.
Simmer in drippings about 20 minutes. Add bacon and place in 3 quart casserole.
Add beans and mix lightly.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: apple crisp
directions: First, mix sugar with 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples and mix lightly.
Spread apples in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with water.
Blend flour, salt, 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon, nutmeg and brown sugar.
Mix in butter to make crumbly mixture.
Spread over apples.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cornstarch putty
directions: Add warm water to dry ingredients to make a stiff dough.
Dust with flour to prevent stickiness. (Long rolls may be made and cut into beads; holes for threading may be made with a nail and beads can then be allowed to dry.)

title: aunt marian's roll-out cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and eggs.
Measure milk and set aside.
Add vanilla and almond to creamed mixture.
Alternate dry ingredients and milk to creamed mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll and cut.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 9 minutes until lightly browned.

title: melissa holtman stock's cornbread casserole
directions: Mix cornbread mix, oil and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 400° for 45 minutes in casserole dish.

title: half pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla, flour and baking powder alternately with milk. Bake in 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or small tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: sunshine chicken
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine mustard, pineapple juice and brown sugar, mixing until sugar dissolves.
Wrap each chicken piece with bacon.
Secure with toothpick.
Brush mustard sauce over chicken and bacon.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add one egg at a time and beat separately.
Make a paste of food coloring and cocoa. Add to sugar mixture.
Sift flour and salt together.
Alternate buttermilk and flour to sugar mixture, starting with flour and ending with flour.
Combine soda and vinegar and add to mixture. Pour batter into 2 (8-inch) pans.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Ice with Red Velvet Cake Icing.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Place in greased dish and top with crumbs; add a little sage if desired.

title: southern bean soup
directions: Pick and wash beans; add beans to water.
Bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes only.
Cover and remove from heat and allow to stand 1 hour.
(This is equal to 12 hours of soaking in cold water.)
Add ham bone, garlic and bay leaf to water and beans. Bring back to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer about 2 hours or until beans are almost done.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer another hour.
Remove ham bone and cut off meat and return meat to pot.
Add skim milk.
Delicious soup.

title: shoe peg corn dip
directions: Mix all ingredients. Chill. Serve with chips.

title: italian wedding soup
directions: Mix meat and bread crumbs with onion and 1 teaspoon of bouillon.
Shape mixture into 40 meatballs.
In a Dutch oven, bring water and remaining bouillon to boil.
Add meatballs and pasta.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add spinach; reduce heat and simmer 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve with grated cheese.

title: breakfast puffs
directions: Melt 1/4 cup margarine in pie plate until bubbly.
In a small bowl mix remaining ingredients and pour into pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Cut into four pieces and serve immediately. Top with jam, jelly, compote, etc.

title: creme de cacao balls
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Shape into balls and roll in powdered sugar. Chill overnight.
(I use Oreos and run through food processor.)

title: quick vegetable soup
directions: Combine vegetables, onion soup and V-8 juice in a large pot. Bring to a boil.
Cook ground beef until meat is brown, stirring to crumble.
Drain.
Stir meat into soup mix.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Beat 2 eggs well.
Add pineapple with juice; add to flour mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar, then the nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
While baking, prepare the glaze.

title: country style venison steak
directions: In 2 1/2 c. water, soak dried onions and place beef base in to dissolve. Pound meat with tenderizer hammer until meat is thin in texture. Mix flour, season-all, pepper, m.s.g., and nutmeg. Coat meat on both sides with flour mixture and fry in hot oil in heavy skillet until browned on both sides. Place in baking pan. Put carrots over meat and put water with onions and base over that. Sprinkle rest of flour mixture over top and cover. (This will make your gravy.)
Cook in oven at 350 degrees for 1 1/2 hours, or until tender. Stir about 30 minutes into the cooking.

title: soup supreme
directions: Boil the bouillon cubes in the water until cubes are dissolved. Add raw vegetables to chicken broth. Boil for 15 minutes or until tender. Stir in frozen vegetables.
Stir in the soup, then the cheese.
Heat until the cheese melts, stirring frequently.
Keep over low heat as it will scorch easily.

title: roasted bell peppers
directions: Cut peppers into fairly thin strips. Combine in large bowl the vegetable oil, lemon-pepper marinade, Worcestershire sauce, garlic and herb salt mix, dill weed and parsley flakes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: In a large saucepan, saute onions, celery, olives, mushrooms, pimentos and bell peppers in butter and garlic powder for 15 minutes.
Add broth and simmer for 15 minutes more.
Add chicken. Cook and drain spaghetti.
Layer spaghetti, sauce and cheese in casseroles.
Bake for 20 minutes at 325°.
May be frozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except Ritz crackers and margarine).
Place in baking dish.
Put crushed Ritz crackers on top.
Slice margarine on top of crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy delicious spaghetti
directions: Brown onions and garlic in olive oil.
Add crumbled hamburg and brown.
Add onion soup, tomato sauce and tomato paste plus 2 cans of water.
Mix well.
Add seasoning, sugar, mushrooms and olives.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Add more water, if needed.

title: berry icing
directions: Mix all until smooth.
Spread over top and sides of cake. (Chiffon Cake by Gert Novitzke.)

title: baccala(salted cod)
directions: Soak the baccala for 24 hours.
Change the water several times.
Wring out baccala - pat dry with paper towels.
Cut into 3 to 4 inch pieces.
Cover bottom of large size baking dish with prepared tomato sauce.
Line leeks over sauce, then fish, olives, capers and anchovies.
Pour sauce over fish.
Cover baking dish tightly.
