Bake at 350° for 35 - 45 minutes, until fish is soft and flaky.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In large saucepan, boil squash and onions for 5 to 10 minutes. Drain well.
In large bowl, combine soup and sour cream.
Stir in carrots and bell pepper, then fold in squash mixture.
Toss Stove Top mix with melted oleo.
Spread 1/2 Stove Top mixture in baking dish.
Top with squash mixture and remaining Stove Top mix.

title: 3 pumpkin pies
directions: Mix all together; put in unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes; then turn oven down to 300°.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: veggie bites(favorite at teacher luncheons)
directions: Press two (8 ounce) packages crescent rolls onto a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking sheet to form the crust.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: giant ice cream cookie sandwich
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 2 cookie sheets.
Mix flour and baking soda.
In a large bowl beat butter, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer until fluffy.
Stir in oats, flour mixture and 1/3 cup chocolate chips until blended.
Divide dough in half. Place half in middle of each cookie sheet and spread into an 8-inch circle.
Sprinkle one with remaining 2 tablespoons chocolate chips, then score into 8 wedges with a sharp knife.
Bake both 15 minutes, turning cookie sheets and switching over positions once, until light brown and crisp looking.
Cool on sheets 10 minutes before removing to racks to cool completely.

title: banana split pie
directions: Blend cream cheese, margarine and sugar.
Spread over crumbs. Slice bananas and put on top of mixture.
Add pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: brown sugar brickle bars
directions: Cook brown sugar and butter in saucepan over medium heat till butter melts and mixture is smooth. Remove from heat, cool slightly. Add eggs one at at time, beating after each one. Combine flour, baking powder and salt add to sugar mixture, stirring well. Stir in brickle chips, pecans and vanilla. Pour batter into a greased 13 x 9 pan. Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes. Cool in pan. Cut into bars.

title: civil war fruit cake
directions: Combine in large saucepan apples, raisins, water, sugars and Crisco and cook for five minutes. Remove from heat and cool thoroughly. Sift together in large mixing bowl the flour and spices. Add the apple-raisin mixture and stir thoroughly. Add the nuts and mix. Divide batter into 3 greased and lined loaf pans. (Line the bottom of pans with a strip of waxed paper.) Spray bottom of pan and waxed paper with nonstick spray. Bake at 350° about 35 to 45 minutes or until done. Don't bake too hard. (You can omit the sugar and use 1 cup molasses.)

title: cream kisses from india
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Cream Crisco and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add essence to the cream mixture.
Add flour and mix. Add milk, if necessary.
Cut into any shape or pipe through a nozzle and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cream it out with nozzle.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in 4 quarts of boiling water for 8 minutes. Drain water from pan with a large slotted spoon. Pasta should not be drained completely dry. Add butter to milk and heat over medium heat, stirring constantly until milk begins to steam. Dissolve cornstarch in 3 tablespoons warm water and add to hot milk. Stir until thickened. Add 4 ounces of cheese to the milk and stir until thoroughly blended. Remove from heat and cool to lukewarm. Add macaroni to milk mixture and 4 ounces of cheese. Mix loosely. Prepare a large glass loaf pan or small casserole dish with nonstick spray. Add mixture and top with remaining cheese. Bake at 325° to 350° for 45 minutes or until cheese on top is brown and bubbling.

title: citrus cheesecake
directions: In bowl combine first 3 ingredients.
Press onto bottom of 7-inch spring-form.
Bake at 325° for 6 minutes; let cool.
In blender combine eggs, sugar, orange peel, juice and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Cut cream cheese into chunks.
Add to mixture and blend until smooth.
Stir in 1/2 cup yogurt.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes or until nearly set.
Combine 1/2 cup yogurt, powdered sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Spread over hot cheesecake.
Loosen sides of pan.
Cool on wire rack.
Chill before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Place lima beans in casserole.
Brown hamburger and onion in skillet.
Drain off grease and add tomato sauce and liquid from the beans.
Sweeten with brown sugar to taste.
Simmer for about 15 minutes.
Pour over lima beans and bake at 350° for one hour or less.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Mix soda with buttermilk.
Mix with sugar and syrup and boil until a ball forms in cold water.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Beat until smooth and pour in a buttered pan.
Let cool before cutting into squares.

title: banana cookies
directions: Combine shortening and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg, vanilla and banana extract.
Stir in bananas, then add flour, baking soda and salt.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Cool, frost with cream cheese frosting and top with chopped nuts.

title: three layer pretzel salad
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix crushed pretzels, butter and sugar in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 8 minutes.
Do not overbake. Remove and cool.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Saute onions and celery.
Pour over bread.
Add seasoning; mix well.
Moisten well with broth. Add eggs; mix well.
Pack lightly in crock-pot and cover.
Set on high for 45 minutes.
Cook on low heat for 4 to 8 hours.

title: pannekaker(norwegian pancakes)
directions: Combine sour cream and cottage cheese.
Add other ingredients and beat with mixer or blender until well mixed. Bake on hot greased griddle until bubbles break on surface.
Turn and bake until golden brown. Serve with butter and syrup.
Can add fruit (diced) or berries, etc., to batter.
Yields 24 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: grand momma's delicious donuts
directions: Combine all ingredients except yeast, potatoes and eggs. Blend together. Let cool slightly then add yeast, potatoes and eggs. Knead until smooth. Place in large greased bowl. Pat top with oil. Cover with towel and let rise until double. Roll out dough 1/3-inch thick. Cut out doughnuts (if you don't have a doughnut cutter, can use biscuit cutter then a 2-liter top to cut holes). Let rise on cookie sheet. Fry doughnuts in large skillet with enough oil to float. When browned, put immediately into glaze. (Do not drain. Helps to have 2 people for this.) Coat both sides.

title: venison bourguignon
directions: Saute the onions in a skillet containing the bacon drippings until the onion chunks are brown around the edges.
Transfer onions to a stew pot.
In the same skillet, brown the brisket meat after dusting it with flour.
Add remaining ingredients (except mushrooms) to the stew pot; cover and simmer on low heat for 3 hours.
Add the mushrooms during the final 1/2 hour of cooking. Makes 4 servings.

title: saucy tomato beef loaf
directions: Combine ingredients and shape into a firm loaf.
Bake at 350° about 1 1/2 hours.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix all together; pour into a Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Scald milk.
Add the bread crumbs.
Stir in the squash, beaten egg and cheese.
Mix in the rest of the ingredients.
Place in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: roast beef
directions: Put 3 or 4 cups of water in medium roaster.
Cook roast in 375° oven for 2 to 3 hours.
Do not let water cook out.
When tender, take roast out of broth and mix well.
Add onion, salt and pepper. Add soup.
Put roast back in gravy and put back in oven with lid on for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: *Cover raisins with water.
Boil 10 minutes.

title: maple bars
directions: Soak raisins in water.
Dissolve yeast and honey in warm water; add salt and applesauce.
Mix in whole wheat flour and unbleached flour as needed for good bread consistency.
Let rise in warm place; when doubled, roll out onto counter in a rectangle as for cinnamon rolls.
Pour pure maple syrup and spread all over. Sprinkle raisins (approximately 1/2 cup) and chopped walnuts (approximately 1/2 cup).
Roll up and slice into 2 to 2 1/2-inch slices and place into baking dish sprayed with Pam and bottom of pan covered with pure maple syrup.
Let rise until double in size. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until done.
Yummy.
When cool, invert on another dish.

title: brisket of beef
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Rub meat with salt and pepper.
Add onion, celery, soup mix, bay leaf and garlic.
Wrap and seal in heavy-duty foil and put in roasting pan.
Place in 425° oven for 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and cook 30 to 40 minutes per pound.
This provides juice for serving and gravy making for leftover hot beef sandwiches or to mix barbecue sauce to serve over meat.

title: chicken breasts supreme
directions: Partially cook bacon to cut down fat; cut in half.
Lay 2 strips of bacon on each breast and place side by side in a 13 x 9-inch pan (presprayed with Pam) which has been covered with a layer of chipped beef.
Mix sour cream and undiluted soup; pour over chicken.
Cook, uncovered, at 300° for 2 hours.
Sauce will be almost absorbed and chicken will be browned on outside and succulent inside.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the butter and sugar together. Stir in vanilla and gradually add flour to mixture.
Fold in nuts and potato chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes until edges of cookies are golden brown.
After 5 minutes of cooling on sheet, gently roll cookies in powdered sugar. Store in lightly covered container between sheets of waxed paper.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, 1 cup sugar and salt in a medium saucepan. Gradually stir in hot water.
Bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat and cook until thick and clear, about 10 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir several spoonfuls of the hot mixture into the beaten egg yolks and mix well.
Pour yolk mixture into saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Then reduce heat and cook 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and lemon rind.
Gradually add lemon juice and mix well.
Cool 5 minutes and then pour into pie shell.

title: marilyn's heavenly salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add a little cherry juice.

title: corn meal rolls
directions: Cook milk and cornmeal in double boiler or heavy pan until thick.
Add sugar, shortening and salt.
Cool until lukewarm.
Add eggs and yeast.
Add sifted flour to make a stiff batter; knead in additional flour.
Put in greased bowl and let rise until doubled in size.
Punch down and shape rolls.
Put in greased pan and let rise again.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: seven seas casserole
directions: In saucepan, add soup, water, seasoning and onion; bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Pour 1/2 mixture into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Make 3 layers, using rice (directly from box), then peas, then tuna.
Add remaining soup.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes, cutting through mixture with knife after baking 10 minutes.

title: dee's chocolate bundt cake
directions: Mix the cake mix per directions on the package.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan and cook at 350 degrees for about 1 hour or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Serve with vanilla flavored Cool Whip or ice cream.
This cake is even better two days after you bake it.

title: mexican tortillas
directions: To each cup of flour add 1 teaspoon salt and 1 tablespoon of shortening.
Mix thoroughly and add enough water to make a dough. Roll out very thin and bake on a dry pan.
(One cup of flour makes 6 tortillas.)

title: fried apples
directions: Use early or green tart apples.
Core and peel, then cut into medium sized hunks into a large frying pan.
Add at least 1/2 stick margarine or butter and about 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Add just a "dash" of salt.
Cook slowly over low heat, stirring frequently with a wooden spoon.
Keep tasting until desired sweetness.
Add more butter if it seems dry.
The butter makes it rich tasting and takes it out of the applesauce category.
Do not overcook and leave it rather chunky.
Serve warm.
Leftovers can be reheated in the microwave.

title: steven's stuffed spinach shells
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions; drain thoroughly. Cook jumbo shells according to package directions; drain and cover with cold water. Combine spinach, cottage cheese, eggs, shredded Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese, garlic powder and pepper. Stuff into shells and place in greased baking dish. (I use 9 x 13-inch.) Cover with tomato sauce. Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes or until bubbling. Bake at 350°.

title: 1-2-3 fudge
directions: Melt all ingredients together in a double boiler, stirring as you melt.
Pour all ingredients into a 9 x 12-inch buttered cookie sheet.
Chill and then cut into squares.
Yield: bunches (depends on size of squares).

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Cut zucchini lengthwise in 1/2 inch slices.
Dip in egg and then in flour.
Fry slices until golden brown.
These slices may be frozen now for later use.
Layer slices with Mozzarella, Parmesan cheese and tomato sauce.
Bake until bubbly at 375°.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut up potatoes into cubes, boil, drain, and mash them.
Save some cheese for topping.
Stir in butter, grated cheeses and seasoning.
Top with remaining cheese. Bake for 20 minutes.

title: chicken quiso
directions: This is a Peruvian dish in South America pronounced "Geeso".

title: salmon loaf
directions: In a bowl; combine salmon, crumbs, onion, butter and salt. Combine milk and egg; add to salmon mixture and mix thoroughly. Shape into a loaf on a greased shallow baking pan or in a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 35-40 min.

title: mom's peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except paraffin wax and chocolate chips. Make into balls.
Chill in the refrigerator for about 30 minutes. Melt paraffin wax and large bag of chocolate chips.
Dip balls into chocolate and let dry on wax paper.

title: soft chocolate cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, the sugars, vanilla and pudding mix in large bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture, then chips and nuts.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: "black-eyed pea" dip(not for the "faint of heart.")
directions: Put first 10 items together in a pan.
Cook over low heat until a boil.
Put next 7 items with first 10 items; simmer 30 minutes. Thicken after the 30 minutes of simmering by adding 1/4 cup bacon drippings and 3 tablespoons flour.
So hot!

title: marshmallow pecan treats
directions: Melt almond bar and peanut butter until melted good!
Then add the remaining ingredients.
In a bowl, scoop out on wax paper by tablespoon and let it cool.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Melt butter and saute pepper and onion.
Add peeled shrimp, soup, tomatoes, salt, pepper and rice.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 2 hours.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt butter; add egg, vanilla, sugar and nut meats.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix and spread in greased 8 x 8 pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange chicken in greased 13 x 9-inch dish.
Cover with broccoli.
Combine soup, cheese, curry, mayonnaise and lemon juice. Pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with more cheese and paprika.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit fizz
directions: Mix 1 cup of each fruit juice together.
Add 1 cup of each fruit juice with each cup of seltzer.
Repeat
as desired.
Chill. Serve.

title: butter roll
directions: Mix well the flour and milk.
Roll out on a floured surface. Cut the stick of butter in thin squares.
Place all over 1/2 of the rolled out dough.
Spread 1/2 cup of the sugar over the butter squares.
Fold one side of the rolled dough over the buttered side. Place in baking dish and bake at 350° until golden brown.
While this is cooking, mix milk, sugar and vanilla in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Pour over the browned roll as soon as you bring it out of the oven.
It will continue to boil some.
When it cools some, it is ready to enjoy.

title: green beans casserole
directions: Dilute mushroom soup with milk.
Chop onions and mix with green beans.
Add soup and stir.
Put in Corning-ware bowl. Sprinkle with onion chips.
Cook for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: triple treat candy
directions: Melt over hot water, milk chocolate and shortening.
Stir until mixture is smooth.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into 8-inch square greased foil-lined pan.
Spread evenly.
Refrigerate until firm (about 15 minutes).
Return remaining mixture to low heat.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix
flour
and
salt.
Beat
eggs slightly; add sugar, flour and salt mixture.
Add vanilla, milk and melted butter. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken almondine
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine soups and sherry together. Saute mushrooms and add to soups.
Heat over low heat for a few minutes.
Line bottom of baking dish or roaster with slices of onion.
Add raw chicken, then pour soup mixture over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered, then an additional 1/2 hour, covered.
Serve with slivered almonds, browned in butter, over chicken.
Very, very good.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: In large bowl, beat shortening until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine oats and next 3 ingredients.
Add to shortening mixture, beating well.
Stir in vanilla, chocolate bits and pecans.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Sift flour 5 more times.
Cream butter well.
Gradually add sugar and beat until smooth.
Add 1 egg at a time, blending well after each.
Then beat very hard and long, the longer, the better. Add flour and beat well.
Add vanilla; pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 300° for about 50 minutes.

title: strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Combine sugar, tapioca, salt and nutmeg.
Add rhubarb and strawberries. Mix to coat fruit.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Place in pie pastry and dot with butter or margarine.
Place lattice crust on top of pie.
Bake at 400 for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops; put aside and leave 6 tablespoons of drippings in skillet.
Add water to soup; mix well.
Add onion, bell pepper, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Boil for 2 or 3 minutes.
Pour over raw rice in a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan; stir well.
Lay pork chops on top; seal with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove pork chops and stir rice mixture.
Replace pork chops; cover back with foil and cook 1 hour, or until done.

title: angel food cake
directions: Let egg whites stand at room temperature for no more than 1 hour (15 minutes in hot weather).
Sift flour and 3/4 cup sugar together 3 times.
Beat whites and salt in large bowl at high speed until foamy.
Add cream of tartar and vanilla, beating to soft peaks.
Gradually beat in remaining 1 cup sugar until stiff peaks form.
Gradually fold flour-sugar mixture into whites.
Turn into an ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Draw knife once through batter to remove large air bubbles.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until long, wooden pick inserted in center tests clean.
Cool 1 hour.
Loosen cake around tube and sides with long, thin metal spatula. Remove cake and serve.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Stir in 2 cups liquid (use orange juice, pineapple juice and water to make 2 cups). Stir in sugar.
Stir in other ingredients.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer
chicken in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour soups over chicken.
Mix
stuffing
with
water
and pour over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple; measure juice.
Measure juice from orange and add to pineapple juice; if not 2 cups, add water to make 2 cups. Heat to a boil.
Add Jell-O and stir.
Add cranberry sauce, pineapple, grated orange, chopped apple and pecans.
Pour in a mold and chill overnight.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Scrape small whole carrots.
Cook in boiling salted water until tender, drain.
Cook sugar, butter and 1/4 cup hot water together 5 minutes. Pour over cooked carrots and bake about 20 minutes in 375° oven.
Baste with syrup.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in baking dish; mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Tastes like fresh corn.

title: butter-nut squares
directions: Mix ingredients.
Add 6 ounces chocolate chips and nuts.
Cook at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cut while warm.

title: bird dog cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box in a 9 x 13-inch pan. While cake is warm, poke holes in cake with a wooden spoon handle. Mix the caramel sauce and Eagle Brand milk together and pour over cake.
Cool cake, then top with tub of Cool Whip and sprinkle with toffee or brickle.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: bell pepper soup
directions: Place whole peppers on their sides on a large baking sheet. Bake at 500° for 20 minutes or until skin is blackened and charred.
Put immediately in a paper bag and seal the top. Refrigerate 10 minutes or until peppers cool.
Peel and seed peppers.
Saute onion and garlic in butter in a Dutch oven until onion is tender.
Add flour, stirring, until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add chicken broth; cook until thickened.
Stir in ground pepper.
Pour 1/2 of soup mixture into electric blender container; add half of skinned peppers and process until smooth.
Return mixture to Dutch oven; repeat procedure with remaining ingredients.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: linda's famous baked beans
directions: Fry hamburger and onions together in a skillet.
Drain all beans.
Mix together.
Add all other ingredients.
Drain fat from hamburger.
Add to beans.
Bake in oven for 1 hour at 350°. Enjoy!!!

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Combine.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes.
The first 10 minutes at 400° and then turn temperature to 300° and bake until done.

title: mom's cole slaw
directions: Let the first 3 ingredients stand with 1 teaspoon salt for 1 hour; stir often.
Then combine remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Let this cool and then pour over the cabbage mixture that has been sitting for 1 hour.
Mix well.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Take stick of butter and rub it on all slides of pot you will use. Rub butter on dish you will be putting fudge in. Melt butter, sugar and evaporated milk. Stir constantly until soft-ball stage, approximately 5 minutes. Then take of burner and stir in vanilla, Marshmallow Fluff and peanut butter. Pour in dish and let set to cool.

title: dutch green split pea soup
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces and set aside.
In a 2-quart saucepan, bring 1 cup of water to a boil.
Add peas and boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand for 1 hour.
Add remaining cup of water and the bacon to saucepan and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, partially cover and let simmer for 1 hour. Add potatoes, leeks, celery root and celery leaves and cook until vegetables are tender, about 30 minutes.
Add kielbasa, savory, and pepper and cook until sausage is heated through.
Serves 2.

title: oyster stew
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and water.
Blend to a smooth paste.
Stir in oysters and their liquor.
Simmer oysters over very low heat until edges curl, then pour into scalded milk. Remove pan from heat; cover and let stand 15 minutes.
Have tureen and soup plates hot; drop in some butter or margarine.
Reheat stew briefly and serve piping hot.
Pour into tureen; sprinkle with paprika.

title: chocolate candy
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a full boil and time for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and peanut butter and blend.
Pour into buttered plate.
Allow to cool.

title: microwave cheese sauce
directions: Place margarine in 2-cup measure.
Microwave at High (100%) until melted, 30 seconds to 1 minute.
Stir in flour.
Blend in milk, mustard and salt.
Reduce power to Medium-high (70%). Microwave until thickened, 2 to 5 minutes, stirring every minute. Stir in cheese until melted.
Serve over hot vegetables.
Makes 4 servings.

title: beef stew
directions: Boil meat and onion until tender.
Add potatoes, carrots and brown gravy package.
Cover top of stew with seasoned salt real well.
Simmer about 2 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine peanut butter, oleo or butter, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended. Add eggs and beat, until well blended.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda; add to creamed mixture at low speed.
Mix just until blended.
Drop by teaspoons 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with tines of fork.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes or until set and just brown.
Cool 2 minutes on cookie sheet.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and oleo in top of double boiler.
Pour over Rice Chex.
Stir until covered.
Pour powdered sugar in bag.
Pour Rice Chex in and shake until covered.

title: amish yuma-setta
directions: Brown hamburg with salt, pepper, brown sugar and onions.
Add tomato soup to this mixture.
Cook noodles and drain.
Add cream of chicken soup to noodles.
Layer hamburg mixture and noodle mixture in casserole dish with cheese between layers and on top. Bake at 350° for 3/4 hour.

title: pork-n-beans ala
directions: After browning hamburger with next 4 ingredients, drain excess liquid.
Put in casserole dish and mix in pork and beans.
Bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: sparkling honey dressing
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Gradually add the oil. Stir until thoroughly blended.
Contains approximately 43 calories per tablespoon.
Makes 2 cups.

title: swiss tuna grill
directions: Combine tuna, celery, onion, mayonnaise, sour cream and pepper.
Spread filling on 8 slices of bread.
Top with remaining bread.
Spread outside of sandwiches with butter.
Cook on hot griddle over medium heat about 3 minutes on each side until toasted and filling is heated through.

title: chocolate banana cake
directions: Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk.
Mix rest of ingredients and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Frost with Mock Whipped Cream Frosting.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut up chicken; boil until done.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups broth. Bone and cut into cubes.
Mix together soups and sour cream. Pour over chicken.
Spread stuffing over chicken and soup mixture.
Melt 1 stick margarine in broth and pour over top. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: lemon poppy seed muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and poppy seed.
Add milk, lemonade, oil and egg whites.
(Do not overmix.) Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: grilled hawaiian chicken
directions: Spray or lightly oil meat. Rub dry mix on meat. Grill until almost done. Remove and place into container of liquid ingredients. Baste for approximately 10 to 15 minutes. Grill 2nd time for 5 to 10 minutes, turning often. Do not overcook. Garnish with grilled orange or pineapple slices.

title: lemon pie
directions: Beat with mixer the sugar and Pet milk until sugar melts.
Add egg yolks; beat.
Add lemon juice.
Heat until thick.
Put in a 9 x 8 1/2-inch square bowl and layer one layer of graham crackers, one layer of pie filling and one layer of whipped topping; repeat layers again and chill before serving.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake by directions.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Fry sausage; drain. Place bread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle sausage evenly over bread. Mix all other ingredients and pour over sausage and bread. Put in fridge overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cracker pie
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, 1/2 cup pecans and baking powder in a large bowl; set aside.

title: hot broccoli casserole
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together; put in a casserole dish. Spread French fried onion rings over the top of casserole; bake at 350° until hot, bubbly and brown on top.

title: fry bake chicken
directions: Melt oleo in saucepan on low heat.
Add next 5 ingredients and simmer for 5 minutes.
Fry unseasoned chicken in hot deep fat for 15 minutes.
After chicken is cooked, season each piece and place in baking dish.
Pour butter sauce over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Halfway through baking time, add mushrooms to chicken.
Turn and baste several times until cooked.

title: taco casserole
directions: Fry chuck with onion (drain grease off).
Mix together and heat.
Add 1/2 package taco chips to mix.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and crushed chips.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Beat egg white and water until medium peaks form.
Stir in pecans until coated.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Add to pecan/egg white mixture.
Stir until well coated. Spread on buttered cookie sheet.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove, cool and store in tightly sealed container.

title: christmas eggnog punch
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until lemon colored.
Stir in water, melted orange juice and lemon juice.
Place scoops of ice cream in punch bowl.
Pour egg-juice mixture over ice cream.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
A festive, delicious Christmas Eve treat.
Makes about 32 punch-cup size servings.

title: chicken and chips
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Empty soup into baking dish.
Add milk and mix well.
Add chicken, 1 cup potato chips, peas and pimientos. Mix well.
Sprinkle remaining chips on top.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oatmeal and water; let cool for 20 minutes.
Cream butter and sugar; add oatmeal mixture.
Mix dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Bake for 30 minutes in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.

title: no bake date cracker cookies
directions: Cook the first 2 ingredients until very thick.
Put on round crackers.
Bake 10 minutes at 325°.
Mix the rest of ingredients. After mixing, spread on top of date mixture.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar, then add Karo syrup, butter, vanilla and pecans.
Place in unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Add boiling water to jello.
Add juice, cranberry sauce and nuts.
Let this semi-set, then add apples.
Place back in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: terry's "hot" chili
directions: Brown hamburger mixture in large pan.
In separate pan, cook spaghetti until tender.
Drain both.
Add tomato juice and remaining ingredients; stir occasionally.
Continue to heat until hot.
Serve with cheese topping.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Saute onions in the butter until golden brown.
Add meat, carrots, tomato soup and seasonings; mix well and transfer to a greased pie plate (9-inch or more).
Cover with the mashed potatoes.
Bake at 400° until potatoes are golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift flour, cocoa, soda and salt 3 times.
Add mayonnaise, water and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: out-of-this-world cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add marshmallows, stirring until melted. Stir in pineapple.
Chill until thick, but not firm. Add cherries, pecans and cottage cheese.
Fold in whipped cream. Pour mixture into an oiled 2-quart mold.
Chill until firm.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in large roasting pan.
Drain syrup from pineapple slices into a medium bowl; stir in French dressing and onion soup mix.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, occasionally basting.
Cut pineapple slices in half and add to roasting pan; turn to coat with sauce.
Bake 15 minutes longer or until chicken is done.
Arrange chicken in deep dish and pour sauce over it.
Makes 8 servings.

title: marinated asparagus
directions: If using fresh asparagus, cook until crisp-tender.
Drain asparagus and lay in shallow pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over asparagus.
Chill at least 5 hours.

title: roadside potatoes
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in blender.
Grate potatoes and cheese into milk mixture and pour into greased baking dish. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pig pickin' cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in 4 layers at 325° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Coat 13 x 9-inch casserole dish with cooking spray.
Make 1 layer with 6 slices bread, cubed.
Make second layer with cubed cream cheese.
Top with layer of 6 slices of bread, cubed. Combine milk, eggs and syrup and pour over bread.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in morning at 350°
for 40 to 45 minutes.
Great for brunch!

title: rolled oats meat loaf
directions: Saute onion and celery until tender-crisp in oil.
Next mix everything except sauce.
Add to meat and mix well.
Pack tightly into a pan or ring and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour. Pour tomato sauce on top before baking.
Let stand about 5 minutes before cutting.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage very fine and cook 9 minutes in boiling, salted water.
Remove cabbage; drain well and place in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Melt butter in saucepan; stir in flour and salt until smooth.
Add milk gradually.
Continue stirring until moisture thickens.
Pour this sauce over cabbage and sprinkle breadcrumbs over top.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes or until crumbs are brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: busy day dessert
directions: Layer in order given in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until brown.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Drain and mash pears.
Reserve 1 cup syrup and heat.
Pour over jello.
Whip cream cheese and add dissolved jello. Chill until lightly thickened.
Stir in pears and whipped cream.
Pour into 4 cup mold and chill.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding as package directs.
Mix Cool Whip and sour cream. Add these to the pudding.
Slice bananas and sprinkle with Fruit Fresh to prevent browning.

title: hot cheese ball
directions: Soften cheeses.
Chop or grind peppers.
Mix all together well.
Form into balls and refrigerate.

title: cheese ball or spread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make into a ball.
Roll in pecans.
Top with cherry and serve with crackers.

title: elsie's chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken in 1 tablespoon of salt.
Cool; take meat from bones and cool.
Cut chicken with scissors.
Mix all ingredients. (Add Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce in salad dressing.)

title: slush punch
directions: Bring water and sugar to a rapid boil, making a simple syrup. Add remaining ingredients except ginger ale and mix thoroughly. Freeze mixture.
When ready to use, stir in ginger ale.
Yield:
5 quarts of slush mix.

title: chicken spaghetti bake
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat, stirring, until mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in broth and cream.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir for 2 minutes.
Add sherry, spaghetti, chicken and mushrooms.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: chicken and sausage gumbo
directions: To begin the gumbo, you must first make a roux.
This is a very important part of the gumbo; it gives it consistency and great flavor.

title: white mountain icing
directions: Cook syrup and water until it forms soft ball in cold water. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Pour syrup over the egg whites; beat until stiff.

title: squash fritters
directions: Cook squash.
Add ingredients until just moist.
Drop by spoonfuls into deep, hot oil.
This will serve as bread for a meal.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add egg and stir.
Add juice drained from pineapple chunks.
Add enough water to make 1 cup liquid. Cook over medium heat until thick.
Remove from heat and let cool to room temperature.
Beat in cream cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip. Use pineapple chunks and other assorted fruit to dip.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients into mixture. Chill 3 to 4 hours or longer.
On well floured surface, roll to 1/8 or 1/4-inch.
Cut into shapes.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Frost or decorate as desired.

title: ham quiche wedges
directions: Heat oven to 425 degrees.
Grease a 12-inch pizza pan.

title: 7 up pound cake
directions: Beat these items till creamy.
Add one egg at a time to the above mixture.
With mixer on low add the items below to the above mixture.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger and fry bacon, onions and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients and bake in large pot or casserole dish at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: pepper steak
directions: In large skillet or wok, stir-fry the garlic in 1 tablespoon of the butter for 1 minute.
Add onion and peppers and stir-fry for 4 to 5 minutes.
Transfer the vegetables with a slotted spoon to a bowl.
Add the remaining butter to skillet or wok.
To prevent overcrowding, stir-fry half the steak at a time, until the meat is cooked through, 2 to 3 minutes.
Return all the steak and the vegetables to the skillet or wok.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Consistency should be rather thin.

title: broccoli  cornbread
directions: Blend ingredients well, adding muffin mix last.
Bake in a 9x13 inch pan at 400°
for 25 minutes.

title: marinated veggies
directions: Mix all vegetables together.
Mix and bring to a boil all liquids; pour over vegetables.
Marinate at least 8 hours.

title: beef with peppers and tomatoes
directions: Mix soy sauce, water, sherry, garlic powder and beef strips in plastic bag or medium bowl; close tightly or cover.
Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Combine green peppers, beef and marinade in 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover.
Microwave at medium (50%) until beef is tender, 20 to 25 minutes, stirring after half of cooking time.
Drain, reserving meat juices.
Set beef mixture aside, covered.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In large bowl, mix flour, 2/3 cup sugar, baking powder and salt; stir in blueberries.
In small bowl, beat eggs, milk and butter; add to blueberry mixture.
Stir just until blended.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Bake in preheated 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cowboy soup
directions: Thrown the whole pile in a big pot and bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Simmer on mid-low heat for a couple of hours, adding more water as necessary to keep stirrable.

title: peppered hamburger meat
directions: Mix hamburger, oatmeal, garlic and salt; make into meatballs and brown.
Add onion, tomatoes, soy sauce, sugar, water and cornstarch; simmer for 15 minutes.
Add diced bell pepper; cook 10 minutes.
(Bell peppers should be crisp.)
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: german chocolate upside down cake
directions: Mix coconut and pecans and put in the bottom of a greased 9 x 13 pan.
Mix German chocolate cake according to package directions and pour over the coconut and pecans.
Melt butter and cream cheese and stir until smooth.
Mix in the powdered sugar and stir until smooth.
Pour over the cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Do not cut until cool.

title: ben johnson jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish in 350° oven. Sift together flour and sugar; add milk and then pour into the baking dish, do not stir.
Add fruit, do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix together sugar, milk, syrup and vinegar.
Boil until a soft ball is formed when a few drops are tested in cold water. Take from fire and cook until lukewarm.
Add peanut butter and beat until creamy.
Pour into buttered pan and cut in squares.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw and prepare broccoli according to directions on box.
In large, covered casserole dish, mix broccoli, egg, mayonnaise, onion, cheese and soup.
Mix well and top with herb seasoning mix. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: famous chili
directions: Fills one Westinghouse cooker. Feeds 50 people.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix and keep
in
airtight
container.
Add 1 to 2 teaspoons, depending on your taste, to 1 cup hot water.

title: hamburger pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400° (425° for metal pan).
Sift flour before measuring.
Spoon lightly into 1 cup measuring cup and level.
Cut Crisco into flour until uniform.
Mix onion/garlic salt and water. Sprinkle on water, a tablespoon at a time.
Work dough into a firm ball.
Divide in half on a lightly floured surface.
Add pie filling.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
When tender, tear into pieces and place in a buttered dish. Sprinkle cheese on top of chicken.
Mix soup and milk together, then pour on top of mixture. Pour Stove Top stuffing on top, then pour broth on very top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes (depending on your oven).

title: budget bouillabaisse
directions: Heat tomatoes (with liquid) and the remaining ingredients except cornstarch, 1/2 cup water and the fish to boiling. Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes. Remove bay leaf.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and cream cheese; mix well!
Add egg yolks, vanilla and all ingredients.
Add whites of eggs.
Bake at 325° in greased and floured tube pan.
Add red or green cake coloring for holidays.

title: chicken liver pate
directions: Grind all ingredients together.
Add enough mayonnaise to form a paste.
Chill.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: excellent white fruit cake
directions: Dredge fruit and pecans in 3/4 cup plain flour.
Add vanilla and lemon to fruit mixture.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until light and creamy.
Add the cup of plain flour and baking powder.
Mix well and pour over fruit mixture.
Mix with hands until all fruit is evenly coated.
Pour into 9-inch tube pan or 2 loaf pans that have been greased and lined with brown paper with 2 layers on bottom.
Do not preheat oven.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, then lower to 250° for 2 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan. Makes approximately 5 pounds of the best white fruitcake you will ever eat.
Wait 24 hours to slice it, if you can.

title: almond paste bars
directions: Blend all ingredients together well. Bake on a cookie sheet at 325° for 30 minutes or until brown. Cool slightly, then cut into bars.

title: breaded pineapple
directions: Soak bread into egg, then add the following ingredients: condensed milk, sugar and pineapple chunks.
Mix well.
Put into a 3-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Great with a ham dinner.

title: pink lemonade salad
directions: Combine sugar and crumbs.
Add margarine.
Pat 3/4 of this mixture in bottom of dish.
Set other 1/4 aside.
Mix Cool Whip, lemonade and milk.
Pour over crumbs.
Sprinkle the top with the rest of the crumbs.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: taco casserole
directions: Crumble beef into a 1 1/2 quart casserole, then stir in onion and cook, covered, on 100% power (high) 4 1/2 to 5 1/2 minutes or till done.
Drain, stir in tomato sauce, water and chili powder. Cook, covered on high, about 6 minutes or until bubbly. Meanwhile, stir together beans and taco sauce.
Spread in the bottom of a 12 x 7 baking dish, then spread the meat mixture on top.
Cook, uncovered, on high power 7 to 9 minutes or until heated through. Top with cheese and cook, uncovered, for about a minute or until cheese is melted.
Top with crushed taco shells or corn chips and lettuce.
If desired, top with tomato, green onions, black olives and avocado dip.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken montezuma
directions: Cook chicken in water with additional chili powder, garlic powder and onion.
Combine chicken and the rest of the ingredients except tortillas and cheese.
Butter a large baking dish.
Put one layer of tortillas, one layer of mixture and one layer of cheese. Alternate layers, ending with cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
A Tex/Mex dish!
Serves 8 to 10.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Grease baking dish with olive and canola oil.
Place cut up potatoes in dish and sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Pour a little olive oil over potatoes and toss.
Bake in oven at 375° for 45 minutes or microwave 10 minutes on High and bake for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini lasagna
directions: In large skillet saute the beef and onion, drain excess fat. Stir in tomato sauce, oregano, basil, salt and pepper to taste. Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Arrange half the zucchini slices in bottom of a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat together Ricotta or cottage cheese and the egg.
Spread over zucchini, top with half of the meat sauce and half the Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat the layers with the remaining zucchini, sauce and Mozzarella.
Sprinkle with the Parmesan cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° until the sauce is hot and bubbly and the zucchini is tender, about 40 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add corn and then sprinkle cornbread over corn; stir gently with a fork.
Add unbeaten eggs (mix with a fork).
Spoon sour cream over top.
Fold in with a fork.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until set.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Add mixed dry ingredients. Add rhubarb and nuts; pour into greased bread pan.
Mix sugar and butter; sprinkle onto batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: shrimp on rice(servings:  4)
directions: Cook desired amount of rice.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Add garlic and shrimp.
Brown shrimp for 4 minutes, about 2 minutes on each side.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Add in this order: celery, bell pepper, green onions and parsley.
Add salt to taste. Toss lightly for 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss until heated through.
Cook for 5 more minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water until tender; drain and arrange stalks in greased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch dish.
Place chicken on top. Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken; sprinkle with cheese and top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Combine beef, veal and onion.
Add water to crumbs.
Add crumbs, egg, salt, 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg and ginger to meat.
Mix well.
Shape meat mixture into 40 balls about the size of a walnut.
Dredge meat balls in flour.
Save remaining flour.
Melt butter in large frying pan.
Add meat balls and brown on all sides.
Cover and cook slowly 20 minutes.
Remove meat balls from frying pan.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add and blend in well the brown sugar.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Beat in eggs one at a time. Add mixture of flour, salt and baking powder and blend.
Add chocolate chips and walnuts.
Spread on greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cut in squares while warm.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Dip chicken in melted margarine.
Coat chicken with combined remaining ingredients.
Place in a greased pan.
Bake 400° for 20-25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: beef jerky
directions: Soak overnight. Spread out on cookie sheet. Bake 150° to 175° about
8 hours.

title: spaghetti sauce with meat
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain well.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add other ingredients and simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours, uncovered.
Serve over pasta.

title: apple sausage brunch cake
directions: Brown sausage.
Pour pancake mix into measuring cup and level off.
In a small mixer bowl, blend pancake mix, cinnamon, nutmeg, milk and egg at medium speed.
Pour in chopped apples.
Pour into greased baking dish (8 or 9-inch round pan).
Arrange sausage on top of batter.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot with maple syrup.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy (use whites at room temperature). Gradually add sugar and beat until mixture is stiff, like meringue.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in rest of ingredients. Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased aluminum foil-covered cookie sheet.
Put into preheated 350° oven.
Immediately turn oven off. Leave in oven for at least 3 hours.
Makes 24.

title: skillet roast
directions: Rub roast in flour and salt until coated. Heat skillet on medium heat; brown 10 minutes until brown on both sides.
Add water; cook until almost done. Add potatoes, carrots and onions (in slices) on roast. Add black pepper. Cook until done.

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Simmer raisins in water for 5 minutes. Drain and save 1/2 cup liquid. Blend shortening, spices and vanilla. Add sugar gradually, creaming thoroughly. Beat in eggs, one at a time. Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt. Add soda to the 1/2 cup of raisin liquid. Add flour alternately with liquid to creamed mixture, mixing well. Add raisins and chopped nuts. Chill. Drop by spoonfuls onto a greased baking sheet and bake in a hot oven 10 to 12 minutes. Yield: 3 dozen cookies.

title: tofu egg foo young
directions: Beat eggs in a bowl.
Mash the tofu into small pieces.
To the eggs add tofu, sprouts, celery, cheese, soy sauce, green onions and parsley.
Mix thoroughly.
Heat olive oil in skillet until hot.
Drop batter by tablespoon into the hot oil.
When one side is brown, turn and brown the other side.
Serves 4.

title: bavarian supper
directions: Quickly brown steaks in hot oil.
Add onion, cook 3 minutes or until almost tender.
Combine gravy mix, vinegar, brown sugar and 1 cup water.
Pour over steaks.
Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: parmesan zucchini strips
directions: Preheat oven to 350. In bowl, mix crumbs and cheese. Beat egg. Cut zucchini in strips lengthwise. Dip zucchini in egg and then in crumbs. Place one stick of butter on cookie sheet and melt in oven. Put zucchini strips on sheet and bake until golden brown.

title: hot chicken sandwiches
directions: Mix together and add water to make spreadable texture.
Heat and serve on buns.

title: baked cheese and rice
directions: Arrange layers of rice and cheese in a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle each layer with salt until dish is almost full.
Add enough milk to come 1/2 way to top of rice.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Dot with margarine and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potato chips.
Put in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until it bubbles.
Add potato chips on top and warm.
Yields 6 servings.

title: olive-artichoke-sausage pie
directions: Simmer sausage in water to cover 5 minutes.
Drain and cut into thin slices.
Simmer artichokes in small amount of boiling water 5 minutes.
Drain.
Combine eggs, olives, Ricotta and Parmesan in blender and blend until combined.
Sprinkle sausage and artichokes over bottom of pastry shell.
Spread cheese mixture over surface. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 375° for 30 minutes or longer until knife comes out clean.
Makes 8.

title: miniature fruit cakes
directions: Dredge fruit in some flour.
Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, then other ingredients.
Mix well and put into miniature paper baking cups.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Makes 11 to 12 dozen.

title: vanilla cooler drink
directions: Mix milk powder and a little soda until mixed well. When milk is mixed with soda, add the rest of the soda. Serves 1.

title: barbecue chip chop
directions: Simmer all ingredients 10 minutes, then add chipped ham.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken and save the broth.
Mix everything together and add enough broth to make it slushy.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes and then put biscuits on top (uncooked).
Turn oven up to 375° and bake until biscuits are brown.
Tasty and easy.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch dish.
Line bottom with single layer of whole crackers.
Prepare pudding, using cold milk.
Add Cool Whip to pudding.
Pour half over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers.
Add remaining pudding and final layer of crackers on top.
Cover with frosting and refrigerate overnight up to 2 days before serving.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add vanilla, sifted flour and salt. Stir well.
Form balls and add nuts.
Bake at 300° to 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: pound cake
directions: Have eggs, margarine and milk at room temperature.
Put all ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.
Put in greased tube pan and bake at 325° or 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: corn and rice casserole
directions: Mix soup, egg and corn.
Add rice, onion, salt and cheese. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: low sugar diabetic spice cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until all water is absorbed.
Add applesauce,
eggs, sweetener and oil; mix well.
Blend in soda and flour.
Add
flavorings
and
mix
well.
Turn dough into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: wassail(christmas drink)
directions: Simmer in crock-pot.
(You may want to use more cider.)

title: zucchini quiche
directions: With a whisk, combine all ingredients well except zucchini. Add zucchini.
Grease pan.
Pour mixture into pan and bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Test with toothpick for doneness.
It should be slightly brown on top.

title: shrimp in puff pastry
directions: Preheat oven and bake shells according to directions.
Keep warm.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Combine orange rind, orange juice and eggs.
Add to dry ingredients, mixing just to moisten.
Fold in berries, nuts and raisins.

title: peach-blueberry crumble
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Drain peaches and the blueberries from muffin mix.
Save 2 tablespoons of the blueberry juice.

title: charles and pat's strawberry cake
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add oil to cake mix.
Add eggs to mix, one at a time.
Add jello and 3/4 of berries.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 25 minutes (depending on oven).

title: dutch oven dinner
directions: Brown pork chops in butter.
Place in bottom of Dutch oven. Medium slice potatoes.
Use spices to taste.
Place on top of chops.
Core and medium slice apples.
Use spices to taste.
Place on potatoes.
Mix equal parts of honey and juice to cover ingredients.
With lid on, place in oven 1 hour at 350°.
When cooking is completed, remove and thicken broth for sauce.

title: basic yeast dough
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer, then knead when enough flour is added to make dough ball up.
This dough can be made into sweet rolls by rolling 1/2-inch thick and spreading with butter, cinnamon and sugar.
Roll and slice.
Also dinner rolls.
Let double in size.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: hummus bi tahini
directions: Wash chickpeas well.
Cover with the water and soak for 12 hours or overnight.
Put on to boil in the water in which they were soaked.
Boil gently for 2 hours.
Add 1 teaspoon salt and cook until very tender, about 3 hours in all.
Drain and serve some of the cooking liquid and 1 tablespoon of the peas.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Chop green onions as fine as possible.
Drain and chill canned shrimp.
Make sure all moisture is removed from shrimp and mash lightly with a fork.
Add green onions and shrimp to sour cream. Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: seafood salad
directions: This amount makes a 3-quart bowl full to take to a picnic.

title: coconut custard pie (2 pies)
directions: Hand mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add eggs; don't overbeat. Add vanilla, margarine and milk; fold in coconut.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes, then reduce temperature to 350° and bake for 15 minutes or at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Mix and pour in casserole dish.
Put 1 stack Ritz crackers, broken in chunks (not crushed) on top.
Pour 1 stick margarine (melted) over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook one package chopped broccoli. Drain well. Put broccoli in 10 x 6 inch baking dish. Combine rest of ingredients and mix into broccoli. If desired, sprinkle 1/4 cup cracker crumbs over all. Bake about 45 minutes.

title: betty's artichoke cheese dip
directions: Combine in souffl dish or 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift 1 cup sugar, flour and soda into mixing bowl.
Add fruit cocktail and juice.
Add eggs; beat until mixed well.
Pour into greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with brown sugar and pecans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Combine remaining sugar with remaining ingredients.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Pour over cake as soon as cake is removed from oven.

title: aunt ruby's chocolate cake
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa, cinnamon, sugar and soda.
Beat margarine, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Slowly add sifted ingredients, beating with a mixer.
Beat with mixer on high speed about 4 minutes.
Bake at 350° in a large cake pan (9 x 12-inch) for 40 to 45 minutes or in small pan (8 x 8-inch or rounds) for 30 to 35 minutes.
Be careful not to overbake.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and margarine in a bowl.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan on buttered aluminum foil (to keep from getting too brown on bottom).
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs (beaten), powdered sugar and vanilla until smooth. Pour over unbaked crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons sugar over while still warm.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: pumpkin roll cake
directions: Grease and flour 15 x 10-inch cookie sheet. Add the eggs to sugar. Mix together pumpkin, lemon juice. Add to egg/sugar mixture. Add the flour, spices, baking powder and salt. Spread in pan and sprinkle with nuts on top. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Turn out on towel with confectioners sugar. Roll into roll shape and cool. Re-roll and spread with mixture.

title: lemon fluff pie
directions: Beat egg whites until peaks; add sugar.
Beat again until stiff.
Blend in remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spoon into baked shell.
Freeze for 2 or 3 hours until firm.
Defrost 15 minutes before serving.

title: arctic melon pops
directions: In blender combine all ingredients.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Pour into 8 (5 ounce) cups.
Cover each with foil.
Poke small holes in foil and insert popsicle sticks.
Freeze approximately 4 to 6 hours.

title: cornell barbecue sauce
directions: Beat all ingredients together and brush on chicken or meat or fish.
Best results if you marinate in sauce for 2 hours.

title: nic-nac nutcracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until slightly stiff.
Add sugar gradually, beating constantly.
Add real vanilla; beat just to mix.
Fold in nuts and cracker crumbs.
Pour into well-greased pie plate and microwave for 4 1/2 to 5 minutes at High power.
After pie is cooled, slather with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
May be garnished with brown sugar, cinnamon and fruit slices if desired.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and
sugar.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Chill dough.
Drop
by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet lined with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Mash crackers.
Add 1/2 margarine to cheese and melt cheese.
Add other 1/2 margarine to crackers.
Put broccoli in casserole dish.
Add cheese and 3/4 of cracker mixture.
Cover with remaining 1/4 cracker mix.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, 30 minutes or microwave on High 12 minutes.

title: occidental hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix dry ingredients in saucepan.
Add milk.
Turn on heat and cook until thick.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.

title: meat sauce for rice balls
directions: In a large saucepan, cook beef, onion and garlic over medium heat, until meat is no longer pink; drain. Stir in the remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Discard bay leaves from meat sauce. May be served with Cheese Stuffed Rice Balls. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Put milk and diced cheese in the top of double boiler.
Remove from heat when melted.
Drain pimento and dice into small pieces. Add to cheese and milk with salt.
Yields 1 3/4 cups.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat; season.
Add green pepper and onion.
Cook and drain macaroni.
Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Cook for 30 minutes over medium heat.
If too thick, add more water.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Chop cabbage and onion; place in large salad bowl.
Crush dry noodles and combine with seeds and almonds on baking sheet.
Broil until lightly browned. Add to cabbage.

title: tomato rice soup
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat. Cover and simmer 8 to 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: pineapple crisp
directions: Spread pineapple (do not drain) on bottom of greased loaf pan. Spread cake mix on top of pineapple, then spread margarine on top of this.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mock pate
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and liver sausage, mixing until well
blended.
Add
remaining
ingredients;
mix
well. Chill. Serve with party rye or assorted crackers.

title: meat and potato pie
directions: Cook roast.
Thicken drippings a little.
Cook potatoes a little.
Cut roast in small pieces.
Add potatoes, roast, onion and carrots to pie crust.
Put other pie crust on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water until tender; drain. In saucepan, melt butter.
Blend flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk; cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add onion (optional) and cheese; stir until melted.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients.
Combine margarine and stuffing mix with a dash of salt and pepper.
Line casserole dish with stuffing (you can use a pastry blender to get a good consistency of mix and margarine).

title: banana split cake
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt butter; add graham cracker crumbs to make first layer.
Mix and beat cream cheese, sugar and milk until fluffy (about 10 to 15 minutes).
Spread on crumbs as second layer.
Next layer is bananas, sliced.
Add crushed pineapple as next layer.
Garnish with cherries and nuts.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple as last layer.

title: warm potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and drain.
Place potatoes and onion in a bowl. Combine all other ingredients and mix all together.
Yield: 4 servings, 69 calories and 1.2 fat per 1/2 cup serving.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Mix cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Line muffin pan with cupcake papers.
Place one vanilla wafer in each tin.
Fill with batter.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in cookie sheet. Spread graham cracker crumbs across bottom of pan. Sprinkle chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, chopped nuts and coconut evenly over graham cracker crumb base.
Pour Eagle Brand milk evenly over the coconut layer.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: the best chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together the sugars, butter or margarine, shortening and the eggs.
Add the flour, soda and salt; beat well.
Add the oats and chocolate chips.
Mix until throughout dough.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cookies will appear underdone.
Do not overcook. Enjoy!

title: perfection punch
directions: Mix lemonade concentrate and the pineapple juice in a punch bowl. Add Riesling; blend well. Keep chilled.
Just before serving, add ice cubes or the ice ring.
Pour in the champagne. Garnish as desired.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Mix well and pour into a well-greased casserole dish.

title: chicken creole
directions: Cook chicken and seasonings until tender.
Take from pot and cool.
Reserve broth.

title: teenie-weenie cook in
directions: Cut a hole in the top of the cabbage to fit the can of sterno. Cut the bottom of the cabbage off so it will sit on a plate.
Now let your imagination be your guide.
Affix the food, bite size pieces, onto the cabbage with the toothpicks.
The meat can be heated by holding over the lit sterno.
Great for parties!

title: sloppy joes
directions: Saute ground meat and onion.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until mixed.
Add water if too thick.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: pound cake
directions: Grease and flour tube cake pan.
Mix first 2 ingredients.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and gradually add sifted flour. Beat about 4 minutes at medium speed.
Place in cold oven.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan.

title: apple dinks
directions: Cut shortening into flour; add sugar, egg, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Mix apples into mixture and pour into greased 12 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until apples are done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions and drain. Arrange broccoli in a buttered casserole.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice
and cheese.
Spoon over broccoli.
Top with pimentos, crackers and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken chow mein casserole
directions: Cook butter, flour, milk and soup in pan.
Makes a sauce.
Add chicken.
Put noodles on bottom of pan or bowl.
Pour in mixture. Cover with noodles.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: dad bernath's paper bag apple pie
directions: Peel apples and cut into bite-size pieces (about 7 cups). Place in bowl.
To make filling, combine 1/2 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix well and sprinkle over apples.
Toss apples to coat well.
Spoon mixture into pastry shell; drizzle with lemon juice.
To make topping, combine 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup flour in a small bowl.
Cut in oleo.
Sprinkle over apples.

title: rainbow cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Put in large cake pan and place in cold oven; turn to 300° and bake approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit salad dressing(this dressing helps to make a great fruit salad.)
directions: Heat fruit and water to boiling.
In a separate bowl, mix cornstarch, sugar, butter and eggs.
Add to fruit mixture and cook until thickened.
Dressing will be thick.
Make Dream Whip and fold in dressing to thin it a bit.

title: ice cream salad
directions: Melt butter in a medium saucepan.
Stir in sugar.
Cook until bubbling.
Add orange juice and lemon juice with the strawberries, peaches, banana and cinnamon.
Bring to a simmer.
Cook uncovered for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir frequently.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Hard boil the eggs.
When cool, mix yolks with vinegar, salt, pepper, mustard, melted margarine and Miracle Whip.
Fill cut in half eggs with mixture.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: delicious strawberry punch
directions: Blend strawberries, pineapple and lemonade in a blender on high until smooth.
Pour over ice in punch bowl and add ginger ale.

title: sirloin on a stick
directions: Mix marinade in a bowl.
Add sirloin; toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate overnight until use.
Preheat broiler.
Remove beef from marinade and thread onto 4 skewers (3 pieces on each) on the diagonal.
Place meat 4 inches from heat.
Broil 3 to 4 minutes on each side, brushing with marinade and turning once for medium-rare meat.

title: gorp(good ol' raisins and peanuts; trail mix)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in airtight container. Yield: 7 cups.
Serving size: 1/3 cup.
Per serving: 116 calories. Exchanges: 1 starch/bread, 1 fat.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Cover the entire cookie sheet with whole graham crackers.
Heat margarine and brown sugar to boiling and boil over medium heat for 2 minutes.
Pour over graham crackers.
Sprinkle top with chopped nuts.
Bake for 15 minutes or until the tops of all the cookies have bubbles on them.
Do not burn.
(This is a very easy recipe.)

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Smooth and press up on sides of pan.
Bake in 350° oven until firm to touch, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Beat eggs until light in color. Sift remaining ingredients together and add gradually to eggs; add lemon juice.
Pour over crust and bake until light golden brown, 25 minutes.
When done, sift powdered sugar over top.

title: broiled scallops
directions: Spray broiler pan with Pam.
Arrange the scallops flat on the pan and lightly spray them with Pam.
Broil for 4 minutes, then pour cooking sherry over them. Pour about half of the sherry, then after the sherry cooks down, pour the rest over the scallops. Broil about 4 to 5 minutes longer.
The scallops should be translucent.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix and pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: almond parmesan chicken
directions: Combine almonds, Parmesan cheese and spices in a bowl; set aside.
Dip chicken in butter, coat evenly, then roll in nuts, cover completely.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir well and drop on wax paper.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Drain and rinse.
Add remaining ingredients and toss.
Mix well and refrigerate.
Toss again before serving.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Add shortening or lard in small pieces and use fork or pastry blender to make uniform crumbs.
Add water, a tablespoon at a time, and mix until mixture forms a rough mass. Wrap and refrigerate for at least 4 hours before rolling out.
I use lard for fruit pies and shortening for cream pies.
Makes one double-crust pie.
Serves 8.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Beat cream cheese until soft.
Add coloring and flavoring. Gradually add sugar.
Knead until consistency is like pie dough. (For firmer, add more sugar.)
Roll into marble size balls.
Dip one side into granulated or colored crystal sugar.
Place sugar side down into cavity of mold, pressing from edge to center. Unmold at once onto waxed paper.
Let air dry.
Makes approximately 24 pieces.

title: mexican soup
directions: Brown onions with ground meat. Drain off all fat. Add in all other ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes. Serve over favorite tortilla chips. Can garnish with grated cheese.

title: coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all the ingredients together in a large mixing bowl.
Pour into the pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: crystallized flowers
directions: Beat egg white lightly to liquefy in small bowl.
Rinse flower petals or blossoms; dry thoroughly.
With small brush, paint both sides of each petal with egg white, being sure to cover petals completely.
Use wooden pick to separate leaves of multi-petal flowers.
Sprinkle lightly with sugar.
Place on rack or baking sheet; let dry in cool, dry place until sugar has hardened.
Store in airtight container to use throughout year.
Fun!!!

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix everything well, except flour.
Slowly blend in flour. Preheat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet and press cookies flat with fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: no apple apple pie
directions: Mix water, sugar and cream of tartar.
Bring to a boil.
Add crackers and boil 1 minute.
Pour into pie shell (unbaked) and dot with butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Add top crust and bake at 400° until crust is done.

title: casserole
directions: Bake at least 1 hour at 350°.

title: super simple bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add eggs and milk.
Beat until fairly smooth.
Batter will be thin.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 40 minutes in greased bread loaf pan.

title: squash dressing casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 325° until brown for 35 minutes.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Mix popped popcorn and pecan halves together in large buttered pan (I recommend a roasting pan).
Keep warm in oven while making "caramel."

title: chicken coleslaw
directions: Mix cabbage, chicken, apples, grapes, celery and walnuts in a large bowl.
Set aside.
Mix sour cream, mayo, honey, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over cabbage mixture and toss gently.
Cover and chill 1 hour.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with Marshmallow Creme. Pour in bowl and serve with pieces of fruit (apples, grapes, strawberries, orange wedges, etc.).

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift in flour, salt, soda, chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: taco rice skillet
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain grease.
Add tomatoes, rice, taco seasoning and enough tomato juice or water to make 2 1/2 cups.
Bring to boil and simmer until rice is done.
Before serving, top with grated cheese and lettuce.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, including carrots, together.
Stir in eggs, oil, vanilla and pineapple.
Add nuts.
Beat on medium speed.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place batter into 3 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake 30 minutes or until center is done. Cool.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: chili
directions: Always use fresh, not frozen, meat.
Cover meat with water and bring to boil.
Add catsup, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Cook on medium heat about 2 1/2 hours, stirring often.
Mash meat with potato masher several times while cooking.
Add more water if needed.

title: graham cracker goodies
directions: Line cookie sheet with graham crackers. Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Mix sugar, butter and oleo. Boil 4 minutes. Pour over crackers and bake at 275° for 12 minutes. Let cool, then break in pieces.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour water over Bran Buds and let cool.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add sugar, flour, baking soda, salt, All-Bran, buttermilk and eggs.
Fold in Bran Buds and water.
Fill greased muffin tins 1/2 full and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Muffin dough keeps in refrigerator for two weeks.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Saute onions, bell peppers and garlic in butter until soft. Combine with shredded cabbage, 1/2 of cheese, bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Pour into casserole dish.
Pour half and half over all of casserole.
Cover casserole.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
(May have to add more half and half before done if it gets too dry.)

title: corn chowder
directions: In saucepan cook potatoes and salt in water to cover until tender. Add bacon, corn, milk, water, soup, butter and pepper. Heat stirring frequently. Garnish each serving with parsley.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown chops; salt and pepper.
Drain off fat.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over chops in baking dish.
Cover and bake for 40 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients together well in a bowl.
Pour into oiled baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven until done and lightly browned on top.

title: ground beef surprise
directions: Press raw beef in the bottom of a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle onions over meat. Put Tater Tots evenly over the onions.
Spoon soup over the Tater Tots and spread evenly.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour.

title: pasta with salmon and fresh veggies
directions: Heat broiler.

Dot salmon with 1 Tbsp. butter.	Sprinkle with thyme, 1/2 tsp. dill, 1/4 tsp. black pepper and 1/8 tsp. salt. Broil 5 to 6 inches from heat 8 to 10 minutes, until salmon almost flakes to touch of fork.
Remove from broiler; keep warm.

title: grape juice punch
directions: Mix grape juice with 1 quart of water.
Add lemonade with prescribed amount of water on can.
Put ice cream in last. Sweeten to taste before adding ice cream.
Serve immediately.

title: taco chicken
directions: Mix soup, chili sauce, water and pepper sauce.
Dust chicken with flour; dip in soup mixture.
Roll in chips.
Place on rack in shallow baking pan.
Drizzle with melted butter or margarine. Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: coconut cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, cream cheese and shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating with electric mixer until light and fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift before measuring 3 cups flour and re-sift with baking powder and salt.
Add sifted ingredients to cream mixture at low speed, mixing until well blended.
Fold in coconut and flavorings.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Butter 2 large baking sheets; set aside.
Butter sides of a heavy 3-quart saucepan.
In saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup, margarine and 1/2 cup water.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat to boiling.
Clip candy thermometer to side of pan.
Cook and stir over medium-low heat to 275°, soft crack stage.
Add nuts; cook and stir to 295°, hard crack stage.
Remove saucepan from heat; remove thermometer.
Quickly sprinkle
soda over mixture, stirring constantly.
Immediately pour onto prepared baking sheets.
Cool; break into pieces.

title: he man chili
directions: Brown ground beef with onions, peppers and celery until done and tender.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Makes a large amount.
Let simmer approximately 2 hours so the flavors will mix.

title: kahlua
directions: Dissolve sugar in water. Add vanilla bean; boil 30 minutes. Remove bean. Mix well, stirring while adding the vodka and coffee. Seal for 21 days. Makes two fifths. "Longer it sits, better it is."

title: fresh apple cookies(serves double)
directions: Mix in order given. Add apples and blend. Spoon out 1 teaspoon dough into 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar mixture. Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: savory hash
directions: In a large pot or electric skillet, melt butter. Add beef, diced potatoes, onion, beef broth, salt and pepper. Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender, approximately 30 minutes. Mix a little cornstarch and cold water and thicken somewhat.

title: pate
directions: Simmer calves liver in water to cover for 25 minutes or until done.
Put through finest blade of food chopper or chop in blender.
Add salad oil, finely chopped onion, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix thoroughly.
Place in lightly oiled mold.
Cover and chill.
Before serving, garnish with finely chopped hard-boiled egg.

title: water chestnut appetizer
directions: Wrap chestnuts with bacon.
Use toothpick to hold together. Bake at 400° until browned; drain off grease.

title: golden chicken rolls
directions: Pound each chicken breast half to a 7 1/2 x 6-inch piece. Place a slice of ham and cheese on each.
Roll up like a jelly roll.

title: artichoke hearts salad
directions: Drain artichoke hearts, olives and mushrooms.
