Cube cheese and mix with vegetables.
Add seasonings and oil.
Toss and let stand at least 1 hour before serving.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook coarsely chopped cabbage 5 minutes in slightly salted boiling water.
Drain and place in buttered casserole.
Cover with chicken soup and Cheez Whiz.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, spread oil on bottom of pan.
Add ingredients, except for chips; mix well.
Add chips; stir.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
Test with toothpick in center to see if done.
Tastes best if cake is cold with whipped cream on top.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions together; drain.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Place cheese on top.
Mix gravy mix and pour over cheese. Arrange Tater Tots on top to cover dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash and dry green tomatoes.
Slice into 1/4-inch rounds. Combine eggs and milk.
Combine flour, cornmeal, salt and pepper. Dip tomatoes in egg and milk mixture.
Roll in flour and cornmeal mixture.
Return to egg and milk mixture.
Roll again in flour and cornmeal.
Fry in hot oil in a heavy iron skillet, turning once until both sides are golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Makes 6 servings.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place butter in measuring cup, place over heat and melt. Blend in the flour and seasoning.
Add milk and cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Layer 1/2 of potatoes, onion and sauce in greased pan. Repeat layers, cover and bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon-nut slices
directions: Slice refrigerated cookie dough into 1/4-inch slices.
Combine pecans and cinnamon.
Dip one side of cookie in pecan mixture. Place nut side upon ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until cookies are lightly browned, 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: grandma petty's raisin spice cake
directions: Put the golden raisins in a pan; cover with water and bring to a boil.
Simmer about five minutes.
Retain the raisins.
Pour one-half cup of the raisin juice into the bowl; add the perked coffee and baking soda.
Cream together the sugar, vegetable shortening and margarine; add the egg and juice/coffee/soda combination; add flour and spices.
Add vanilla, blending well after each addition.
Lastly, blend in the raisins and nuts. Prepare either a small angel food cake pan or 8 x 8-inch square pan by greasing and flouring lightly.
Bake at 350° for one hour. Frost with simple confectioners sugar, milk and butter frosting when cool.

title: grandma's greenies
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
They are best when chewy.

title: chicken capri
directions: Put Bisquick mix and chicken in a bag and shake.
Brown chicken in a skillet with oil or cooking spray.
Place in a baking dish.
Mix can of soup with 1/2 can of water.
Pour over chicken and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: charcoal steak marinade
directions: Combine the mixture and pour over your steaks 2 to 3 hours before cooking.

title: corn muffins
directions: Mix together and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: ham waikiki
directions: Drain pineapple.
Set aside slices and juice separately.
In a small saucepan, combine cornstarch with Worcestershire sauce and ginger.
Blend in reserved pineapple juice (about 1 cup).
Cook and stir over moderate heat until thickened.
Place ham on a rack in a broiler pan.
Brush pineapple juice mixture over ham.
Place under a preheated hot broiler for 10 minutes, brushing once more.
Turn ham; add reserved pineapple slices to broiler rack.
Brush ham and pineapple slices with pineapple juice mixture.
Broil ham until glazed, 10 minutes.

title: 3 bean baked beans
directions: Drain beans and save juice.
Mix all ingredients together and place in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cover with bacon strips.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 2 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix ingredients with jello dissolved in the 2 cups of hot water.
Place in jello mold to set.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and Crisco together.
Add eggs, one at a time, alternating eggs and flour.
Add flavor and salt.
Fold in sour cream.

title: party potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and drain.
Beat sour cream and cream cheese until blended.
Add hot potatoes gradually until all are blended. Add milk at this time, if too stiff.
Season with garlic salt. `Put in 2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter and top with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
If refrigerated, bake 1 hour.

title: cinnamon bun cake
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Sprinkle in nuts and raisins.
Arrange frozen roll dough on top.
Mix sugars, pudding and cinnamon and sprinkle over dough.
Melt butter and pour over dough.

title: taco soup
directions: Mix all together and simmer in crock-pot on low for 2 hours.

title: broccoli-corn bake
directions: Mix all together.
Place in a casserole.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in the 1 1/2 cups warm water. Add salt, brown sugar and flour.
Knead until smooth.
Cover with cloth and let rise 15 minutes.
Taking small amount of dough, roll out into a rope.
Lift ends and cross over.
Twist and tack ends into top of pretzel (by pressing gently).
Continue with rest of dough. Taking pretzels, one at a time, place in boiling soda water for 1 minute.
Place on greased cookie sheets and sprinkle with kosher salt.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve immediately. Makes approximately 16.

title: breakfast muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients in one bowl.
In another bowl mix eggs, milk and shortening.
Mix well, then combine ingredients. Fill greased muffin tins as usual.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: kamaboko dip
directions: Mix ingredients and spread on Ritz crackers.

title: rhubarb apple crisp with vanilla ice cream
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Lightly butter a 10-inch pie plate. In a mixing bowl, stir together the flour, oats, brown sugar and salt.
Add the pieces of butter and, using your fingertips, pinch the butter into the flour mixture until pea-size pieces form.
Set aside.

title: graham cracker bar
directions: Layer bottom of jelly roll pan with graham crackers.
Bring to a boil the margarine, butter and sugar.
Pour over crackers and spread evenly.
Sprinkle with chopped walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool in pan.

title: chocolate wacky cake
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl before mixing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
A very moist cake.

title: different chocolate cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; cover and let set 10 minutes. Cream butter, 2 eggs and vanilla; add oatmeal mixture.
Mix well. Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: potato boats
directions: Cut potatoes and squash (separately) into small cubes of equal size.
Boil potatoes.
Add squash approximately 10 minutes later for even cooking.
Drain and mash the two together for mashed potato-style texture.
Add the curry powder and melted butter; season to taste.
Place mixture in a baking dish.
Brush butter across top of mixture.
Sprinkle top with more curry powder and paprika.
Brown in oven at 350°.

title: grace's pasta e fagiole bianco
directions: Boil pasta and set aside.
Brown garlic, onion and oil in a nonstick frying pan.
Olive oil is optional.
Puree 1 can of cannellini beans with water in can in a blender.

title: gene's brisket
directions: Trim as much fat as possible from brisket.
Place brisket in 10 x 14-inch pan.

Pour liquid smoke and Lea & Perrins over meat. Sprinkle well on both sides with spices and meat tenderizer. Cover with foil and marinate at least 4 hours in refrigerator. Bake, covered, at 200° for 12 hours.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine the ingredients until well blended.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Roll mixture into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place on a baking sheet and put into oven.
Bake about 20 minutes.
Makes about 30 Sausage Balls.
Serve hot for best results.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Trim and bone meat; cut into thin pieces, about 2-inches long. Place meat in bowl, add mustard and mix well.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Melt butter in large skillet and cook onions over low heat until soft, but not brown.
Remove from pan.
Brown meat in skillet over low heat until brown, turning occasionally.
Then add paprika, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, tomato juice and liquid from mushrooms.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until meat is tender.
Stir in onions, mushrooms and sour cream.
Continue cooking just until mixture is hot; do not boil.
Sprinkle parsley flakes on top.
Serve over hot rice or noodles.
Serves 6.

title: buttercream icing(cake decorators icing)
directions: Add the salt to the water and stir.
Add this to the sugar, vanilla and shortening.
Beat with a mixer (watch carefully, it is hard on the mixer).
This recipe is enough to ice an 8 or 9-inch two layered cake.

title: barbecue sauce from scratch
directions: After all vegetables are chopped, put in a large pot and cook until all the veggies are soft, about 30 minutes.
Press through a sieve or food mill.
Put back on stove and cook until mixture is reduced to about 1/2, or about 45 minutes.
Add with the sieved mixture the remaining ingredients, and let cook.
Tie peppercorns in a cheesecloth and drop in the mixture to cook.
After all ingredients are together, they should cook about 1 1/2 hours.
Stir frequently to keep from sticking.
When of desired thickness, pour hot, into sterilized jars and seal.
Process pints 20 minutes in boiling water bath.
Yield:
4 to 5 pints.
(To use, add 1 cup salad oil to 1 pint and mix thoroughly.)

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Chop onion and saute in margarine.
Add frozen broccoli and cook about 5 minutes.
Add cooked rice, soup, Cheez Whiz and water chestnuts.
Pour into casserole and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°. Ritz crackers can be used as a topping.

title: lemon bundt cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour all at once; beat well.
Add lemon extract.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done; cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruits.
Sprinkle Tang and instant pudding over fruit and mix well.

title: yummy nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 220° or 225°.
Beat egg white until stiff. Add light brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat a little; add nuts and coat good.
Put on lightly greased (use margarine) cookie sheet. Bake 30 minutes.
Turn oven off and let set 30 minutes before taking up.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients until smooth batter.
Pour into pie dish.
Drain peaches (save juice).
Place peaches 1-inch from rim so crust can come up during baking.
Cream cream cheese, sugar and peach juice.
Mix until creamy and pour on top of peaches. Sprinkle with 1 1/2 teaspoons sugar mixed with cinnamon. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm or cool. Preparation Time: 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream the sugar and oil.
Add eggs.
Add flour, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, water, pumpkin and nuts.
Blend well. Bake in 3 greased and floured bread pans for 1 hour at 350°.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° until knife comes out clean (50 to 55 minutes).
Serve with topping.

title: seafood salad
directions: Marinate macaroni in French dressing.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Keep chilled.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Mix Roka Bleu and Old English Kraft together with the cream cheese.
Roll ball in crushed pecans.
Chill until ready to use.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Mix soft margarine and graham cracker crumbs.
Pat onto a baking sheet.
Evenly distribute the coconut, nuts and chocolate chips.
Drizzle the Eagle Brand over the layers.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter popcorn
directions: Pop popcorn.
Combine corn syrup and brown sugar and cook until hot and bubbly.
Stir in peanut butter and cook until blended.
Pour over corn and stir in.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat together oil, eggs and sugar.
Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to mixture.
Next add apples, nuts and raising. Grease and flour 13x9 pan.
Bake at 350 about 45 minutes or until done.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spread nuts and coconut over bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Mix cake mix according to directions and pour over the coconut and nuts.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients except milk, stir in enough milk to get medium stiff batter.
Cook in pan after you fry fish.
Cook on medium-high heat.

title: quick cinnamon muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease 10 (2 1/2-inch) muffin pan cups.
Shape 2 biscuits into a ball.
Dip in melted butter, then in mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Place in muffin pan and bake 10 to 15 minutes or until muffins are crusty.
Serve warm. Makes 10.

title: vanilla pudding
directions: Note:
Use 1 fresh egg in place of Egg Beaters.
Beat egg and mix with the milk before using.

title: watermelon snow
directions: In blender container or food processor bowl with metal blades, place watermelon cubes.
Cover; process until smooth.
Pour watermelon puree into 2 quart non-metal freezer container; stir in remaining ingredients.
Freeze 2 hours; stir well.
Freeze until slush consistency, about 3 to 4 hours longer.
Makes ten 1/2 cup servings.

title: pink pie
directions: Mix the jello with the hot water and cool. Cream the cream cheese and sugar.
Combine all the ingredients.
Put in shell. Refrigerate until set. Serves 6.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix flour, sugar and baking soda; cut in shortening with pastry blender until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Stir in sour cream until mixture leaves side of bowl and round up into a ball.
Turn onto lightly floured cloth-covered board.
Knead lightly 10 times.
Roll or pat dough 1/2-inch thick. Cut with floured 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place about 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown, 10 to 12 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Yields about 18 biscuits.

title: italian pasta soup
directions: Brown pork with fennel seed, basil, 1/2 onion and garlic in a stock pot.
Once meat is lightly browned, add the beans, water, bouillon cubes, tomatoes and pepper flakes.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.
Add remaining onion, green pepper and wine and simmer another 20 minutes.
Add salt and spaghetti that has been broken into 2-inch pieces.
Cook just until spaghetti is al dente.

title: bean dip
directions: Layer ingredients in a 9 x 9-inch Pyrex dish in order listed, ending with cheese (grate as much cheese as you like).
Bake at 400° to 450° for 15 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender, drain.
Boil eggs, 8 to 10 minutes; set aside.
Put potatoes into bowl, add mustard and enough Miracle Whip to moisten.
Add relish and all but two eggs. Mix to desired consistency.
Slice the two remaining eggs and garnish top of potato salad.
Serve hot or cold.

title: marshmallow cream fudge
directions: In saucepan, mix marshmallow cream, sugar, evaporated milk, salt and margarine together.
Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce to moderate heat and boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir until chips are melted.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan. Chill until firm.
Makes 2 1/4 pounds of fudge.

title: apple strudel(germany)
directions: Spread (brush) phyllo dough with melted butter.
Cover with damp paper towels.
Mix fruit, sugar and lemon juice.
Spread fruit down center of phyllo dough.
Roll jelly roll style.
Make 3 diagonal knife slits.
Spread top with melted butter.
Sprinkle top with sugar.
Bake at 370° until brown and until apples pierced with fork are tender.
Serves 4.

title: glazed ham and sweet potatoes(microwave)
directions: Arrange sweet potatoes (yams) around edges of 12 x 8-inch dish. Place ham slices in center overlapping slightly to fit dish. Combine remaining ingredients to make glaze; pour half over ham and yams.
Cover dish with wax paper.
Microwave at High for 4 minutes. Pour remaining glaze over ham and yams.
Do not cover.
Microwave at High 4 to 7 minutes or until ham is hot.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly in large mixing bowl. Pour mixture into a greased and floured 8 x 8 pan. Bake at between 350° to 375° for approximately 30 to 45 minutes or until brown. When doubling the receipt, cooking time will be 1 hour.

title: english trifle
directions: Arrange jelly rolls in bottom of bowl.
Soak with sherry. Pour fruit cocktail over rolls with 1/2 of juice.
Make custard (directions on box, Publix).
When cool, pour over cocktail.
Top with whipped cream, cherries and almonds.
Oh, it's soo-good.

title: kids coolers
directions: Place 1 cherry in each cube in ice tray.
Cover with pineapple juice.
Freeze.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix together yeast and hot water.
Add sugar, eggs, salt, warm water and melted butter.
Mix with 4 cups flour.
Let rise until double.
Roll out.
Spread with melted butter.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon until butter is soaked up.
Roll up and cut.
Let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
While still hot, spread with butter frosting.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.
Make ahead so it can be chilled.

title: chicken continental
directions: Saute chicken, mushrooms and garlic in oil in a large skillet until chicken is lightly browned.
Add broth, beans, salt and pepper. Bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice. Remove from heat; cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Makes about 6 cups or 4 servings, less than 350° calories each.

title: india curry tuna salad
directions: Mix up day before.
Can be used for sandwiches or for stuffed tomatoes or on crackers.

title: p.t.a.  chicken salad
directions: Mix and serve on a bed of lettuce

title: chester cookies
directions: Simmer
raisins
in 1 1/4 cups water until soft.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, then dry ingredients and mix well.
Add juice
from
cooked raisins.
Last, gently stir in raisins.
Bake for
to 10 minutes at 350°.
This is a very soft cookie.

title: lemon whippersnaps
directions: Grease cookie sheets.
Combine cake mix, whipped topping and egg in large bowl.
Stir until well mixed.
Drop by teaspoons into powdered sugar; roll to coat.
Place balls 1 1/2-inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until light golden brown (for chewy cookies do not overbake).
Remove from cookie sheet; cool.
Store in tightly closed container.

title: cinnamon rice pudding
directions: Combine 3 cups milk, uncooked rice and next four ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Bring mixture to a boil over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: foolproof meringue
directions: Mix cornstarch, water and 2 tablespoons sugar; cook together until clear, then set aside.
Add a bit of salt to egg whites and whip until foamy or standing in peaks, at which time add the cornstarch mixture.
Continue beating until creamy, then add 6 tablespoons sugar gradually, beating until very creamy.
Pile on pie and brown at 325°.

title: potato salad
directions: Cut potatoes up in large bowl, add all ingredients except 2 boiled eggs and cayenne.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Melt butter and add to brown sugar.
Add eggs, flour, vanilla and nuts.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken wings oregano
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Mix ingredients together (except chicken).
Brush on chicken.
Broil 10 minutes on each side, basting occasionally.
When done, pour remaining sauce over chicken and serve.

title: stewed turkey necks
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper in paper or plastic bag.
Add a few necks at a time.
Shake to coat.
Heat shortening or oil in a stock pot on medium heat.
Brown necks on all sides.
Add onion, celery, garlic and bay leaf.
Saute 3 minutes.
Add water, bouillon cubes, celery seed and red pepper flakes.
Cover.
Cook on medium-low heat for 2 hours or until meat is very tender.
Add additional salt and pepper to taste, if needed.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach, squeezing dry.
Mix together all ingredients (except bread) and refrigerate.

title: spicy roasted potatoes
directions: In a medium bowl, mix mustards, oil, garlic, tarragon, paprika and red pepper into a smooth paste.
Cut unpeeled potatoes into 1-inch chunks.
Pat dry with paper towel and toss with mustard mixture until coated.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion; drain.
In a crock-pot, set on low or on top of stove; mix all of the ingredients.
Simmer; the longer, the better.
You can substitute ground pork or ground turkey.

title: white fluffy frosting
directions: Make a white sauce with 1/4 cup milk and flour.
Gradually add to 3/4 cup milk in a saucepan.
Over medium heat, cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Set aside until completely cold. Beat Crisco and sugar until very fluffy.
Add cold white sauce to sugar mixture.
Add vanilla; beat until very fluffy.
Frost cake, making frosting stand up in peaks all over cake by tapping spatula all over cake.

title: watermelon drink
directions: Place all the ingredients in the blender and blend for 2 minutes.
Refrigerate for an hour and serve.

title: red bean soup
directions: Chop bacon and onion. Cook bacon. Add onion and saute.
Drain. Blend 1 can of beans and add.
Add remaining ingredients and 2 cans water. Cook 30 minutes. Serve with rice, grated cheese and chopped onions or Fritos.

title: oysters ruth
directions: Cut top off French bread for a lid.
Scoop out soft bread. Put in drained oysters.
Pour cocktail sauce over oysters.
Put on lid.
Wrap bread in foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Serve in slices.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in flour and corn meal.
Add eggs, milk, vanilla flavoring and lemon juice.
Mix together and pour into uncooked pie crust.
Bake in oven at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix all together and form into any size meatballs (appetizers or larger for dinner).

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Pour small amount in pan.
Saute onion and celery.
Add uncooked rice, broccoli, 1 1/2 cups water, soup and cheese.
Add chicken.
Mix and heat together.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Brown chicken breasts in butter.
Put in glass dish.
Slice mushrooms over top.
Sprinkle with lots of Parmesan cheese.
Pour heavy whipped cream over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve over rice cooked with chicken broth.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown and crumble meat.
Add all ingredients except cheese. Simmer 20 minutes.
Put grated cheese on top.
Put into oven and brown cheese.

title: four layer chocolate cake
directions: Mix and press into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and cocoa.
Pour hot water over sugar mixture.
Add
eggs
and
mix
well.
Sift	flour, salt, baking soda
and
baking powder together.	Add flour mixture, milk and vanilla
to
sugar	mixture.
Pour	into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° approximately 50 minutes.

title: creamed peach pie
directions: Mix together sugar, oleo and flour with mixer until creamy. Add egg, vanilla and salt.
Mix well. Pour over about 1-quart drained peaches (sliced) which have been placed in unbaked pie shell.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: shrooms-n-cheese
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems.
Place caps in rows on foil lined pan.
Cut cheese into tiny pieces and place one piece in each mushroom cap.
Top each with small dab of margarine.
Broil until cheese melts and serve.

title: seafood salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; refrigerate.

title: roast wild goose with baked apple
directions: Cook goose giblets until tender.
Chop and add to stuffing made by mixing bread crumbs, onion, fat, sage, salt and pepper. After blending and washing the goose thoroughly, stuff, sew the neck and back closed.
Roast for 15 minutes at 500°.
Reduce the heat to 350° and cook about 1 1/2 hours.
Wash and core apples; sprinkle with brown sugar.
Stuff with seasoned sweet potatoes. Bake until tender; serve hot with goose.

title: spirelle and ham skillet
directions: Cook onion and ham in hot oil until ham is browned.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes on low.
Add cheese, parsley and spirelle.
Serve at once.

title: robbins oatmeal molasses cookies
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients together well.
Drop by teaspoons of dough on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields about 5 dozen.

title: holiday ribbon pie
directions: *Suggested fillings:
1 cup finely chopped cookies, candies, nuts, mini marshmallows, chocolate chips, peanut butter chips or 1/2 cup jam.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter in a deep 13 x 9-inch dish.
Put chicken on top of butter.	Pour Veg-All on top of chicken.
Mix cream of chicken soup and chicken broth together in a separate bowl and then pour over Veg-All.
In another separate bowl, mix Bisquick and milk. Pour this mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Makes a very large casserole.
It's the best chicken pot pie ever and so easy.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix well.
Set aside and let rise double.
Roll out and bake or store in refrigerator.

title: mom's beans
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: hootenanny pancakes
directions: Combine eggs, milk and salt in blender until fluffy.
Tap in flour, a little at a time, until well blended.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 425°.
When butter is bubbly, add batter. Immediately return to oven.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: microwave pralines
directions: Combine sugar and whipping cream in bowl.
Microwave on High for 13 minutes.
Remove and quickly add butter, pecans, salt and vanilla.
Beat the mixture, then spoon out by tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Allow to cool.

title: macaroni-potato salad
directions: Cube cooked potatoes, cut up eggs and chopped onions; mix together milk and mayonnaise.
Add mustard, salt, sugar and vinegar.
Toss with potatoes, macaroni, egg and onion.

title: carousel burgers
directions: Mix thoroughly but lightly.
Shape into patties and cook.

title: baked beans
directions: Saute onion
and
green
pepper in 3 tablespoons water. Mix all other ingredients together with vegetables.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.

In a large bowl, combine first 4 ingredients and blend well. Stir in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt. Blend well. Shape into 1-inch balls. Combine 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon. Roll balls in sugar mixture. Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until set.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.

title: jellied apples
directions: Cook on
top of stove.	Pare and core apples.
Place in enameled pan and sift sugar over them.
Add 1/4 cup cold water and lemon
juice.
Cover
and
let come to boil.
Remove cover and continue
to
cook.
When
bottom
of apple is clear, turn with an egg
whip
or spoon so other end will be in the syrup. When done (or
syrup	is
ready
to jell), take up apples and place
on a platter.
Fill center with cherries or dates, nuts or raisins. Serves 8.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Peel and cube avocados.
Save the seeds.
Dice the tomato also. Put together in a bowl.
Add finely chopped cilantro and onion, lemon juice, salt and a dash or so of hot sauce.
Mix and serve.

title: potatoes deluxe(large casserole for a large group.)
directions: Mix well and pour into a 13x9-inch casserole baking dish. Crush 1 cup of potato chips for topping and sprinkle over potatoes. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Easily doubled.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of celery

title: pink punch
directions: A careless word may kindle strife,

title: church windows
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter.
Cool thoroughly.
Add chopped nuts and marshmallows.
Mix (will be very sticky).
Shape into three rolls.
Roll in coconut and freeze.
Cut into slices while frozen.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook mix, sugar, cornstarch, water and food coloring.
Cool for 2 minutes after cooking.
Add jello.
Bake pie crust.
When cool, place strawberries in crust, then pour ingredients over berries.
Put in refrigerator and let chill.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken.
Save 1 1/2 cup broth.
Melt butter in large pan.
Blend in flour.
Cook on low heat until bubbly, stirring frequently.
Add broth and milk.
Cook until thickened.
Add chicken, peas and carrots, salt, poultry seasoning and pepper. Heat all and pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish with one pie shell on the bottom.
Top with other pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: surprise cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pat into the bottom of a pan (cookie sheet size).
Mix with mixer next 3 ingredients and pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: ham and cheese roll-ups
directions: In a small bowl, combine cheeses and oleo until well blended. Spread 1/4 of mixture on each slice of ham. Roll up from short end; chill for several hours or wrap in Saran Wrap and freeze, if desired. To serve, slice rolls into 1/2 inch slices. Arrange slices on top of Ritz Crackers. If frozen, let stand at room temperature 20 minutes before slicing. Makes about 32 appetizers. Double recipe if needed.

title: harvard carrots
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Blend in vinegar and water.
Cook over medium heat until thick and bubbling, stirring constantly.
Add salt, pepper and carrots.
Heat until carrots are hot.
Stir in butter.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken and stove top
directions: Brown chicken in butter, salt and pepper.
Make Stove Top according to the box.
Layer the stuffing and one can of gravy. Then put the chicken breast, bake for about 30 minutes. Then put the other can of gravy and bake for 30 more minutes or until chicken is done.

title: chicken stock
directions: Rinse and place chicken pieces in cold water and place in large kettle.
Add remaining ingredients and slowly bring to boil. Simmer covered for 2 hours.
Strain broth into large bowl.
Cool to room temperature and refrigerate.
Layer of fat will rise to top and should be removed before reheating the broth.
This can also be frozen.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: baked cheesecake pie
directions: Combine crumbs and butter; press into buttered 8-inch pie plate building up the sides.
To make filling, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually blend in 1/2 cup sugar, lemon juice, vanilla and salt.
Add eggs one at at time, beating well after each.
Pour filling into crumb crust.
Bake in slow oven, 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until set.

title: raisin honey chews
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar, honey and egg; stir in flour, soda, salt and oats; beat well.
Add raisins.
Drop by tablespoonful on greased baking sheets.
Bake above oven center at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until evenly browned.
Let stand on sheets 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove and cool.
Makes about 36 cookies.

title: sugared popcorn
directions: Remove all unpopped kernels from popcorn.
Place popcorn in a 12 x 17-inch baking pan.
Combine brown sugar, butter, syrup and salt in 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook for 5 minutes longer.
Do not stir. Remove from heat.
Stir in soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn, stirring gently.
Bake for 10 minutes longer.
Remove to large bowl.
Cool.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Place biscuits on greased cookie sheet.
Add 1 spoonful of sauce to each biscuit and spread evenly.
Add cooked hamburger to biscuits.
Cover with cheese.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.
(Toppings can vary to your preference.)

title: hummingbird cake(in loving memory of "uncle" bill martin)
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add eggs and oil stirring until dry ingredients are moist.
Do not actually beat with mixer.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, nuts, and bananas.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.
Bake in 3 pans.
When done, cool 10 minutes in pans, then turn on cooling racks until completely cooled.

title: butternut casserole
directions: Mix squash with 1/4 cup butter, 1 tablespoon brown sugar and salt.
Heat 1 1/2 tablespoons butter in skillet.
Add apples and sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Cover and simmer until tender. Spread apples in 2 to 3-quart casserole.
Spoon squash evenly over apples.
Mix cornflakes, pecans, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 2 tablespoons butter.
Sprinkle over squash.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until heated through.

title: quick sweet rolls
directions: Thaw, but do not let rise, 2 loaves frozen bread.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut bread into pieces and place in pan.
Melt oleo and add other ingredients.
Pour over bread.
Let stand, covered, in refrigerator overnight.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Immediately turn out onto foil-lined cookie sheet.

title: chicken hash
directions: In a medium skillet, combine frozen potatoes, chicken gravy, chicken and celery.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: grandma's famous chocolate pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a heavy saucepan; stir well. Set aside.
Combine egg yolks and milk; beat with a wire whisk 1 to 2 minutes or until frothy.
Gradually stir into sugar mixture; add butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly; add vanilla.
Spoon mixture into pastry shell; set aside.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar at high speed with an electric mixer for 1 minute.
Gradually add 1/3 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating until stiff peaks form and sugar dissolves (2 to 4 minutes).
Spread meringue over hot filling, sealing to edge of pastry.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 28 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield:
One 9-inch pie.

title: doug's dump cake
directions: Mix pineapple and pie filling.
Place in 10 x 15-inch pan. Sprinkle cake mix on top and press down.
Sprinkle coconut on cake mix and press down.
Sprinkle nuts on top of coconut and press down.
Divide margarine into bits and sprinkle over top of cake. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: champagne cookies
directions: Cream butter, powdered sugar and egg.
Add dry ingredients. Add fruit and nuts.
Shape dough into oblong rolls (little-finger size).
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Roll in granulated sugar while hot.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Line casserole with dried beef.
Wrap asparagus in 1/2 boned chicken breast, then wrap with a bacon strip.
Place in casserole the salt, pepper, dash of nutmeg, parsley flakes and dash of marjoram.
Mix together the soup and sour cream; pour over chicken breasts.
Place in a 300° oven for 3 hours, or until done.
(Dash of sherry adds to taste in sauce.)

title: brownie mallow bar
directions: Prepare brownie batter according to package directions for fudge-like brownies.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 28 to 30 minutes.
Top with marshmallows.
Bake 3 minutes longer.
(Marshmallows will not be completely melted.)
Cool on a wire rack.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan in the oven.
Watch carefully so it doesn't burn.
Add each ingredient in order, layering the cookies.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican fiesta quiche(serves 6)
directions: In a medium bowl, beat together one of the eggs, water and garlic powder.
Stir in the corn meal until the mixture is crumbly. To form the crust, press the corn meal mixture into the bottom and up the sides of a lightly greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: cranberry pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops.
Pour cranberry sauce over chops.
Cover with soup and bake in a covered dish for 45 minutes in a 350° oven or until chops are tender.

title: marinated strawberries
directions: Hull berries and cut into halves.
Toss berries with marmalade.
Refrigerate 20 minutes.

title: omelets
directions: In a small frying pan (6 to 8-inch), spray with butter flavored Pam.
Saute mushrooms and green pepper until tender. Remove and set aside.
Re-spray pan.
Over medium heat, cook Egg Beaters, moving cooked egg to center to make omelet.
When eggs are cooked, turn off heat.
Arrange vegetables on 1/2 of omelet and cheese over the vegetables.
Fold in half.
Eat immediately. Calories:
Fat:
0 gram.

title: fresh pork barbecue
directions: Cook picnic shoulder in pressure cooker until it falls off bone.
While shoulder is cooking, simmer remaining ingredients in a deep frying pan.
When meat is done, pull or cut in shredded pieces and put into sauce.
Continue to simmer for approximately 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve on buns, if desired.

title: quick stew
directions: Brown the meat slightly in the oil.
Add the onions, carrots, potatoes, peas, seasoning and water.
Bring the mixture to a boil and allow to simmer for a few minutes.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter in a heavy saucepan.
Blend in flour until smooth. Add milk gradually; stir until thick.
Add other ingredients, stirring constantly.

title: egg and sausage strata
directions: Line a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with bread cubes.
Set aside.
In a skillet, brown sausage with the onion and green pepper.
Drain.
Stir in pimientos.
Sprinkle over bread.
In bowl, beat eggs, milk, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, salt, pepper and oregano.
Pour over sausage mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer or until knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Let stand for 10 minutes.

title: orange jello delight
directions: Combine Jell-O with 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add 1 1/2 cups cold water.
Chill until thick.
Add, stirring well, the oranges and 1 cup of Cool Whip.
Chill 3 hours in Jell-O mold.
Especially well received by young family members.

title: split open biscuits for two
directions: Mix flour,
salt,
baking powder and oil.
Add milk and stir. Put on
floured
board
and
knead.
Roll
out to about 1/4-inch thickness.
On
one-half, cover with soft butter (not melted). Bring other
half
of
dough over to cover.
Cut out with biscuit cutter.
Put
in preheated pan with enough oil to dip both sides of
biscuit.
Bake in a 350° oven until golden brown.
Grated cheese,
cut
up sausage, bacon, ham, chicken, etc., may be used for
different
fillings, also cinnamon and sugar mixture or fruits or jams.
Always use with butter.

title: soft ginger cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and molasses.
Then add the rest of the ingredients.
Roll out dough and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake on greased cookie sheets 375 for 10-12 minutes.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve lime jello in the hot water. Add the pineapple juice. When slightly thickened, whip and add all other ingredients.

title: fried chicken
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a clean, plastic bag.
Dip chicken in milk.
Drop each piece in the plastic bag and shake to coat thoroughly.
Fry in hot fat, 1 inch deep, until golden brown and tender, about 25 minutes.

title: skillet fried pizza
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder and water; flatten dough by hand.
Lay on top of pepperoni in hot 9-inch skillet.
Fry until brown on both sides.
Add pizza sauce and toppings.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Allow cream cheese and butter to reach room temperature and mix together well.
Add 3 cups sugar and mix until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Add flour and salt.
Beat mixture for 3 minutes.
Add flavoring of choice and beat for 2 more minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan and place in a cool oven. Turn oven to 300 - 325 degrees and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter and cheese in saucepan.
Add milk and soup and bring to a boil.
In a casserole dish, add rice and broccoli and pour over cheese mixture.
Stir until moist and bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until golden.

title: sausage and cheese biscuits
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Mix sausage, cheese and dry Bisquick.
Add enough water to make dough that will bounce back slightly to touch.
Press dough to about 1 inch thick; cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 375° until light brown.
Serve warm.

title: zucchini bread
directions: *May substitute 1 cup of apples, finely shredded, in place of zucchini.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, eggs, sour cream and oil; pour 1/2 of batter into bottom of cake pan.
Sprinkle enough brown sugar to cover the batter.
Sprinkle cinnamon to cover brown sugar.
Cover with pecans.
Pour remaining batter on top of the pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Take enough confectioners sugar to cover cake.
Add milk until thin enough to spread.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown the bacon, ground beef and onion.
Add the beans.
Mix together the balance of ingredients and add to meat and beans. Simmer together for approximately 1 hour.

title: chili casserole
directions: Cook ground beef, onions and green peppers; drain.
Mix Hamburger Helper and sauce.
Mix water, corn and tomatoes in 2-quart baking dish.
Bake 40 minutes.
Stir and sprinkle corn chips on top to serve.

title: sawdust salad
directions: In oblong dish, mix lemon and orange Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water.
Add cold water.
Add marshmallows, bananas, pineapple and nuts; allow to set.
Mix pineapple juice, flour, sugar and egg; cook until thick (can cook in microwave).
Cool and spread on Jell-O mixture.
Mix the Dream Whip.
Beat in the cream cheese.
Spread on mixture.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.

title: sweet pea salad
directions: Mix peas, egg and mayonnaise.
Add ham, bell pepper and green onion.
Add salt to taste.

title: batter bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix all other ingredients. Refrigerate until used.
May be kept several days.
Cook in greased muffin pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: macaroni and tuna casserole
directions: Mix first three ingredients well and pour into large baking dish.
Combine butter and crackers, and spread over macaroni mixture.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
Beat butter, sugars, vanilla and eggs until light and fluffy.
Blend in flour mixture.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop from teaspoon, 2 inches apart, onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes, until golden brown.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: the "mushroom" salad
directions: Cook spinach as directed.
Drain and add salad dressing. Divide onto four salad plates.
Hard-boil four eggs.
Peel and slice off top and bottom so egg will sit upright.
Place one on each salad plate.
(Dice the cut off egg white ends.)
Slice both tomatoes in halves and put each half on top of an egg, flat side down, so it looks like a mushroom cap.
Moisten the cap with a little oil and sprinkle the diced egg white on top.
Makes four servings.

title: chicken gourmet dish
directions: Put chicken breasts in frying pan.
Add 1 bottle Zesty Italian dressing.
Put on medium heat; cover and cook for 45 minutes, then serve.

title: potato
directions: Mix and bake in casserole dish at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: 3-step cherry cheesecake
directions: Mix all ingredients (except cherry pie filling) until well blended.
Pour into graham cracker shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool, then refrigerate for 3 hours.
Spread the cherry pie filling on top and serve!

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Fix potatoes as if you were making mashed potatoes (instant potatoes can be used).

title: pizza dip
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Put in pie plate and spread sauce on top.
The rest of the ingredients are placed on top and baked 1/2 hour at 350°.
After removing from the oven, spread on cracker to be eaten.

title: taco casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Grease an 11 x 7-inch baking dish.

title: grapefruit salad
directions: Bring 1 cup nectar to a boil; add Jell-O and dissolve.
In 1/2 cup nectar, dissolve the plain gelatine, then add to hot Jell-O. Add remaining nectar.
Cool until thickened.
Pour into square glass dish.
Add pineapple and sectioned grapefruit.
Continue to chill until firm, stirring occasionally.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: In large bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk until smooth.
Stir in ReaLemon and vanilla.
Pour into prepared crust; chill for 3 hours, or until set.
Top with strawberries and desired amount of glaze.
Refrigerate leftovers. (Cool Whip instead of glaze is very good.)

title: cool whip pie
directions: Combine yogurt, strawberries and Cool Whip and put in pie crust.
Freeze for four hours.
Remove from freezer 1/2 hour before serving.

title: polly's creamy frosting
directions: Beat everything together.
Spread on cake.
This makes enough frosting for a layer cake, cupcakes or a 13 x 9-inch cake.

title: baked apple dumplings
directions: Unroll crescents. Peel and thinly slice apples. Place a few apple slices on each roll. Place on greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Melt butter and mix with 1 cup sugar and spices. Spoon over each roll. Pour soda evenly over rolls. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
(If using a glass baking dish, preheat to 325°.)
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, melt margarine.
Make sure entire bottom of pan is coated with margarine.
Evenly layer next 4 ingredients in order given.
Drizzle top of cookie bars with sweetened condensed milk.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool.
Cut into bars.

title: dietetic apple cake
directions: Combine raisins, water and 1 packet sweetener in small saucepan; simmer over medium heat until all water is absorbed.
In a large bowl, combine oil, apple, applesauce, eggs, prunes, cinnamon, allspice, vanilla and 8 packets sweetener; mix well.
In small bowl, combine baking powder, salt and flour.
Add flour mixture to batter; mix well.
Pour batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake is light brown.
Yields 20 servings.
Each serving contains 153 calories (37% from fat).

title: no calorie soup
directions: In a large pot, mix all ingredients.
Let simmer for 3 hours. Good hot or cold.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix cooked chicken, peas, carrots and soup in baking dish. Cover and bake for 20 minutes in 375° oven.
Remove from oven and place biscuit dough on top.
Leave lid off and bake until biscuits are brown.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix
first
ingredients
in oblong dish.
Crush Ritz crackers; mix in margarine.
Spread on top of Veg-All mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: potato yeast rolls
directions: Add 2 tablespoons sugar to potato water and stir.
Dissolve yeast in the potato water.
Blend together sugar, shortening, salt and eggs.
Add the yeast mixture and beat in potatoes.
Add the flour a half at a time.
Turn this sticky dough onto a floured cloth or counter.
Knead in enough flour to make dough elastic. Let rise until double in size.
Make into rolls.
Let rise in a warm place.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: lee's salad(christmas salad)
directions: Use juice from the pineapple and water to make 2 cups liquid. Heat Jell-O and liquid in saucepan and add the marshmallows until dissolved.
Cool until starts to set.
Add the Miracle Whip salad dressing to the cream cheese.
Add the crushed pineapple to cheese and Miracle Whip mixture and fold in the whipped cream.
(I use a can of evaporated milk chilled in refrigerator and whipped.)
Mix in with cooled Jell-O and pour in oblong cake pan.
Allow to set firmly.

title: ohio oven fried chicken
directions: Salt chicken.
Dip in eggs.
Roll in cracker crumbs.
Place in a buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender, turning chicken every 15 minutes.

title: irrestible brownies
directions: In a 2 1/2 to 3 quart saucepan, over low heat, melt butter. Remove from heat.
Add sugar, flour, cocoa, baking powder, salt, eggs and vanilla.
Stir with spoon until blended and smooth. Stir in 1 1/2 cups of chips and nuts.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350°.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup chips on top.
Before baking, cool and cut into 2-inch squares.

title: rice-cheese-zucchini casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions. Quickly steam zucchini until barely tender.
Set aside.
In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, place cooked rice.
Mix in chiles and sprinkle on 1/2 of cheese. Arrange zucchini over cheese.
Add tomato slices, sprinkle with salt.
Combine sour cream, oregano, garlic salt, green pepper and onion.
Spoon over tomato.
Scatter remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: betty's fruit dip
directions: In small bowl, combine milk, pudding and orange concentrate. Beat 1 minute.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
When mixed well, store in covered container overnight.
Serve with any fresh fruit. Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: sweet bread pudding
directions: Break bread in cubes in greased pan or dish, 15 x 10-inch. Sprinkle with raisins and coconut.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and salt together.
Mix milk and water; heat.
Add melted butter.
Combine sugar mixture, milk and egg; mix well.
Pour over bread; allow to stand 1/2 hour before baking.
Bake in 325° oven 1 1/2 hours or until done.
While in oven, it will rise, but don't worry, it will go down.

title: bertha's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar and syrup; mix well.
Add rest of ingredients and mix.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake 5 minutes at 450°, then cut oven down to 300°.
Bake until brown.

title: sara's cookie whip
directions: In a 2-quart bowl, spoon Cool Whip into bowl to make one small layer. Dip one cookie into milk and place onto Cool Whip layer. Repeat until cookies cover Cool Whip layer. Repeat layering Cool Whip and cookies, ending with layer of Cool Whip on top. Sprinkle top with crushed cookies.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix together. Pour into 2 uncooked regular pie shells. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with hot water, then cold.
Chill and fold in fruit.

title: healthy baked fish
directions: Place frozen fish (unthawed) on a broiler pan.
Spread mayonnaise on top to completely cover fish.
Season to taste. Bake 30 minutes or until fish flakes in a 350° preheated oven. Yield: 4 servings.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put coconut and pecans in bottom of pan.
Make cake according to package directions.
Pour over coconut and pecans.
In separate bowl, mix oleo, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spoon over cake.
This sinks into cake.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: lo-cal cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add skim milk powder and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 45 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet and dust with cinnamon.
Makes 2 dozen, 32 calories each.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and beat. Sift flour, cocoa and soda together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning with flour.
Mix well, then add boiling water.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes or test with a toothpick for doneness.

title: chocolate sundae cake
directions: Prepare cake mix, using package directions.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Make deep indentations in hot cake, using end of wooden spoon.
Warm hot fudge and caramel sauces.
Pour hot fudge on top of cake, then pour caramel sauce over top of cake.
Chill until serving time. Spread with whipped topping and sprinkle with pecans.
Cut into squares.
Yields 20 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Brown the ground beef and combine with the taco mix.
Refrigerate until cool.
Add the dressing and top with the Doritos. Serves 12 to 15.

title: roast and relaxation
directions: You will also need a large (14 x 20-inch) Reynolds oven cooking bag.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Combine blueberries, sugar and cinnamon.
Pour into dish.
Mix remaining ingredients until blended; drop spoonfuls onto fruit. Bake 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and sour milk. Mix together dry ingredients and add alternately with bananas.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Dip one side of chicken in butter. Remove from pan.
Stir rice in butter.
Stir in soups; rinse cans with one can of water and add to mixture.
Stir well.
(Soups, water and rice can be mixed in a bowl and poured over butter.) Place chicken on top of mixture, buttered side up.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, using a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: squash muffins
directions: Beat egg.
Add milk, squash and oleo.
Sift dry ingredients and add to the squash mixture.
Put in muffin tin.
Bake at 400° about 20 minutes.

title: homemade white castles
directions: Brown beef and drain off grease; add dry onion soup and cream of mushroom soup.
Mix in cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.

title: saffron-roasted potato and fennel salad
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine first 3 ingredients in medium bowl.
Mix in 1/2 cup oil. Season with salt and pepper.
Transfer mixture to baking pan. Cover and bake 15 minutes.
Uncover, stir potatoes and bake until tender, about 20 minutes more. Transfer potato mixture to bowl and cool.

title: trammel's toffee
directions: Line a large jelly roll pan with foil.
Melt 1/2 stick butter and pour over foil.
Put saltines over butter.
Melt 2 sticks of butter in boiler, then add sugar.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally, over medium heat.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and let cool for a minute.
Add condensed milk, then pour over crackers.
Put in 425° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
It will darken and get bubbly.
Remove from oven and scatter morsels evenly over top.
When morsels are shiny, carefully spread over mixture with the back of a spoon.
Let cool and cut into small bite size pieces.

title: mexican squash
directions: Boil squash with onion and salt until slightly crunchy. Drain well. Put in bottom of greased casserole. Mix in corn. Add green chilies. Cover with Cheez Whiz or cubed Velveeta cheese. Top with bread crumbs or a can of fried onion rings. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: garlic-lemon chicken breasts(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Wash chicken breasts and pat dry. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Saute garlic over medium heat. Add chicken breasts and brown for 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
Pour 1/4 lemon juice over the chicken and cook for 1 minute.
Turn chicken breasts and add remaining lemon juice and white wine.
Cover and cook over medium-low heat until done (approximately 15 to 20 minutes). Serve with wild rice.

title: low-fat hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, white sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa in a bowl.
Blend in milk and Butter Buds.
Stir in Grape-Nuts cereal.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch square pan sprayed with non-fat cooking spray.

title: spiced apple rings
directions: Cook into syrup.
Drop enough apples to fill jar.
Cook until tender.
Pack in jars.
Add hot syrup to 1/2 inch from top.
Seal. Makes enough syrup for six pints.

title: sweet-sour cabbage slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, onion and celery salt.
Blend together sugar, vinegar, salt, pepper and cream.
Pour over cabbage and toss.

title: neiman-marcus bars
directions: Grease and flour a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Mix cake mix, eggs and butter.
Pat in bottom of pan.
Break pecans over top.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla, salt and sugar.
Add eggs. Mix well.
Pour over top and bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Refrigerate.

title: 10 minute peanut brittle
directions: Combine corn syrup and sugar in microwave-safe bowl.
Blend well.
Cook on High for 4 minutes.
Add salt and nuts; cook on High for another 4 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla; cook 1 1/2 minutes. Add baking soda until light and foamy.
Pour onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Cool completely and break.

title: cheeseburger quiche
directions: Brown ground beef with onions, salt and pepper. In a separate med. size bowl beat eggs. Add milk, cheese and browned ground beef to eggs. Stir to coat evenly. Pour into deep dish pie crust. Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: dark applesauce fruit cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat after each addition.
Add raisins and nuts to a small portion of the flour.
Sift remaining flour together with soda, salt and spices.
Add dry ingredients with vanilla, candied fruit, applesauce and crushed pineapple.
Beat well.
Fold in raisins and nuts; beat well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Top with cherries.
Bake for 2 hours at 325°.

title: 2nd buttermilk roll recipe
directions: Mix buttermilk, sugar, salt and shortening. Crumble yeast into mixture. Stir well. Mix in 2 1/2 cups flour or enough to make a dough that handles easily. Turn out on floured surface and let rest 10 minutes. Knead well for 3 to 5 minutes. Shape into rolls. Roll in butter (melted). Put in pan and let rise 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until brown. Makes 15 rolls.

title: dear abby pecan pie
directions: Mix well; pour into unbaked pie shell, deep dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate easter eggs
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream peanut butter and butter until well mixed. Fold in coconut, nuts and 1 cup sugar; mix well. Sprinkle some of the remaining sugar on a board. Turn peanut butter mixture onto board; knead in enough of the remaining sugar until mixture holds its shape when formed. Shape into small egg-shaped pieces. Cover and chill for 1 hour.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Brown onions and pepper.
Add rest and heat until cheese melts.

title: quick peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well.
Spoon on a cookie sheet.
Press down with fork. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: raisin bread
directions: Scald milk; put raisins in milk and allow to cool.
Sift flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add milk, raisins and egg to flour mixture.
Stir quickly.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Sprinkle top with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and mayonnaise.
Add crushed pineapple, cherries, pecans and sugar and mix well.
Keep in freezer.

title: elegant cheese squares
directions: Combine crumbs and butter and press firmly to cover bottom and sides of 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken and vermicelli
directions: Brown mushrooms 10 minutes in butter; add chicken (boiled), sour cream and cream of mushroom soup.
Let set for 10 minutes; add cooked vermicelli and sprinkle Parmesan on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly hot.

title: apple brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir well.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
When cool, sprinkle powdered sugar over top with sifter, then serve.

title: roux with no fat
directions: In heavy skillet or pot at medium-low heat put flour in pan. Do not spray or add any oil.
(The reason I use so much flour is so I can store some for later use.)
Stir occasionally until brown.
This will take about 35 to 45 minutes.
Use amount needed according to recipe calling for roux.
Example:
Flour to be browned for gravy, add dehydrated onions (because they are browned without oil or fat).

title: chili
directions: Saute onion, green pepper, mushrooms and garlic in water until tender.
Add ground meat and continue to cook on medium heat until browned.
Add tomatoes and spices.
Simmer on low heat for 1 hour. Add beans and heat thoroughly.
Use Tabasco to add as much zip as you and your family like.

title: eggs, ham and cheese casserole(serves 15)
directions: Place in bottom of buttered 9 x 15-inch pan the bread, then put the ham on top of the bread and then put the cheese on top of the ham.
Mix together the eggs, milk and salt.
Pour over top of bread, ham and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Just before baking, drizzle 1/3 cup melted margarine over the top.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: drumstick torte
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pat into a 9 x 13-inch glass or metal dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: old fashioned sugar cream pie
directions: Mix in blender and pour into unbaked deep dish pie shell. Sprinkle top of pie with cinnamon and dot with butter before baking.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Turn oven down to 300° and finish baking for another 30 minutes or until set.

title: white cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into a ball.
Put in fridge for about an hour.
Pinch off small pieces and roll into balls. Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Mix well and sprinkle 1 box Jiffy cake mix (yellow or white) over this and dot with butter.
Pour 1 cup water over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cubed steaks parmesan
directions: Beat together the egg, pepper and water.
Combine cracker crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Dip steaks in egg mixture, then in crumbs.
In frying pan, brown steaks in 2 tablespoons oil.
Remove steaks.
Add tomato sauce.
Replace steaks in pan.
Do not let tomato sauce on top of steaks.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes. The last couple of minutes, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese on top of meat.
Replace cover.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine meat, onion, egg and oatmeal.
Form into small balls. Brown in small amount of oil.
Combine jelly and sauce in a saucepan.
Heat and simmer until it thickens.
Serve over meatballs and rice.

title: fried ice cream
directions: Make ice cream snowballs (amount your choice) and freeze uncovered on wax paper for 1 hour.
Beat up egg whites until frothy with a fork.
In another bowl crush nuts.
Dip snowballs into egg, then nuts, then egg, then nuts.
Freeze at least 5 hours.
Deep fry in 380° oil for 10 seconds.
Drain on a paper towel.
Place in a serving bowl and drizzle with honey and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Yummy!!!

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix vegetables in a bowl.
Blend sugar, vinegar and oil.
Pour over vegetables.
Mix and chill at least 2 hours.
Good with bean supper.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients.
Shape into 2 loaves in shallow baking pan.
Spread with catsup or your favorite barbecue sauce.
Bake 1 hour until done.

title: jello salad
directions: Bring to boil the Jell-O and pineapple.
Mix in Cool Whip and buttermilk.
Refrigerate until set and serve.
Good diet food.

title: spiced tea(instant)
directions: Mix together and store in sealed container. Place 1 or 2 tablespoons mixture in cup.
Add boiling water.

title: my potato salad
directions: Put mayonnaise in large mixing bowl; peel potatoes while hot and mash into mayonnaise.
Add all other ingredients and mix well. If salad is too dry, add 2 tablespoons white vinegar and 1 teaspoon sugar with small amount of water.

title: black bean soup
directions: Mix Campbell's black bean soup and water until smooth. Add beans, ground beef and salsa.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve with sour cream, grated cheese and tortilla chips.

title: no fry sunshine doughnuts
directions: Combine milk, shortening and salt.
Cool.
Dissolve yeast in warm potato water.
Add mashed potatoes and dissolved yeast to milk mixture.
Blend eggs, allspice and cornstarch, then add flour, blending constantly.
Cover with moist dishtowel and let rise.
Place dough on floured board and knead.
Roll out dough to 1/2-inch thickness and cut with doughnut cutter.
Place on buttered large cookie sheet and let rise.
Bake at 425° until browned.
May brush with butter and sprinkle with sugar.

title: chopped hot dogs
directions: Combine all ingredients except buns, in a bowl together. Place on hot dog buns.
Wrap in aluminum foil and freeze.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
No need to defrost first.

title: creamy chicken enchiladas
directions: Stir chicken, green pepper, 1/2 cup picante sauce and cream cheese in saucepan over low heat until smooth.
Spoon 1/3 cup chicken mixture into each tortilla.
Roll up.
Place, seam side down, in lightly greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Stir cheese spread and milk in saucepan over low heat until smooth.
Pour sauce over tortillas; cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Pour remaining picante sauce over tortillas.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: lemon bread
directions: In medium bowl, with electric mixer, cream 1 cup sugar with the shortening.
Add lemon rind and beat in eggs.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together; add alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in nuts.

Pour into greased 9 x 5 x3-inch loaf pan and bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. In small saucepan, heat 1/4 cup sugar in lemon juice, stirring until dissolved, and pour over hot bread.
Allow to cool in pan.

title: peach glazed corned beef
directions: Place corned beef in heavy saucepan or Dutch oven.
Add water to cover.
Add bay leaf; cover and simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours, or until meat is tender.
Remove from heat.
Cool meat in cooking liquid.
Remove meat; slice across the grain.
Arrange slices, overlapping, in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Drain peaches, reserving 1/4 cup syrup.
Arrange peaches around meat.
Combine reserved syrup and remaining ingredients; pour over meat.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, basting occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken tostadas
directions: Mix chopped onion with chopped tomato and set aside.
Skin and bone cooked chicken and shred meat.
Store, covered, in refrigerator until needed.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Brown chicken and lay in baking dish.
Brown garlic and mushrooms in butter.
Combine vegetables with soups and milk. Mix and pour over fried chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Mix cookies and margarine.
Press into a 10-inch pie pan.
Mix milk and Marshmallow Creme well with mixer.
Add coloring and flavoring.
Fold whipped cream into mixture.
Pour over cookie crust.

title: chocolate bundt cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° in a Bundt pan for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: pork chops with bread dressing
directions: Brown chops in margarine.
Spoon bread dressing on top of chops (in baking pan). Mix soup and water until smooth.
Pour over chops and dressing.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake for an additional 30 minutes.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Soak the raisins in the hot water overnight.
Add flour and raisins with the water alternately.
Bake in 4 cans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: heavenly hamburger
directions: Brown meat in butter.
Add garlic, salt, pepper, sugar and tomato sauce.
Cover and cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Blend scallions, sour cream and cream cheese in blender or processor.
Cook noodles.

title: 3-bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and bacon with onion. Mix in all 3 different beans with the ketchup and the 2 sugars.
Bake in small roaster or casserole dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: okra-bacon casserole
directions: Slice okra into thin rounds.
In a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole, arrange okra, tomatoes, onion and green pepper in layers.
Season each layer with salt and pepper sauce to taste. Lay bacon over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: double chocolate almond biscotti
directions: Beat butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Gradually beat in dry ingredients.
Stir in almonds and chocolate chips. Shape dough into 2 logs (1 1/2 x 15-inches).
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes; cool.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Put on baking sheet, cut side down.
Bake an additional 30 to 40 minutes or until dried.

title: bananas foster
directions: Mix butter and brown sugar in a saute pan.
Cook over medium heat until caramelized.
Cut bananas in quarters.
Add and cook until tender.
Add cinnamon and banana liqueur; stir.
Put in a heat resistent serving bowl.

title: nonfat creamy sauce
directions: Combine ingredients and heat gently.
Overheating causes curdling.
This sauce can be used over pasta, vegetables, meats or seafood.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. In large bowl with fork, mix flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
With 2 knives cut into shortening until it resembles coarse crumbs. Stir in bananas and eggs.
Bake 55 minutes to 1 hour. Cool on rack 10 minutes.

title: magic lemon pie
directions: Beat eggs; add milk and lemon juice.
Pour in shell and chill.

title: pecan stuffed squash
directions: Reserve 2/3 cup broth; pour remainder into shallow baking dish. Place squash cut side down in broth. Bake until fork-tender. In medium saucepan over medium-high heat, heat reserved broth and butter until melted; stir in stuffing mix, pecans and raisins. Turn squash over, cut side up; spoon stuffing mixture into squash cavity. Bake 20 minutes more, until squash is done, basting after 10 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: green chilis rice
directions: Mix together the sour cream and chilis and set aside.

Butter a 1 1/2 qt. casserole dish. Put half the rice in the bottom and spread with half the sour cream mixture. Top with half the cheese and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Repeat these layers a second time. Cover and bake for 25 minutes at 375°f. 190°c. gas mark 5.

title: homemade chicken pot pies
directions: Bake 50 minutes at 325°.

title: coquille st. jacques
directions: Wash scallops in cold water.
Bring enough water (salted) to a boil to cover scallops.
Drop scallops into boiling water, lower heat and simmer 3 minutes (save water).
Chop finely shallots and parsley; combine with sliced mushrooms and fry in 2 tablespoons butter.
Make a sauce by melting 3 tablespoons butter, adding 2 tablespoons flour, then put in the water which the scallops were boiled.
Boil this sauce for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in egg yolk, scallops and the browned shallots, parsley and mushrooms.
Fill scallops shells, cover with a coat of bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Place in preheated oven for about 10 minutes.

title: sweet potato fluff
directions: Beat potatoes, margarine, sugar, eggs, milk, orange juice and rind with electric mixer until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake in preheated oven (350°) for 45 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into well-greased pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn chip taco dip
directions: Spread cream cheese over bottom of 10-inch pie plate. Sprinkle tomato, onion and green pepper evenly on top of cream cheese.
Spread half bottle of chili sauce over vegetables. Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese on top.
Microwave on High until cheese melts or place under broiler until cheese is melted.
Scoop up dip with corn chips.

title: clams casino
directions: Cook spinach and drain.
Drain clams and add sour cream, spinach and seasoning.
Add 1 cup of the toasted bread crumbs and 1/2 of the clam juice you saved into mixture.
Stir well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: grandmom schuler's german peach cake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt, sugar, margarine and milk to make a sweet dough. Grease cookie sheets or baking pans with margarine. Spread dough 1/4 to 1/2-inch thin across pan (dip fingers in milk to help spread dough and keep it from sticking to fingers). Make rows of fruit, covering all of the pan. Sprinkle with a good amount of cinnamon and sugar, then add dots of butter all around the cake. Bake at 375° approximately 1/2 hour or until you can lift up the edge of the dough.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar before serving.
(Wonderful in the summer!)

title: salmon-corn casserole
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Saute onion in 2 tablespoons butter. Combine with other ingredients using 1 cup crumbs.
Put in casserole and cover with 1/4 cup crumbs and dot with 1 tablespoon butter.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook, cool, drain and mash squash.
Saute onion and pepper. Mix together squash, onion, pepper, and rice.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When nearly done sprinkle rolled crackers and cheese on top.
Cook until the cheese is melted.

title: one step lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large skillet brown ground beef; drain. Stir in spaghetti sauce, water, basil and oregano.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
In small bowl combine cottage cheese and egg.

title: sour cream fudge
directions: Butter an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
In a heavy 3-quart saucepan, cook over moderate heat stirring constantly the sugar, sour cream, corn syrup and butter until mixture boils.
Cover and cook 1 minute.
Remove cover.

Without stirring, continue cooking until the temperature on a candy thermometer reaches 236° or a small amount of mixture when dropped into a large bowl of very cold water forms a soft ball that flattens on removal from the water. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Do not stir.
Cook on wire rack until temperature reaches 176° (about 15 to 20 minutes).

title: toffee cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk; mix thoroughly.
Add flour and cinnamon.
Blend lightly but thoroughly.
Spread even layer over surface of a 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Work with palms of hand to smooth surface.
Beat egg white slightly; spread on top to completely cover.
Sprinkle pecans over all, pressing into dough.
Bake at 275° over 1 hour.
Cut while hot into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Break apart.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: tropical gingerbread(cake)
directions: Melt shortening in 3 or 4-quart saucepan over low heat. Remove, let cool.
Add sugar and egg; beat well.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Combine molasses and hot water, add alternately with flour to first mixture.
Pour into a greased angel food cake pan 9 x 9-inch.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
You may frost or serve with ice cream or whipped cream.
(If frosting, sprinkle generously with coconut.)

title: helen langford's pepper and onion pickles
directions: Grind in food chopper.
Cover with boiling water.
Drain and cover with weak boiling vinegar.
Drain and add 1 pint vinegar, 1 cup brown sugar and 1 tablespoon salt.
Cook 20 minutes.

title: glazed orange chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken skin side up in 7 x 12-inch metal pan.
Season with salt and pepper.
Combine next 5 ingredients and stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour over chicken. Bake 35 minutes.
Remove chicken from pan.
Stir cornstarch mixture into pan juices and bring to boil over high heat.
Return chicken to baking pan and turn to coat.
Increase oven temperature to 450°.
Bake chicken 10 more minutes.
Serve over rice.
Looks great with a broccoli stalk on the side!

title: homestyle pork
directions: Put in Dutch oven pot 3 or 4 cups of cold water and rinsed sauerkraut.
Add whole cranberries and mushrooms.
Cover with more cold water to 1 inch of cooking pot.
Add pepper.
Cover until boils, then simmer for 3 hours, or until when,
using fork to pierce meat, it falls apart.
Serves 6.

title: laura's meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients well, adding enough water to moisten bread crumbs.
Form into 1 1/2-inch round balls and bake (or pan brown) at 400° for 40 minutes.
Loosen from pan and roll on paper towel to remove any excess fat and add to sauce.

title: cream cheese pineapple biscuits
directions: Press finger in center of each biscuit making deep indentation about 1 3/4-inch wide. Fill indentation with cream cheese. Arrange well-drained crushed pineapple around outside edge of cream cheese.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake as directed on biscuit package.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix the oranges, pineapple, peaches, bananas and apples. Add the pudding, milk, orange juice concentrate and sour cream.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Saute chopped celery, onion and green pepper.
Mash cooked carrots and mix with sauteed vegetables.
Put in buttered baking dish. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together the ingredients. In another bowl, mix 1 large box instant vanilla pudding with the pineapple juice. Stir well. Pour over the fruit. Mix well. Chill.

title: ron's barbecue sauce
directions: In saucepan, mix vinegar, water, sugar, mustard, pepper, salt, cayenne, lemon, onion and butter.
Simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Add catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to a boil. Good on spareribs, broiled chicken, short ribs, lamb chops, etc. or use as a baster when broiling chicken, roasting lamb or spareribs or braising short ribs.
Makes approximately 1 3/4 cups.

title: honey chicken
directions: In a bag, shake flour, salt and pepper; add chicken to bag and shake to coat.
Melt 1/2 stick butter in baking dish; roll chicken in butter and place skin down in dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. In saucepan, melt 1/2 stick butter; stir in honey, lemon juice and soy sauce.
Turn chicken over; pour mixture over chicken and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Dissolve pudding in pineapple juice; add pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add nuts, cherries and marshmallows.
Pour in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cool 1 hour before serving.

title: egg custard
directions: Melt butter.
Add milk; heat to scalding (not boil).
Beat the eggs slightly.
Add sugar and vanilla; stir into milk.
Strain into a 9-inch pastry lined pan.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 475° for 10 minutes.
Turn control to 375° and bake 10 minutes longer.
(Before filling crust, brush the crust with unbeaten egg whites.)

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add onion.
Cook and cream potatoes.
Using large casserole dish, hamburger being the first layer, then add next layer of potatoes.
Continue until all is gone.
Cover top with cheese slices.
Bake at 300° until cheese melts.
Recipe may be reduce to half of ingredients called for. Makes a lot.

title: congealed english pea salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pea juice, vinegar, salt, onions, mustard and mayonnaise.
Stir until mixture is smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a quart dish.
Refrigerate until set.

title: fruit delight
directions: If using frozen or canned fruits, be sure to drain very well. Mix fruits together and set aside.
