Mix together cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Fold into fruit; cover and store in fridge.
Will set in about 1 hour.

title: marian's jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add white soda.
Chill until almost set.
Add pineapple and some bananas.
Put in pan and let set.

title: mounds cake
directions: Bake chocolate cake according to directions in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Saute celery, onion and garlic in olive oil.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, water and seasonings.
Cook to boiling.
Make meatballs.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel apples and then slice.
Spread apples in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
In small bowl, combine the rest of the ingredients, then sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Set cream cheese out to soften.
Mix pepper, onions, olives and pimentos in bowl; set aside.
Mix cream cheese and dip mix. Spread on tortillas.
Sprinkle vegetables on each tortilla.
Roll each tortilla up and wrap in plastic wrap to chill overnight. Slice the next day and insert toothpicks.

title: sausage-cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well: cheese, Bisquick and then sausage. Roll into balls about the size of a large marble.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: spicy red cabbage
directions: In a pot, bring the broth to a boil.
Add the onion and garlic and cook, uncovered, over medium heat until soft, about 10 minutes. Add the remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer slowly for 40 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 8.

title: twice-baked sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Pierce the sweet potatoes with a fork and bake until soft to the touch, about 50 minutes or microwave on High, uncovered, for 11 to 13 minutes.
Let the potatoes cool.
Cut the potatoes in half and carefully scoop out the filling. Transfer the filling to a bowl and beat with an electric beater until smooth, adding a tablespoon of milk at a time.
Set aside. Peel and chop the apple and sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon. Microwave in a bowl for 15 seconds or heat in a saucepan for 5 minutes with 1 tablespoon of water to soften slightly.
Fold the apples into the sweet potato and bake for 10 minutes at 425° or microwave for 2 minutes on High.
Yields 4 (1/3 cup) servings.

title: flaky pie crust
directions: Sift
salt
and flour into mixing bowl.
Cut into flour 1/2 of	shortening until cornmeal consistency.	Cut remainder of shortening	until size of peas.
Slightly beat egg and add cold water and vinegar.	Blend together with fork until dough holds together.
Roll out into pies.
Makes 2.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat sugar and oil together.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Batter will be very runny.
May add nuts or raisins.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in greased pan.

title: decadent fudge cake
directions: Cream butter in a large mixing bowl, gradually add sugar beating well at medium speed with electric mixer.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine buttermilk and soda stirring well.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with flour, beginning and ending with flour.
Add 2 bars melted chocolate, chocolate syrup and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in 1 cup mini-morsels.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa, egg yolks and milk.
Cook on top of stove until thick. Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover with meringue.

title: glazed orange angel food cake
directions: Sift together flour and 3/4 cup sugar. In a large bowl, beat egg whites, cream of tartar and salt until frothy. Gradually add remaining sugar, beating until stiff peaks hold. Beat in extracts. Gradually add flour-sugar mixture. Pour into ungreased 10-inch tube pan, folding gently. Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until done. Invert cake to cool. Mix together confectioners sugar, orange juice and orange peel. Use to frost cake.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Place first 6 salad ingredients in a large bowl in order they are listed.
Then spread a layer of mayonnaise over peas. Sprinkle sugar over mayonnaise and then add cheese and bacon bits.
Half of this recipe still serves a lot!

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Sift together in bowl the flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and 2 tablespoons of cocoa.
Stir in milk and melted butter. Blend in chopped nuts.
Spread in a 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with mixture of brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Pour hot water over everything.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.
May be doubled for a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Butter sides and bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Sprinkle with crumbs; shake to coat.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Beat in remaining ingredients and pour into pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°, until firm around edges and soft in center.
Turn off oven. Open door and let cake cool 30 minutes in oven.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Top of cake will crack when cooling.

title: refreshing punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Scoop orange or lemon sherbet into punch.
Very good.
Make right before serving.

title: cooked ice cream
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in cold milk.
Add all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Be careful not to scorch milk mixture.
Cool and freeze according to freezer instructions.

title: creamed cabbage
directions: Boil in salted water and drain. Line baking dish with bacon strips. Add a layer of cabbage, then a layer of grated cheese.
In a saucepan, melt butter. Add the flour, then milk, stirring constantly until it boils slightly and thickens.
Pour mixture on top of cabbage/cheese layers.
Sprinkle with black pepper and paprika. Bake in 350° oven until slightly browned.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar, a little at a time and beat until no longer grainy.
Add salt.
Mix.
Fold in pecans and chocolate chips.

title: egg salad
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Yields 2 cups sandwich filling.

title: yellow butter cake
directions: Cream butter. Add sugar gradually, beating well.
Add well beaten egg yolks and vanilla.
Beat again.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk to yolk-sugar mix.

title: summer dessert
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours or overnight. Any type fresh fruit may be used. Frozen or canned fruit not recommended.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Mix cream cheese, dressing mix and mayo together.
Spread on slices of bread.
Top with 1 cucumber slice.
Sprinkle lightly with garlic salt.

title: persimmon pudding(heritage recipe)
directions: Mix the first 9 ingredients together in order and bake.
Bake 350 degrees for 40 minutes.
Just prior to taking out of oven; mix brown sugar, flour, water and vanilla in a saucepan.
Cook until thick.
Pour over pudding and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: banana squares
directions: In a small mixing bowl beat egg whites until soft peaks form; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl cream shortening and sugar. Beat in egg yolks; mix well.
Add bananas.
Combine flour and baking soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Fold in egg whites.
Fold in nuts if desired.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.
If desired, garnish with a dollop of whipped cream and a few banana slices.
Yield:
12 to 16 servings.

title: lo-cal potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes; cool.
Mix together other ingredients and add to potatoes and stir.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Cook string beans.
Layer them with sprouts, onion rings, water chestnuts and mushrooms.
Dilute soup with milk and pour over all.
Top with lots of grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 30 minutes or until bubbly and heated through.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400°
for 10 minutes, then at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: kahlua
directions: In saucepan, combine water, instant coffee and sugar.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add brandy, vodka and vanilla.

title: pumpkin-pecan loaves
directions: Combine margarine and sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Blend in pumpkin.
Add combined dry ingredients, mixing just until moistened.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into two greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: applesauce
directions: Place fruit and water in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish. Cover.
Microwave at High for 5 to 9 1/2 minutes, stirring after half the time, until fruit starts to turn transparent.
Stir in sugar.
Let stand, covered, for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir before serving.
Puree, if desired.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix by hand or with electric mixer.
Divide in small portions and freeze.
Makes approximately 25 (9-inch) crust.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans together.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes; cool.
Mix the sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese together; beat until fluffy.
Spread on the cooled crust.
Blend lemon pudding and milk; pour over cheese mixture.
Refrigerate until ready to serve, then spread with more Cool Whip.
May sprinkle a little coconut on top, if you wish.

title: cranberry holiday punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and float fruit slices on top.
This is pretty and not sweet.
It is pretty with an ice ring of cranberries and holly.

title: almond delight
directions: Mix
together
brown sugar, margarine, almonds, coconut and flour.
Put in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or
until
golden
brown,
stirring every few minutes. Cool.
Take less
than 1/2 mixture and set aside.
Put remaining into pan. Beat
together
pudding
and
milk until thick. Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread
on baked layer.
Sprinkle rest of baked mixture on top.
Refrigerate.

title: pastry for single crust pie
directions: Mix flour and salt. Cut in lard.
Sprinkle mixture with water until all is moistened. Form into ball.
Roll dough onto floured surface, fitting a 9-inch pie plate.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all of the above together.

title: stuffing
directions: Cook onion, celery and butter until tender.
Mix other ingredients together. Add celery and onion.
Stir together.
Pour into buttered pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: wine and pepper cream sauce
directions: Melt butter in a skillet.
Add shallots and cook gently 3 minutes.
Add brandy to pan and allow to heat through a few seconds, then flame.
When flames subside, add wine to shallots. Stir in stock and peppercorns and boil rapidly 2 to 3 minutes or until slightly reduce.
Remove from heat and stir in cream and chopped parsley.
Return to medium heat and heat through 2 to 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Garnish with parsley sprigs, if desired.
Makes 3/4 cup.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use greased or paper muffin cups.

title: snowball cake
directions: Mix gelatin into 2 Tbls. cold water, add juice of one lemon, add the crushed pineapple and 1/2 cup of sugar.
Mix together and place in refrigerator for 15 minutes until set.
Beat one pack of dream whip and mix into gelatin mix, add cherries and pecans.
Line mixing bowl with saran wrap.
Crumble cake in lined mixing bowl, placing a layer of cake bits and layer of gelatin mixture. Alternating this step until bowl is full.
Set in refrigerator at least 4 hours and preferably overnight.
Before serving time remove cake from bowl and lift off saran wrap.
Mix one package dream whip and spread on cake, cover dream whip with coconut.
Keep refrigerated.

title: peach cup salad
directions: On a bed of lettuce, arrange 2 peach halves for each serving. Fill centers with mixture made by combining celery, nuts, raisins and apple butter. Garnish with mayonnaise or half mayonnaise and whipped cream.

title: taco salad
directions: Toss all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour dressing over and toss just prior to serving.

title: mexican sausage and rice
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add thinly sliced sausage, pepper and onion.
Cook and stir until vegetables are tender.
Add corn, broth and salsa; bring to a boil.
Stir in rice; cover. Remove from heat.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork. Sprinkle with cheese; cover.
Let stand for 2 to 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Enjoy!

title: "like bailey's" irish cream
directions: Mix together in blender.
Keep in refrigerator for up to 1 month. Stir before serving.

title: corn and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice and mix with other ingredients.
Bake in greased casserole dish.
Top with butter and grated cheese.
Bake at 325° or 350°, depending on oven, for 20 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix real good.
Make little balls.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut meat into small pieces.
Roll pieces in flour and brown in the fat in a heavy pan.
Remove meat.
Add water and scrape up brown bits.
Add salt, pepper, bay leaf, sugar and tomato sauce. Add browned meat.
Cover tightly and cook on low for about 1 1/2 hours.
Add cut-up vegetables; cook about 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serves 6.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Mix salt and cabbage.
Let stand 1 hour.
Squeeze out excess moisture.
Add carrots and green pepper.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Fold together, chill and serve.

title: hototay(soup)
directions: Mix first 12 ingredients together.
Wrap in wonton paper and set aside.
Boil gizzard in chicken broth until tender.
Add shrimp, liver and wonton, lastly, add the vegetables.
Season with salt and m.s.g.
Sprinkle with sesame oil.
Serve piping hot with raw egg.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Peel apples and cut into small squares. Set them to the side. In large bowl, mix the oil, sugar and eggs together and beat well. Add flour and vanilla to mixture gradually. Fold in apples and nuts. Bake in an ungreased bundt pan at 350° for 70 minutes. Let cool then remove from pan.

title: glazed chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine shortening, catsup, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce in pan.
Bring to boil; remove from heat. Arrange chicken pieces in baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour sauce over chicken pieces.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Turn chicken pieces several times during baking.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and soda.
Add pineapple and eggs.
Beat well and pour into greased sheet cake pan.
On top, add brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Pour icing over cake immediately.

title: broiled grapefruit
directions: Cut grapefruit in half.
Cut around each section and remove center.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon sugar on each half.
Place cherry in center.
Broil until sugar melts and edges turn slightly brown. Serve immediately.

title: homemade mayonnaise
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add egg yolks and blend.
Add vinegar; mix well with mixer on medium speed.
Add salad oil, 1 teaspoon at a time, beating with rotary or electric beater, until 1/4 cup has been added.
Add remaining oil in increasing amounts, alternating last 1/2 cup with lemon juice.
Beat in hot water; this takes away oily appearance.
Makes 2 cups.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Combine ingredients and mix with shredded cabbage.
This recipe came from the Rev. Harold King's mother-in-law.

title: chicken breast with rice
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Dip one side of chicken in butter.
Remove from pan; stir rice into butter in pan. Stir in undiluted soups; rinse cans with 1 can water.
Add to rice mixture.
Stir; lay breasts over mixture (butter side up) so they cover mixture.
Do not press down.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: crab fondue
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together; heat through until cheese melts.
Cut French bread into cubes and dip.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix peanut butter and sugar, then stir in remaining ingredients.
Shape in 1-inch balls and put on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with fork to flatten slightly.
Bake in moderate 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: skillet corn
directions: Slice off one pint of kernels from fresh roasting ears of sweet corn.
Place in a skillet with 1/2 cup shortening, sugar, salt and pepper.
Fry over low heat until done (about 8 to 10 minutes).

title: baked pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 3 tablespoons juice.
Combine sugar, flour and stir into 3 tablespoons flour.
Mix well.
Pour over pineapple, add cheese and flour mixture.
Mix well and pour into greased casserole.
Combine crumbs with melted butter and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until crumbs are golden.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: herb marinated tenderloin
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Marinate the tenderloin for at least 24 hours, turning occasionally.
Bake in marinade at 425° for 45 minutes for rare.
For medium well, bake at 425° for 45 minutes and reduce heat to 325° for 45 minutes.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt peanut butter and butterscotch chips together.
Mix in cereal or noodles and chocolate until all covered.
Spoon onto cookie sheet with small spoon.
Cool.

title: potica cake
directions: Melt and cool oleo and milk.
Mix yeast in water.
Sift flour, salt and sugar.
Stir egg yolks into milk mixture.
Add this mix to sifted flour mix.
Add the yeast mixture.
Beat well, cover and refrigerate overnight.
This dough will be very sticky.

title: fresh vegetable dip
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Dip vegetables in dip.

title: ham and cheese(appetizers)
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the flour, cornmeal, baking powder and salt.
Cut in the butter until the mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in the ham and cheese.
Combine the milk and mustard. Stir into the mixture.
Quickly mix to a dough.
Add a little extra flour if dough is too sticky.
Pat out onto a lightly floured board, making the dough 1/2-inch thick.
Cut biscuits with a 2-inch cutter or a small glass.
Place on a lightly buttered baking sheet. Bake at 450° for about 12 minutes until golden.
Serve hot from the oven or reheat before serving.
Makes 24 small biscuits.

title: pizzelle
directions: *You may substitute lemon, whiskey, orange, vanilla or any other flavoring.

title: harvard beets
directions: Blend sugar, salt and cornstarch in double boiler.
Stir in vinegar, then cook until smooth and thick, stirring constantly. Add butter, onion and beets.
Heat an additional 20 minutes.

title: carolyn's cupcakes
directions: Melt butter and place in 1-cup measuring cup.
Add eggs, then enough milk to fill cup.
Add vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add liquid ingredients; stir until mixed.
Pour into greased muffin tins lined with cupcake papers.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: white bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add next 5 ingredients to yeast mixture.
Add flour 1/2 cup at a time until soft, pliable dough is formed.
Knead on floured board about 3 minutes.
Let rise until doubled.
Punch down and divide into 3 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° about 30 to 40 minutes.
Brush with melted butter.
Yields 3 large loaves.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Melt lard in boiling water.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Add yeast. Add eggs, sugar and salt.
Add flour.
Put in greased bowl and let stand overnight in the icebox.
Put on greased and floured cookie sheet in small rolls and let raise 2 1/2 hours.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown.

title: caesar salad
directions: Crush garlic into oil.
Let stand several hours.
To 1/2 cup of oil, add mustard, salt, pepper and Worcestershire.
To washed greens, put oil mixture and anchovies.
Break eggs into salad, one at a time.
Add lemon and 2 tablespoons grated cheese.
Toss gently until greens glisten.
Serve at once.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Beat the butter in a large mixer bowl until creamy.
Add 1/3 cup of the sugar a little at a time; beat until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time; continue beating.
Add lemon juice, then flour.
Continue beating, then add milk, lemon rind and vanilla.

title: chili dip
directions: Mix together and cook slowly on low heat until cheese melts.

title: frozen pudding sandwiches
directions: Add milk gradually to peanut butter in a deep bowl, blending until smooth.
Add pudding mix.
Beat slowly with rotary beater or at lowest speed of electric mixer until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Let stand about 5 minutes.
Spread filling about 1/2-inch thick on 12 of the crackers.
Top with remaining crackers, pressing lightly and smoothing around edges with spatula.
Freeze until firm, about 3 hours.
Wrap individual sandwiches for storage.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger; do not drain.
Add taco seasoning.
In a small saucepan, empty chili mix into water.
Bring to a boil for 3 minutes.
Dip tortillas in oil to soften.
Fill with hamburger, onion and cheese.
Roll up; place in baking dish.
Pour chili mixture over all; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until cheese melts at 350°.

title: torta
directions: Beat egg yolks until lemon colored. Add sugar gradually. Add 1 cup melted pork lard. Sift in flour and baking powder. Pour milk and mix well. Spoon into muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake in hot oven (400°). Remove when golden brown. Spread butter on top and sprinkle with sugar.

title: green beans
directions: Add bouillon cubes to rapidly boiling water.
Add green beans, cook 2 to 3 hours, until tender on medium heat.
Cook until all but a small amount of water is gone.
Add margarine and pepper. Stir well and serve.

title: sweet-sour pot roast
directions: Heat shortening in Dutch oven or heavy skillet with tight fitting lid.
Add meat and onions.
Brown, turning often.
Add pepper, cloves, honey, sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Cover tightly.
Simmer slowly over heat or bake in a 300° oven for 3 to 3 1/2 hours, until meat is tender.

title: zucchini pineapple
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil.
Add zucchini and simmer 20 minutes.
Put in hot jars and seal.
Makes 8 to 9 pints.

title: italian roast beef
directions: Brown meat first.
Mix all together in a crock-pot or roaster. Cook until meat can be shredded easily with two forks.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugars; add eggs, butter and flour.
Mix well.
Add vanilla, salt and milk.
Turn into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: green bean bake
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, combine milk, soup, soy sauce and pepper.
Stir well.
Stir in beans and 1/2 of the onions. Cover and bake for 25 minutes at 350°, or until thoroughly heated. Top with remaining onions and bake for 5 more minutes.

title: hamburger with baked beans
directions: In skillet brown 1 medium onion chopped with ground beef. Salt and pepper.
Drain.
In casserole dish mix together pork and beans, molasses, ketchup, dry mustard and Worcestershire sauce. Then add ground beef.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off fat.
Add seasonings and cook slowly 10 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce and spaghetti sauce mix.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook lasagna. Drain and rinse.
Into 8 x 12 x 2-inch dish pour 1/3 of meat sauce. Cover with strips of lasagna, then Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with meat sauce.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: curried chicken cantaloupe salad
directions: Discard seeds from melon and with melon baller, cut out balls. Combine melon balls with chicken, grapes, celery and almonds.
Mix together remaining ingredients and gently fold into chicken mixture.
Fill melon shells.
Serves 2.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together until smooth.
Pour into a greased 9 or 10-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean, about 50 to 55 minutes.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans, thoroughly.
Toss with green pepper, onions and pimento.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables. Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Drain before serving.
Yield 6 to 8 servings.

title: egg and shrimp toasts
directions: Beat eggs with 1 tablespoon water and a pinch of salt.
Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in a pan and lightly brown the bread on one side.
Place on a serving dish with browned side up.
Keep warm. In the same pan, melt remaining butter and cook eggs, stirring gently until set.
Spread the fried bread with the mustard, then spoon the egg mixture on top.
Top with shrimp and serve garnished with tartar sauce.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9 X 13 pan.
In a bowl, mix milk, flour, and sugar to make a batter.
Pour over melted butter.
DO NOT STIR. Spoon in fruit adding a little juice (not a lot).
DO NOT STIR. Bake 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: turkey noodle bake
directions: In a 2-quart casserole stir together soup and milk.
Add turkey, cheese and onion.
Mix well.
Stir in uncooked noodles. Pour in water.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake, covered, in preheated 350°
oven for 50 minutes or until noodles are tender.

title: hamburg and tomato soup casserole
directions: Brown hamburg and put in casserole dish.
Add potatoes, carrots, onions, tomato soup and water; mix well.
Bake, covered, at 375°
for 1 hour, then uncovered for 1/2 hour.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Simmer, covered, onion, carrot, celery, garlic and water for 10 minutes.
Transfer to blender.
Add broccoli, salt, cayenne pepper and macaroni.
Cover and blend on high.
Remove cover and add chicken stock and cream.

title: mexican skillet corn
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from drippings, drain, crumble and set aside.
Add vegetables and chili powder to drippings. Stir, cover and cook over low heat for 15 to 20 minutes or until corn is tender.
(Stir occasionally to keep from sticking.)
Add salt and pepper; mix well.
Pour into serving dish; sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Serve hot.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: apple raisin bran muffins
directions: In a large bowl mix the flour, bran, wheat germ, baking soda and nutmeg.
In a medium bowl combine orange juice, buttermilk or yogurt, egg, molasses, syrup and oil.
Stir into dry ingredients and blend well.
Stir in orange rind, apple, raisins and sunflower seeds.
Spoon mixture into prepared muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Makes 24 muffins.
Bake at 350°.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients.
Cut the ribs into individual pieces.
Marinate for at least 24 hours.
Place ribs in 2 roasting pans at least 13 x 9-inch large.
Add 1/2 of the marinade to each pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Drain off all liquid and fat.
Bake, covered, for an additional 1/2 hour. Serve with dark sauce.

title: lazy lasagna
directions: *If desired, add 1 pound browned ground beef to sauce.

title: paradise pudding
directions: Cut up fine vanilla wafers, cherries and marshmallows.
Whip the cream until well beaten.
Put altogether in the jello (which has been frozen slightly).
Mix well, then put back into refrigerator until serving time.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 stick	margarine in a casserole dish. Wash the rice and place
in
melted margarine. Salt and pepper chicken. Place on rice.
Pour onion soup and cream of chicken soup over chicken. Add 1 can of water. Bake for 1 1/2 hours in a covered dish at 350°.

title: sand tarts
directions: Mix oleo and sugar.
Add flour and nuts.
Roll in little logs (about finger size).
Bake; let cool.
Roll in powdered sugar. Bake in a 350° oven for about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: miss jane's famous carrot cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; stir in eggs, oil, and vanilla; mix well.
Spoon batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350 for 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Spread Cream Cheese Frosting between layers and on top of cake while still warm.

title: pumpkin pie makes own crust
directions: Grease pan lightly.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350°.
Cover pie with pan and bake for another 40 minutes.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: In microwave melt Velveeta cheese and 1 stick of butter in microwave-safe bowl.
Meanwhile, cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain well.
Put cooked broccoli in an oblong baking pan.
Stir Velveeta and cheese until well blended.
Pour over broccoli.
Melt second stick of butter; crush Ritz crackers into the butter.
Stir until well coated.
Sprinkle on top of broccoli and cheese.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bean soup
directions: Place beans in large pot and cover with water; soak overnight. Drain and add 1 quart of water and salt pork.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and cook covered over low heat about 2 hours.
Add onion, celery, ham and 2 additional cups of water.
Cover and cook for 1 hour or until beans are tender.
Add salt, pepper, tomato soup and 1 cup of water if desired; simmer until soup reaches desired consistency.
Taste and season to personal taste.
Add less water if you like thicker soup.

title: mim's peanut brittle
directions: Mix peanuts, sugar and syrup together in a heavy saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook to hard crack (300°). Remove from heat and stir in baking soda.
Stir real fast as this will rise quickly.
Pour onto baking sheet to cool.
Break into pieces when hard.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and eggs; beat well.
Add milk and cook over medium heat.
As it cooks, add margarine and cook until bubbly. Cool and pour into 9-inch baked pie shell.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Shape into 1/2 to 1 teaspoon balls.
Decorate with sprinkles, Kisses, nuts.
(I like anis seed added to dough.)
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat until incorporated.
Bake in 3 greased small loaf pans or 2 large.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until light brown.
Remove from pans at once.
Cool on rack.

title: oreo ice cream cake
directions: Crush oreos; reserve 1/2 cup for top and mix with butter and sugar. Press into a 9 x 13 inch pan. Cut ice cream into slabs and lay on crust. Freeze 1 - 2 hours. Pour a thin layer of hot fudge on the ice cream. Top with cool whip and oreos.

title: apple-scotch cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar 2 minutes.
Add egg and applesauce. Beat well; add combined dry ingredients.
Stir in raisins and nuts, if desired.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: potato balls or cakes
directions: Mix all the ingredients well, except oil.
Drop by teaspoon into the hot oil or pan-fry if making potato cakes.

title: summertime rice salad
directions: Bring water to a boil in saucepan.
Stir in rice.
Cover, remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Add celery, pickle, onion, parsley and mustard.
Mix well, cover and chill about 1 hour.
Add mayonnaise.
Serve on crisp lettuce.
Garnish, if desired, with hard-cooked egg slices or olives.

title: broiled tomato slices
directions: Wash tomatoes; remove stem end.
Cut into thick slices or halves.
Sprinkle each with salt, pepper, sugar, dill weed and dot with butter.
Broil 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: fat-free chocolate mousse
directions: Beat egg whites on high speed until fully whipped (2 minutes). Add Equal, whip again (1 minute).
Add pudding and stir with spoon.
Spoon into 2 parfait glasses.
Garnish with fruit (strawberry, cherry).
Serves 2.
Zero fat grams.

title: ice cream delight
directions: In a heavy skillet on low heat, melt butter.
Add pecans and coconut.
Heat until light brown.
Add brown sugar and stir well. Remove from heat and place half of cooked mixture in 9 x 12-inch Pyrex
baking
dish.
When cool, place ice cream on top and remaining
cooked
mixture on top of ice cream.
Freeze and cut in squares and serve.

title: orange pineapple salad
directions: Combine pineapple, sugar and jello; bring to a boil.
Allow sugar and jello to dissolve.
Cool and add water and buttermilk. Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts.
Pour into an oblong dish.
Chill.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter with mushrooms.
Add sauerkraut; fry for a short time.
(Keep adding a little water so the mixture doesn't dry out.)
Add salt and pepper.
In a casserole dish, add all the ingredients.
Add a little more water.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 or 3/4 hour.
Enjoy!!

title: quick and easy salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Cool slightly.
Pour over ice cream and stir well (use hand mixer to blend thoroughly).
Add fruit cocktail and crushed pineapple including the juice from both. Stir and chill until set.
You can add some chopped pecans to this recipe if you desire.

title: munnie's pot roast
directions: A proper pot roast is a square cut of chuck, rump or round.
A heavy metal or iron pot with grill insert and tight cover is the proper setting for braising the roast.
Brown the meat carefully on all sides; season as you brown.
Slip the grill under the roast and add a small amount of water or tomato juice.
Cover and simmer over low heat, renewing liquid occasionally.
Add vegetables; cover and cook over low heat until meat and vegetables are tender.

title: sparkling fruited pop
directions: Mix concentrated juice and sparkling water in a large container.
Gently stir until combined.
Makes eight 5-ounce servings.

title: black walnut gift loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Mix sugar, shortening and eggs. Beat until light. Add mashed bananas. Stir in sifted dry ingredients, beating smooth.
Add nuts. Pour into pan. Bake 60 to 70 minutes. Cool on rack.

title: california fresh strawberry pie
directions: To moisture-proof your pie crust, brush bottom with beaten egg before baking.
Bake and set aside.
Wash uncapped strawberries. Lay out on lots of paper towels to dry.
Pat lightly and set aside to dry.

title: easter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except for 2 egg yolks, and pour into two 8 or 9-inch pastry lined pie plates.
Cover both pies with top pie crust.
Brush tops with beaten egg yolks.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Brush again with egg yolk while baking.

title: dutch potato soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan over high heat, bring potatoes, water, salt and pepper to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Drain potatoes, reserving broth.
Mash half of potatoes.
Set aside cubed and mashed potatoes and broth.

title: no peek beef stew
directions: In a crock-pot, stir together all ingredients.
Cover and cook for 5 hours on high.
Serve over cooked white rice or noodles.

title: no crust pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except water.
Slowly stir in water.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until a knife inserted into center comes out clean.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Stir boiling water into jello in large bowl for 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in cold water.
Stir in ice cream until smooth.
Pour into serving bowl.
Refrigerate for 3 hours or until firm.
Garnish with Cool Whip, fruit, and nuts. Makes 8 servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook beef, onions and mango together.
Add tomatoes and seasoning.
Add cabbage; cook until crisp.
Cook rice, then blend. Add sour cream and heat; do not boil.
Put in serving dish.
Put cheese on top.
Serve as soon as cheese melts.

title: cranberry fruit nut bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; cut in butter. Combine orange peel, juice and egg. Add to dry ingredients, mixing just to moisten. Fold in cranberries and nuts. Put in greased loaf pan and bake 40 to 60 minutes, depending on size of pan. It took 40 minutes in my long, narrow loaf pan. Cool, wrap and store overnight.

title: jello cake
directions: Bake cake as directed (13 x 9-inch pan).
Mix jello with 1/2 cup hot water.
Pour over cake.
Just before serving, spread container of Cool Whip over top of cake.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Remove cartilage from crab meat and chop.
In a large bowl, mix cream cheese, sour cream, mayonnaise, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and garlic salt until smooth.
Add enough milk to make mixture creamy.
Stir in 2 tablespoons of the grated cheese.
Fold crab meat into cheese mixture.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 325° uncovered until mixture is bubbly and brown on top, about 30 minutes.
Garnish with paprika.
Best served with Ritz crackers!

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg. Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream. Add vanilla and mix. Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheets. Sprinkle with sugar mixture.
(This mixture is just a little sugar and cinnamon mixed together.) Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: poke cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Mix at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool in pan 15 minutes. Dissolve Jell-O as directed.
Poke holes in cake with fork.
Pour warm Jell-O over cake.
Chill 4 hours.
Spread prepared Dream Whip on top.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon and pour over apples. Mix together with hands or spoon. Pour into a 9 x 13 inch baking dish. In a separate bowl combine flour, brown sugar and melted butter; mix together and sprinkle over apples. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: beef and dressing casserole
directions: Put dressing in a bowl with 1 cup hot water.
Cover and let stand (set aside).
Brown hamburger with chopped celery and onion - no salt.
Add cream of chicken soup and put in bottom of a casserole.
Spread dressing on top of meat.
Add 1/2 cup water to cream of celery soup and pour over all.
May add mushrooms to this if desired.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: sweet onion-smothered hamburgers
directions: Place sliced onion in a medium nonstick skillet coated with cooking spray.
Cover and cook over medium heat 10 minutes or until onion is limp and golden, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat to low and add 1/4 cup chili sauce and grape jelly.
Cover and cook 5 minutes or until onion is tender and thoroughly heated.
Combine beef and next 5 ingredients in a bowl; stir well.
Divide mixture into 4 equal portions, shaping each into a 1/2-inch thick patty. Prepare grill or broiler.
Place patties on grill rack or broiler pan coated with cooking spray and cook 4 minutes on each side or until done.
Line the bottom halves of each bun with a lettuce leaf; top with a patty, 1/4 cup onion mixture and top half of bun.

title: danish pastry apple bars
directions: Combine flour and salt and cut in shortening.
Beat egg yolk in measuring cup; add enough milk to make 2/3 cup liquid.
Mix well.
Stir in flour mixture.
On floured surface, roll half of dough.
Measure 17 x 12-inch rectangle.
Sprinkle in corn flakes; top with apples.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on the apples.
Roll dough to 15 x 10-inch rectangle; place over apples and seal.
Cut slits.
Beat egg white until frothy; brush on crust.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Drizzle powdered sugar and milk, combined, when cool.

title: blueberry angel dessert
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese and sugar; fold in the thawed whipped topping and cake cubes.
Spread evenly into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; cover with pie filling. Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Cut into squares to serve.
May also be layered in a large glass truffle bowl.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Instead of oleo, I spray my skillet with Pam and use 2 tablespoons of corn oil.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add all ingredients and simmer approximately 1 hour.
Remove bay leaf before pouring sauce over spaghetti.

title: dad's turkey stuffing
directions: Boil giblets until tender, saving water.
Chop giblets.
Tear bread into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients together.
Use water from giblets and continue mixing until stuffing is the consistency of a thick paste.
Stuff the bird.
Place what's left in a loaf pan and cook until done (bread like).
Time varies due to amount left.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Use 1 heaping tablespoonful per cup of hot water.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: scottish picnic salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, green onions and mustard and set aside. Flake tuna and toss with dill weed. In 3-quart serving bowl, layer lettuce, shells, cucumber, tomatoes, tuna, peas and bacon. Spread mayonnaise mixture over bacon, sealing to edge of bowl. Sprinkle with cheese and cover. Chill overnight. Toss to serve. Serves 8 to 10.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Stir together flour, salt, soda and sugar; mix in raisins and pecans (if desired).
Mix in buttermilk with wooden spoon.
Knead 1 minute.
Place in greased and floured 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
